{"query": "There's an automatic Day Change punch in in our timesheet. How to avoid that?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to set up auto-punch out for my employees", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times "], "generated_answer": "To avoid automatic Day Change punch-ins, you can set up an auto punch-out time for your employees. Follow these steps:\n\n1. Type 'settings' in Slack and click on the settings panel link.\n2. Scroll down to the \"Time Tracking\" section.\n3. Go to \"General Time Settings\".\n4. Switch the toggle ON for \"Auto punch-out time\".\n5. Update the time at which you want to punch out your employees.\n\nThis will ensure employees are automatically punched out at the specified time, preventing unwanted automatic punch-ins.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118262", "reference_answer": "To avoid automatic Day Change punch-ins, set up an auto punch-out time for your employees by going to the settings in Slack, navigating to the Time Tracking section, and enabling the auto punch-out feature.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "instead of auto punching out, can I set up reminders for people to punch out?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to set up punch in/out reminders", "How to set up auto-punch out for my employees", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times "], "generated_answer": "Yes, you can set up punch out reminders for your team. Here's how:\n\n1. Go to the AttendanceBot dashboard and navigate to Settings -> Basic Settings.\n2. Scroll down to the Time Settings section.\n3. Switch the toggle from \"Inactive\" to \"Active.\"\n4. Click on the edit icon and add the punch out time for the reminder.\n\nThis reminder will be sent to all members of the Slack team at their respective local time.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000049838", "reference_answer": "Yes, you can set up punch out reminders for your team using the AttendanceBot dashboard. Here's how: 1. Go to Settings -> Basic Settings and scroll down to the Time Settings. 2. Switch the toggle from 'Inactive' to 'Active.' 3. Click on the edit icon and add the punch out time. This reminder will be sent to all members of the Slack team at their respective local time.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
