{"query": "can i set up recurring shifts for my team?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to view my shifts and the shifts of my employees", "How to use shift management and create shifts for your team", "How to create and manage open shifts and shift templates"], "generated_answer": "Yes, you can set up recurring shifts for your team in AttendanceBot. Follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to your Settings Panel by sending the command `settings` to the bot and follow the link.\n2. Navigate to Time Tracking --> Shift Management --> Create & View shifts page.\n3. Click on a date for the user you wish to create a shift.\n4. In the dialogue box, set the shift START TIME and END TIME.\n5. Set up SHIFT REPEAT for the shift to repeat on particular day(s) for the next week or month.\n6. Once created, the user will be notified on Slack.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000092410", "reference_answer": "Yes, you can set up recurring shifts for your team in AttendanceBot. Here's how: 1. Go to your Settings Panel by sending the command `settings` to the bot and follow the link. 2. Navigate to Time Tracking --> Shift Management --> Create & View shifts page. 3. Click on a date for the user you wish to create a shift. 4. In the dialogue box, set the shift START TIME and END TIME. 5. Set up SHIFT REPEAT for the shift to repeat on particular day(s) for the next week or month. 6. Once created, the user will be notified on Slack.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
