{"query": "There's an automatic Day Change punch in in our timesheet. How to avoid that?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to set up auto-punch out for my employees", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times "], "generated_answer": "To avoid automatic Day Change punch-ins, you can set up the auto punch-out feature. Here's how:\n\n1. Type 'settings' in Slack and click on the settings panel link provided.\n2. Scroll down to the \"Time Tracking\" section.\n3. Go to \"General Time Settings\".\n4. Switch the toggle ON for \"Auto punch-out time\".\n5. Update the time at which you want to punch out your employees.\n\nThis will ensure that employees are automatically punched out at the specified time, avoiding unintended punch-ins.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118262", "reference_answer": "To avoid automatic Day Change punch-ins, enable the auto punch-out feature in your settings. Go to 'settings' in Slack, find 'Time Tracking', and toggle ON 'Auto punch-out time'. Set your desired punch-out time.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
