{"query": "how to stop daily schedule and notification", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to schedule reports", "How to deactivate a user in AttendanceBot", "How to manage hybrid work schedules (WFO/WFH days) in Slack using AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "To stop a daily schedule and notification in AttendanceBot, you need to manage your hybrid work schedule. Here's how you can do it:\n\n1. From the \"Menu,\" select \"Time off and hybrid work.\"\n2. You will see your current workday schedule. Choose the option to \"Update\" or \"Delete.\"\n3. Select \"Delete\" to eliminate the schedule entirely, which will stop the daily notifications.\n\nIf you need further assistance, please type 'ticket' to open a support ticket.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131569", "reference_answer": "To stop daily schedules and notifications in AttendanceBot, go to 'Time off and hybrid work' in the Menu, then update or delete your current workday schedule. Deleting it will stop the notifications. For more help, type 'ticket' to open a support ticket or visit the support portal: https://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131569.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "What will be our settings if we work on flexible hours, meaning even if outside work hours people can work and just track their hours?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?", "How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?", "Work Model - Hybrid or Fully Remote"], "generated_answer": "For flexible work hours where employees can work outside of standard work hours and track their time, you can configure AttendanceBot to accommodate this by setting up individual work hour settings. Here's how you can do it:\n\n1. Go to the custom field section of your personnel dashboard.\n2. Activate the necessary work hour periods for each employee, choosing from \"Daily Work Hours,\" \"Weekly Work Hours,\" \"Biweekly Work Hours,\" or \"Monthly Work Hours.\"\n3. Set threshold hours for each employee by entering a numerical value in their profile or using the import/export page for bulk settings.\n\nThis setup allows employees to track their hours flexibly while ensuring that any overtime or TOIL is calculated based on the configured thresholds.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000106516", "reference_answer": "To work with flexible hours and track time in AttendanceBot, follow these steps: 1. Set up time tracking by clocking in and out to generate timesheets. 2. Configure individual work hour settings for each employee in the personnel dashboard. 3. Set threshold hours for overtime calculations. 4. Create overtime policies and alerts to manage overhours effectively.", "quality_score": 4.6, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "People work overnight, how to fix their time in and time out", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?", "How to set up auto-punch out for my employees", "How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?"], "generated_answer": "To manage overnight shifts in AttendanceBot, you need to ensure that your time tracking settings accommodate such schedules. Here's how you can address this:\n\n1. Go to the settings panel by typing 'settings' and clicking on the link shared with you.\n2. Navigate to the \"Time Tracking\" section.\n3. Adjust the \"General Time Settings\" to ensure that the time tracking system can handle overnight shifts. This may involve setting appropriate start and end times that span across two different days.\n\nIf further adjustments are needed, such as specific overtime rules for overnight work, you may need to configure overtime settings accordingly.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118262", "reference_answer": "To manage overnight shifts in AttendanceBot, go to the settings panel, navigate to 'Time Tracking', and adjust the 'General Time Settings' to accommodate shifts that span across two days. Ensure overtime rules are configured if necessary.", "quality_score": 4.6, "bucket": "well_answered"}
