{"query": "I can't alter my times on the timesheet or add clock-in/clock-out times", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to approve the timesheets of my reportees"], "generated_answer": "If you're unable to alter your times on the timesheet or add clock-in/clock-out times, it might be because your admin hasn't enabled the \"Allow self editing of punches\" option in the timesheet settings. You should contact your admin to ensure this setting is enabled.\n\nIf the setting is enabled and you're still facing issues, follow these steps to edit your timesheet:\n\n1. From the \"Menu,\" select \"Timesheet actions\" and click on \"Edit\" to access your timesheet editor.\n2. Choose the date range and select the employee (if applicable).\n3. Click \"Expand\" on any day to view or edit specific punches.\n4. To edit, click the pencil icon next to the punch time, update the details, and hit \"save.\"\n5. To add a new entry, click the green \u201cadd punches\u201d button, select the type of entry, fill in the details, and hit \u201csave.\u201d\n\nIf these steps don't resolve your issue, consider opening a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118260", "reference_answer": "If you're unable to alter your times on the timesheet or add clock-in/clock-out times, it might be because your admin hasn't enabled the 'Allow self editing of punches' option. Contact your admin to check this setting. If it's enabled, follow these steps: 1. Go to 'Timesheet actions' and click 'Edit.' 2. Select the date range and employee. 3. Click 'Expand' to edit punches. 4. Click the pencil icon to edit or 'add punches' to add new entries. If issues persist, open a support ticket.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how manager can check report ", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to view all managers and reportees", "What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?", "How can I generate reports?"], "generated_answer": "A manager can check various reports in AttendanceBot by following these steps:\n\n1. To view the team's absence report, type \"team report\" and specify the department.\n2. For the team's timesheet report, type \"timesheet team report\" and specify the office, departments, projects, etc., then hit \"Confirm\" to generate a CSV report.\n3. To get a quick absence summary for a specific reportee, type \"summary @reportee\".\n4. For a quick timesheet report for a specific reportee, type \"timesheet @reportee\".\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118266", "reference_answer": "A manager can check various reports in AttendanceBot by typing 'team report' for absence reports or 'timesheet team report' for timesheet reports, specifying details as needed. For quick summaries, use 'summary @reportee' or 'timesheet @reportee'.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
