{"query": "Hi,\n \nI\u2019m Roy with Jan-Pro of Silicon Valley, helping businesses in San Mateo keep their offices clean, healthy, and professional.\n \nI\u2019d be happy to stop by and provide a complimentary cleaning bid\u2014no obligation.\n \n\u201cJan Pro has been cleaning our business since we opened. They always do a great job. If we need a special request to clean because of an event we held they don't have a problem coming to clean after. Jan Pro has always been very responsive to our requests. The staff is very easy to work with. I would highly recommend working with Jan Pro and their staff.\u201d - Scott M.\nWould a quick visit this week work for you?\n \nBest regards,\n \nRoy Lau\nJan-Pro of Silicon Valley\nroy@janprosiliconvalleyclean.com\n \nRespond with stop to optout.", "retrieved_contexts": [], "generated_answer": "", "reference_answer": "", "quality_score": 0, "bucket": "unknown"}
{"query": "How do I add punches", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times "], "generated_answer": "To add punches in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the settings dashboard and navigate to Time Tracking.\n2. Click on \"Edit Timesheet.\"\n3. Select the date range and employee from the dropdown menu.\n4. Click on \"Add punches.\"\n5. In the dialogue box that opens, fill out the details for Punch In-Out Date & Time.\n6. Hit \"Save\" to create the punch entry.\n\nNote: Employees can only update their punches if the admin has enabled \"Allow self editing of punches\" in timesheet settings.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118266", "reference_answer": "To add punches in AttendanceBot, go to the settings dashboard, navigate to Time Tracking, and click on 'Edit Timesheet.' Select the date range and employee, then click 'Add punches.' Fill in the Punch In-Out Date & Time details and hit 'Save.' Note: Employees can only update their punches if allowed by the admin.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "How do I add a missed punch", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times "], "generated_answer": "To add a missed punch in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the AttendanceBot dashboard and navigate to \"Time Tracking\" and then \"Edit Timesheet.\"\n2. Select the date range and the employee from the dropdown menu.\n3. Click on the \"Add punches\" button.\n4. In the dialogue box that appears, choose the type of entry (e.g., punch in/out pair, single punch in, etc.).\n5. Enter the necessary details such as dates, times, project tags, and any remarks.\n6. Click \"Save\" to create the punch entry.\n\nNote: Employees can only add punches if their admin has enabled \"Allow self editing of punches\" in timesheet settings.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118260", "reference_answer": "To add a missed punch in AttendanceBot, go to the dashboard, navigate to 'Time Tracking' > 'Edit Timesheet', select the date range and employee, click 'Add punches', choose the entry type, enter the details, and click 'Save'. Ensure your admin has enabled 'Allow self editing of punches'.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
