{"query": "how do i create an office wide day off?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?", "How to set up offices and regional holiday calendars", "Taking time off"], "generated_answer": "To create an office-wide day off, follow these steps:\n\n1. Type 'settings' in Slack to access your settings panel.\n2. Click on the \"Offices\" section in the sidebar navigation to manage your offices.\n3. Use the \"Create new\" option if you need to create a new office.\n4. Assign offices to employees by going to the \"People\" option in the sidebar and adding the offices in their profile on the Personnel page.\n5. Once offices are set up, you can create holidays for each office.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000051706", "reference_answer": "To create an office-wide day off, follow these steps: 1. Type 'settings' in Slack to access your settings panel. 2. Click on the 'Offices' section in the sidebar navigation to manage your offices. 3. Use the 'Create new' option if you need to create a new office. 4. Assign offices to employees by going to the 'People' option in the sidebar and adding the offices in their profile on the Personnel page. 5. Once offices are set up, you can create holidays for each office.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
