{"query": "I\u2019m preparing a quick guide for my team on how to use AttendanceBot properly. Can you help me draft a short message?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How can I get help from AttendanceBot support?", "How do I learn more about the product?", "How to setup Slack channel notifications with AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "Certainly! Here's a concise guide for your team on using AttendanceBot:\n\n---\n\n**Welcome to AttendanceBot!**\n\nHere's how you can make the most of it:\n\n1. **Leave Tracking**: Request and approve leave, announce it in channels, and manage leave policies.\n2. **WFO/WFH Planning**: Plan your work-from-office/home days, set schedules, and manage office capacities.\n3. **Time Tracking**: Clock in/out, generate timesheets, manage overtime, and track project time.\n\nFor real-time updates, add AttendanceBot to your Slack channels using \"/invite @attendancebot\".\n\nNeed help? Direct message \"help\" in Slack or contact support at support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com.\n\n---\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118265", "reference_answer": "Here's a concise guide for your team on using AttendanceBot: 1. **Leave Tracking**: Request and approve leave, announce it in channels, and manage leave policies. 2. **WFO/WFH Planning**: Plan your work-from-office/home days, set schedules, and manage office capacities. 3. **Time Tracking**: Clock in/out, generate timesheets, manage overtime, and track project time. For real-time updates, add AttendanceBot to your Slack channels using \"/invite @attendancebot\". Need help? Direct message \"help\" in Slack or contact support at support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "Can you rewrite that focusing on how employees should correctly use clock-in and clock-out to ensure accurate payroll?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?", "How to set up auto-punch out for my employees"], "generated_answer": "I don't have enough information to provide a detailed answer on how employees should correctly use clock-in and clock-out for accurate payroll. You may want to open a support ticket by typing 'ticket' for further assistance.", "reference_answer": "To ensure accurate payroll, employees should follow these steps: 1. Send 'Menu' as a direct message to AttendanceBot to access the options menu. 2. To clock in, select the 'In \u2705' button. If it shows 'Out \u274c,' you're already clocked in. 3. For project tracking, choose a project and confirm to start.", "quality_score": 1.8, "bucket": "content_gap"}
