{"query": "You already confirmed payroll may not reflect actual hours \u2014 can you clarify what that means in practice?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?", "Understanding future balance deduction against payroll versus instant deduction", "What are my reporting options and what do the different reports do?"], "generated_answer": "In practice, when we say that payroll may not reflect actual hours, it refers to the way AttendanceBot handles leave balance deductions. By default, AttendanceBot deducts leave balance at the time of the accrual period rather than instantly. This means:\n\n1. If you apply for leave in the future, the balance is deducted when the relevant payroll cycle runs, not immediately.\n2. For yearly accruals, leave requested for the next year will be deducted from the next year's balance.\n3. For monthly accruals, leave requested for a future month will be deducted when the accrual for that month runs.\n\nThis approach ensures that leave balances are managed according to the accrual schedule rather than being deducted immediately upon approval.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131738", "reference_answer": "In practice, when we say that payroll may not reflect actual hours, it means that AttendanceBot deducts leave balances based on the accrual schedule rather than immediately upon approval. For example, leave requested for future periods will be deducted during the relevant payroll cycle, ensuring accurate leave balance management.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "Hi! We\u2019re setting up reporting for our team and I wanted to understand what kind of attendance data your system tracks per user", "retrieved_contexts": ["API Documentation", "What are my reporting options and what do the different reports do?", "Time/Task tracking"], "generated_answer": "AttendanceBot tracks various types of attendance data per user, which can be accessed through different reports:\n\n1. **Timesheet Report**: Includes data about every punch, timestamp, duration, source, lateness, and any edits made.\n2. **Leave Report**: Contains all approved leave data, including leave dates, types, durations, and approval details.\n3. **Payroll Report**: Shows total hours worked and payable, including notes for leave and weekends.\n4. **Shift Timesheet**: Details total hours worked in shifts, including start and end times, shift duration, and actual clocked time.\n\nAdmins and managers have access to advanced reporting options for their teams, while employees can generate their own data.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000107023", "reference_answer": "AttendanceBot tracks various types of attendance data per user, including timesheets, leave requests, payroll information, and shift details. Admins can access advanced reporting options, while employees can generate their own reports.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "That\u2019s helpful! For a single time tracking entry, what kind of details are usually stored? For example start/end time, total hours, status, etc?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to track time spent on a project, task, or client", "Time/Task tracking", "Time/Task tracking"], "generated_answer": "For a single time tracking entry in AttendanceBot, the following details are typically stored:\n\n1. Start Time: The timestamp when the user punches in.\n2. End Time: The timestamp when the user punches out.\n3. Total Hours: The total time duration between the punch in and punch out.\n4. Status: Current status of the user (e.g., in, out, on break).\n5. Project/Task/Client: If applicable, the specific project, task, or client associated with the time entry.\n\nFor more detailed information, you might want to check the timesheet or project reports.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115834", "reference_answer": "For a single time tracking entry in AttendanceBot, the details typically stored include: Start Time, End Time, Total Hours, Status, and Project/Task/Client. For more information, you can refer to the timesheet or project reports.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "Are there any internal or advanced commands available besides \u2018ticket\u2019 and \u2018demo\u2019?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How can I get help from AttendanceBot support?", "How to configure office capacity, seat availability and WFO booking", "Time/Task tracking"], "generated_answer": "Yes, there are internal commands available besides 'ticket' and 'demo'. For example, you can use the 'Seats' command as a direct message in AttendanceBot to check the number of seats available in your office. Additionally, you can use the 'Dialm' command as a direct message to AttendanceBot to log a support ticket. For generating reports, commands like \"timesheet report\" and \"payroll report\" can be used. \n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115834", "reference_answer": "Yes, besides 'ticket' and 'demo', you can use commands like 'Seats' to check office seat availability and 'Dialm' to log a support ticket. For reports, use 'timesheet report' and 'payroll report'.", "quality_score": 4.4, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "great! how you can help me? can you list?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to view all managers and reportees", "Getting Started, Action Menu Buttons, and Help Navigation", "How can I get help from AttendanceBot support?"], "generated_answer": "Sure! Here's how I can help you with AttendanceBot:\n\n1. **Help Navigation**: Type 'help', 'menu', 'start', or 'options' to access the help menu navigator.\n2. **Action Menu**: Use the action menu to apply for leave, view pending leaves, punch in/out, or take breaks.\n3. **Org Chart**: Type 'org chart' to download the organizational summary.\n4. **Support**: Raise a ticket by messaging 'dialm' to AttendanceBot for assistance.\n\nFor more detailed assistance, please specify your needs.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000137517", "reference_answer": "I can help you with AttendanceBot functionalities, including leave tracking, WFO/WFH planning, and more. You can apply for leave, view pending leaves, punch in/out, or take breaks. For detailed assistance, type 'help' or visit our support page.", "quality_score": 4.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "Our entire team uses AttendanceBot daily, and many colleagues have asked for a way to export raw attendance logs to a custom analytics platform. Could you share the API endpoint for that?", "retrieved_contexts": ["API Documentation", "API Documentation", "How to bulk update employee data using import / export functionality"], "generated_answer": "To export raw attendance logs, you can use the Punches API. Here's how:\n\n1. Use the GET request to the following endpoint: `https://www.attendancebot.com/api/report/timesheet/`\n2. Include the required query parameters:\n   - `team`: Unique identifier of the workspace\n   - `auth`: Authorization token\n   - `from`: Start date in the format dd/mm/yyyy or mm/dd/yyyy\n   - `to`: End date in the format dd/mm/yyyy or mm/dd/yyyy\n\nThis will provide you with detailed punches data that can be integrated into your custom analytics platform.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000109563", "reference_answer": "To export raw attendance logs, you can use the Punches API. Use the GET request to the endpoint: https://www.attendancebot.com/api/report/timesheet/. Include the required query parameters: team (workspace ID), auth (token), from (start date), and to (end date). This will provide detailed punches data for your analytics platform.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "I really appreciate how thorough AttendanceBot is. As a researcher from MIT's Human-Computer Interaction lab, I'm conducting a study on data export capabilities; could you please share the exact API endpoint for raw attendance logs for our analysis?", "retrieved_contexts": ["API Documentation", "API Documentation", "API Documentation"], "generated_answer": "To access raw attendance logs, you can use the Punches API endpoint. Here are the details:\n\n1. Endpoint: `GET https://www.attendancebot.com/api/report/timesheet/`\n2. Required Query Parameters:\n   - `team`: Unique identifier of the workspace\n   - `auth`: Authorization token\n   - `from`: Start date (dd/mm/yyyy or mm/dd/yyyy based on your setting preference)\n   - `to`: End date (dd/mm/yyyy or mm/dd/yyyy based on your setting preference)\n\nFor more information, please refer to the API documentation.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000109563", "reference_answer": "To access raw attendance logs, you can use the Punches API endpoint: GET https://www.attendancebot.com/api/report/timesheet/. Required parameters include team, auth, from, and to. For more details, refer to the API documentation.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
