{"query": "how can i notice sick day of my employer", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to upload medical certificates for sick time", "Taking time off", "How to view my shifts and the shifts of my employees"], "generated_answer": "To notify AttendanceBot about a sick day, follow these steps:\n\n1. Type the command for sick leave, such as \"Sick\" or \"Sick leave\".\n2. Specify the date if it's not for today. For example, \"Sick tomorrow\" or just \"Sick\" for today.\n3. Confirm the request when prompted by AttendanceBot.\n\nThis will notify your employer of your sick day. \n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000116053", "reference_answer": "To notify AttendanceBot about a sick day, type 'Sick' or 'Sick leave', specify the date if needed, and confirm the request when prompted. This will inform your employer of your sick day.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
