{"query": "how can i make a time tracking report?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to track time spent on a project, task, or client", "How do I get the summary or report of my time in office?", "How to track time spent on a project, task, or client"], "generated_answer": "To create a time tracking report, follow these steps:\n\n1. Type \"timesheet\" in Slack to get a summary of your punch logs for the current day.\n2. For a report of your time in office for the current or previous month, type \"timesheet report\" to receive a downloadable CSV report.\n3. To generate a report for a specific time period, append the date range to the command, e.g., \"Timesheet Report jan 3 to feb 10\".\n4. Managers can type \"Report\" and select the report type as Timesheet Report/Timesheet Summary Report, then confirm to download a CSV report.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118258", "reference_answer": "To create a time tracking report in AttendanceBot, type 'timesheet' for a daily summary or 'timesheet report' for a downloadable CSV of your time in office. For specific date ranges, use 'Timesheet Report [start date] to [end date]'. Managers can also access reports through the options menu.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "i need a report with all user active", "retrieved_contexts": ["How can I generate reports?", "How to generate a report with specific filters", "How do I get the summary or report of my time in office?"], "generated_answer": "To generate a report with all active users in Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Type the command \"report\" as a direct message to AttendanceBot.\n2. Follow the prompt to select the report type and enter the necessary details like duration.\n3. Use filters if needed to specify active users.\n4. Hit \"Confirm\" to generate the report.\n5. Hover over the report and click the Download button to download it.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000093467", "reference_answer": "To generate a report with all active users in Slack, type 'report' in a direct message to AttendanceBot, follow the prompts to select the report type, specify filters if needed, and confirm to generate and download the report.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
