{"query": "On our teams channel.. I dont get my \"Personnel\" Duwyne to report when he logs in.. it only posts when he logs out.. why is this? All the other \"personal\" I see both in and out", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I find my missing employee profile on the dashboard? (Slack)", "How to view employee status on a dashboard or in Slack", "Time/Task tracking"], "generated_answer": "To ensure that Duwyne's punch-in status is reported in the channel, follow these steps:\n\n1. Verify if Duwyne's profile is active in AttendanceBot:\n   - Go to \"Settings\" > \"People\" > \"Personnel\".\n   - Toggle off \"Show active personnel only\".\n   - If Duwyne's profile is found, ensure it is marked as \"active\".\n\n2. Check if the channel notifications are configured correctly:\n   - The admin should go to the settings dashboard by typing \"settings\".\n   - Navigate to the \"Notification\" section and ensure that notifications for both punch-in and punch-out are enabled for the channel.\n\nIf the issue persists, try re-syncing:\n- Click the teal \"RE-SYNC\" button in the \"Personnel\" section and wait 1-4 hours.\n\nIf these steps don't resolve the issue, consider opening a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131680", "reference_answer": "To ensure Duwyne's punch-in status is reported, check if his profile is active in AttendanceBot, verify channel notification settings for both punch-in and punch-out, and re-sync if necessary. If the issue persists, open a support ticket.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "Time entered incorrect for today Arrived at 7:15 am ", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to apply for time off for half a day or few hours?", "What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?"], "generated_answer": "To correct the time entry for today in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. From the \"Menu,\" select \"Timesheet actions.\"\n2. Click on \u201cEdit\u201d to open your timesheet editor on the dashboard.\n3. Find today's date and click \"Expand\" to view the minute-by-minute punch history.\n4. Locate the incorrect punch entry and click the pencil icon to edit it.\n5. Update the time to 7:15 am and hit \"Save.\"\n\nThis will update your punch time and flag the change in the system.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118260", "reference_answer": "To correct the time entry for today in AttendanceBot, follow these steps: 1. From the 'Menu,' select 'Timesheet actions.' 2. Click on 'Edit' to open your timesheet editor on the dashboard. 3. Find today's date and click 'Expand' to view the minute-by-minute punch history. 4. Locate the incorrect punch entry and click the pencil icon to edit it. 5. Update the time to 7:15 am and hit 'Save.' This will update your punch time and flag the change in the system.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
