{"query": "i need to cancel anapproved vacation for a person", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to change or edit an existing approved leave", "How to cancel / retract / rescind / delete a leave request", "How to delete approved leave for a reportee or employee"], "generated_answer": "To cancel an approved vacation for a team member, follow these steps:\n\n1. In Slack, type the command \"delete @username\" to AttendanceBot, replacing \"@username\" with the Slack username of the team member.\n2. A list of approved leaves for that user will appear, starting with upcoming leaves.\n3. Click the \"Delete\" button below the leave you wish to cancel.\n4. You will receive a Slack confirmation, and the team member will be notified of the cancellation.\n\nIf you can't find the leave, scroll to the bottom and click \"show more\" to load additional leaves.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000093812", "reference_answer": "To cancel an approved vacation for a team member in AttendanceBot, type 'delete @username' in Slack, select the leave to cancel, and confirm the deletion.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "If someone forgot to check in how should I mark it?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I find my missing employee profile on the dashboard? (Slack)", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "Time/Task tracking"], "generated_answer": "To mark a missed check-in, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the AttendanceBot dashboard.\n2. Navigate to Time Tracking and select Edit Timesheet for the specific user.\n3. Click on the green \u201cadd punches\u201d button to open the punch entry menu.\n4. Choose the type of entry (e.g., single punch in) and enter the necessary details like date, time, project tags, and remarks.\n5. Hit \u201csave\u201d to create the punch entry.\n\nNote: Ensure that the \"Allow self editing of punches\" option is enabled in timesheet settings if employees need to update their punches themselves.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118260", "reference_answer": "To mark a missed check-in, go to the AttendanceBot dashboard, navigate to Time Tracking, select Edit Timesheet for the user, click 'add punches', choose the entry type, enter the details, and save. Ensure 'Allow self editing of punches' is enabled if needed.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "How to add someone to attendance bot that is already using slack and was set to inactive before?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I install AttendanceBot in Slack?", "How do I invite new users on my team to start using AttendanceBot?", "Adding New Users to Hangouts/Google Chat"], "generated_answer": "To add someone to AttendanceBot who is already using Slack and was previously set to inactive, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open the 'settings' dashboard and go to the People --> Personnel tab. You can access this directly by messaging 'profile'.\n2. Ensure the \"Show active personnel only\" toggle is turned off to view inactive users.\n3. Use the search bar or scroll to find the user's profile.\n4. Toggle their status to \"Active\" on the right side of their profile.\n5. Optionally, update additional fields such as manager, office, department, and join date by clicking on their name.\n6. You can send a welcome message by going to the Invite page (People > Invite), selecting the employee, and sending the default or a custom message.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115576", "reference_answer": "To add someone to AttendanceBot who is already using Slack and was previously set to inactive, go to the People --> Personnel tab in the settings dashboard, turn off the 'Show active personnel only' toggle, find the user, toggle their status to 'Active', and optionally update their details. You can also send a welcome message from the Invite page.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "OK where do I find a sick leave report for the year?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to download team vacation data and reporting", "How to upload medical certificates for sick time", "What are my reporting options and what do the different reports do?"], "generated_answer": "To find a sick leave report for the year, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open the \"Menu\" and select \"Data & Integrations\".\n2. Click on \"Reports\" and choose the \"Leave Report\" for a history of all approved leaves.\n3. Select the date range for the year you are interested in. You can choose a preset duration or specify your own date range.\n4. Decide if you want to download data for all employees (based on your permissions) or a specific employee, office, or department.\n5. Hit \"Confirm\" to download the report.\n\nAlternatively, you can message \"leave report <start_date> to <end_date>\" to AttendanceBot for a quick download.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000063984", "reference_answer": "To find a sick leave report for the year, open the 'Menu', select 'Data & Integrations', click on 'Reports', and choose 'Leave Report'. Set the date range for the year and download the report. Alternatively, message 'leave report <start_date> to <end_date>' to AttendanceBot.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
