{"query": "Request time off", "retrieved_contexts": ["Taking time off", "How to apply for time off for half a day or few hours?", "How to configure and use time-off-in-lieu (TOIL) (Slack)"], "generated_answer": "To request time off using AttendanceBot in Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Type the command with the leave type name, followed by the date. For example, \"Vacation 05/04 to 05/07\" for a 4-day leave.\n2. Alternatively, use a conversational approach like \"WFH tomorrow\" or \"Sick\" for today.\n3. Specify dates using formats like MM-DD, MM/DD, or phrases like \"today\", \"tomorrow\", etc.\n4. AttendanceBot will verify the dates before recording your leave request.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000116053", "reference_answer": "To request time off using AttendanceBot in Slack, type the command with the leave type and dates, like 'Vacation 05/04 to 05/07'. You can also say 'WFH tomorrow' or 'Sick' for today. AttendanceBot will verify the dates before recording your request.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
