{"query": "how do i log a task", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to Configure Project, Client, and Task / Subproject Tracking in AttendanceBot", "Time/Task tracking", "How to Configure Project, Client, and Task / Subproject Tracking in AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "To log a task in AttendanceBot, you need to create a sub-project within an existing project. Here's how:\n\n1. Open a project by clicking the circular arrow icon at the bottom right of the project tile.\n2. Click on the \u201cSub Projects\u201d tab at the top.\n3. Click \u201cCreate New.\u201d\n4. Name and optionally describe the sub-project.\n5. Assign employees to the sub-project. By default, all employees assigned to the main project will be included, but you can modify this as needed.\n6. Click \u201cCreate Sub Project\u201d when ready.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000138976", "reference_answer": "To log a task in AttendanceBot, create a sub-project within an existing project by following these steps: Open the project, click on 'Sub Projects', create a new sub-project, name it, assign employees, and click 'Create Sub Project'. For more details, visit the documentation: https://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000138976.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how do i log my hours?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to send hours to Gusto for payroll", "How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?", "How do I get the summary or report of my time in office?"], "generated_answer": "To log your hours in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Type \"in\" in your chat app (Slack, MS Teams, or Google Chat) to start logging your hours.\n2. When you finish working, type \"out\" to stop logging your hours.\n3. If you want to track time spent on specific projects, include the project name after \"in\" or \"out\" (e.g., \"in ProjectX\").\n\nThis will help you keep track of your work hours and project time efficiently. \n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000112898", "reference_answer": "To log your hours in AttendanceBot, send 'Menu' as a direct message to AttendanceBot. Select the 'In \u2705' button to start recording your hours. If it says 'Out \u274c', you're already signed in. To stop recording, select the 'Out \u274c' button. For breaks or lunch, use the appropriate options in the menu.", "quality_score": 4.2, "bucket": "partial"}
{"query": "how do i specify what I'm doing with that time?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to track time spent on a project, task, or client", "How to track time spent on a project, task, or client", "Taking time off"], "generated_answer": "To specify what you're doing with your time in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure your admin has configured projects, tasks, or clients in AttendanceBot.\n2. When you punch in, select the appropriate client, project, or task from the menu.\n3. Alternatively, type \"in\" or \"out\" directly to AttendanceBot for faster toggling between projects.\n4. Each punch will be tagged with the selected project, client, or task for detailed reporting and analytics.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000051253", "reference_answer": "To specify what you're doing with your time in AttendanceBot, ensure your admin has set up projects or tasks. When you punch in, select the appropriate project, task, or client from the menu. You can also type 'in' or 'out' for quick toggling. Each entry will be tagged for reporting.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how do i create a task?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to Configure Project, Client, and Task / Subproject Tracking in AttendanceBot", "How to Configure Project, Client, and Task / Subproject Tracking in AttendanceBot", "How to use Slack onboarding functionality"], "generated_answer": "To create a task (sub-project) within an existing project in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open a project by clicking the circular arrow icon at the bottom right of the project tile.\n2. Click on the \u201cSub Projects\u201d tab at the top.\n3. Click \u201cCreate New.\u201d\n4. Name and optionally describe the sub-project.\n5. Assign employees to the sub-project. By default, all employees assigned to the main project will be included, but you can add or remove employees as needed.\n6. Click \u201cCreate Sub Project\u201d when ready.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000138976", "reference_answer": "To create a task (sub-project) within an existing project in AttendanceBot, follow these steps: 1. Open a project by clicking the circular arrow icon at the bottom right of the project tile. 2. Click on the 'Sub Projects' tab at the top. 3. Click 'Create New.' 4. Name and optionally describe the sub-project. 5. Assign employees to the sub-project. By default, all employees assigned to the main project will be included, but you can add or remove employees as needed. 6. Click 'Create Sub Project' when ready.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "does attendancebot integrate with other applications?", "retrieved_contexts": ["I don't use Slack or Microsoft Teams. Can I still use AttendanceBot?", "How do I install AttendanceBot in Slack?", "How to integrate your calendar with AttendanceBot for Slack"], "generated_answer": "Yes, AttendanceBot integrates with calendars such as Google Calendar and Outlook. You can subscribe to a public calendar to view your team's leave or integrate with a personal calendar to automatically block out unavailable time based on the AttendanceBot calendar.\n\nTo integrate a calendar:\n1. Go to the \"menu\" and select \"data & integrations.\"\n2. Select \"Calendar\" on the sub-menu.\n3. Use the \"Enable\" or \"Get link\" buttons based on your integration type.\n\nFor detailed steps on integrating with specific calendars like Apple Calendar, Google Calendar, or Outlook, please refer to the documentation.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000017361", "reference_answer": "Yes, AttendanceBot integrates with calendars like Google Calendar and Outlook. You can subscribe to a public calendar to view your team's leave or integrate with a personal calendar to block out unavailable time. For integration, go to 'data & integrations' in the menu, select 'Calendar', and use the 'Enable' or 'Get link' buttons. For detailed steps, refer to the documentation.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
