{"query": "can I create a channel where everyone can punch IN, OUT, BREAK and LUNCH?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to announce in/out and breaks/lunch on a Slack channel", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How do I apply for lunch or break with AttendanceBot in Slack?"], "generated_answer": "Yes, you can create a Slack channel where everyone can punch IN, OUT, BREAK, and LUNCH using AttendanceBot. Follow these steps:\n\n1. Add AttendanceBot to the relevant Slack channel by typing `@attendancebot` in the channel, sending `/invite @attendancebot`, or adding it through the channel's integrations tab.\n2. Navigate to \"Settings, people, policy\" > \"Notifications\" in the AttendanceBot menu.\n3. Click on \"Create new\" to configure a notification rule.\n4. Select the \"In/Out Notifications\" tile, configure the channel, people, and timing, then save changes.\n5. For break and lunch notifications, create an additional \"Break/Lunch notifications\" rule with similar configurations.\n6. Optionally, create a \"Punch card\" notification to announce status snapshots at specific times.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000049835", "reference_answer": "Yes, you can create a Slack channel where everyone can punch IN, OUT, BREAK, and LUNCH using AttendanceBot. Add AttendanceBot to the channel, configure notification rules for In/Out and Break/Lunch, and optionally set up Punch card notifications for status updates.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
