{"query": "Can I please get a copy of the invoice 967C769F-0054?", "retrieved_contexts": ["Billing - how do I download past invoices or receipts?", "Billing - can I get a discount as a non-profit organization using AttendanceBot?", "API Documentation"], "generated_answer": "To get a copy of the invoice, please follow these steps:\n\n1. Send a direct message to AttendanceBot with the command \"Settings\".\n2. Click on the link prompted to access the settings dashboard.\n3. Navigate to the \"Subscription\" tab to find your invoice number.\n4. Share the invoice number with our support team by raising a ticket using the command \"Dialm\" or start a live chat.\n5. Our team will email the invoice to you.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131565", "reference_answer": "To get a copy of invoice 967C769F-0054, please send a direct message to AttendanceBot with the command 'Settings', access the settings dashboard, navigate to the 'Subscription' tab, and share the invoice number with our support team via a ticket or live chat. Our team will email the invoice to you.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "I need to punch in for 3/13 at 1 pm and punch out for 4pm", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to set up auto-punch out for my employees"], "generated_answer": "To add a new punch entry for March 13th from 1 PM to 4 PM, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to your timesheet in AttendanceBot.\n2. Click on the green \u201cadd punches\u201d button to open the punch entry menu.\n3. Choose the type of entry you need (punch in/out pair).\n4. Enter the date as March 13th and the times as 1 PM for punch in and 4 PM for punch out.\n5. Add any project tags or remarks if necessary.\n6. Hit \u201csave\u201d to create the punch entry.\n\nNote: Ensure that your admin has enabled \"Allow self editing of punches\" in timesheet settings for you to make these changes.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118260", "reference_answer": "To punch in for 3/13 at 1 PM and punch out at 4 PM, follow these steps: 1. Go to your timesheet in AttendanceBot. 2. Click on the green 'add punches' button. 3. Choose punch in/out pair. 4. Enter the date as March 13th and times as 1 PM and 4 PM. 5. Add project tags if needed. 6. Hit 'save'. Ensure self-editing is enabled.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "How dobi clock in?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to track time in Slack using AttendanceBot", "Time/Task tracking", "Time/Task tracking"], "generated_answer": "To clock in using AttendanceBot in Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Send \"Menu\" as a direct message to AttendanceBot.\n2. In the menu that appears, select the \"In \u2705\" button to start recording your hours.\n3. If you're tracking projects, choose a project from the menu and confirm your selection.\n\nAlternatively, you can simply type \"in\" as a direct message to AttendanceBot to clock in.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118256", "reference_answer": "To clock in using AttendanceBot in Slack, send 'Menu' to AttendanceBot and select 'In \u2705' or simply type 'in' to clock in directly.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "How do I set a time in and time out?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to set up auto-punch out for my employees", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times "], "generated_answer": "To set a time in and time out in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Access the \"Menu\" and select \"Timesheet actions.\"\n2. Click on \u201cEdit\u201d to open your timesheet editor on the dashboard.\n3. To add a new punch entry, click the green \u201cadd punches\u201d button.\n4. Choose the type of entry (punch in/out pair, punch out/in pair, single punch in, single punch out, or lunch/break).\n5. Enter the dates, times, any project tags, and remarks.\n6. Hit \u201csave\u201d to create the punch entry.\n\nNote: You can only update punches if your admin has enabled \"Allow self editing of punches.\"\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118260", "reference_answer": "To set a time in and time out in AttendanceBot, access the 'Menu' and select 'Timesheet actions.' Click 'Edit' to open your timesheet editor, then click the green 'add punches' button. Choose the type of entry, enter the dates and times, and hit 'save.' Note: You can only update punches if your admin has enabled 'Allow self editing of punches.'", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
