{"query": "how can i create a new project?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to Configure Project, Client, and Task / Subproject Tracking in AttendanceBot", "How to Configure Project, Client, and Task / Subproject Tracking in AttendanceBot", "How to track time spent on a project, task, or client"], "generated_answer": "To create a new project in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to your dashboard and find the \u201cTime Tracking\u201d section.\n2. Click on the \u201cProjects and Clients\u201d page.\n3. Click the blue \u201cCreate New\u201d button at the top right.\n4. Assign a name to the project and optionally describe it.\n5. If the project is for a specific client, select a client or create a new one.\n6. Choose between self-assign or managed assignment for project assignment.\n7. Select the employees to assign to the project.\n8. Click \u201cCreate Project\u201d to finish.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000138976", "reference_answer": "To create a new project in AttendanceBot, follow these steps: 1. Go to your dashboard and find the 'Time Tracking' section. 2. Click on the 'Projects and Clients' page. 3. Click the blue 'Create New' button at the top right. 4. Assign a name to the project and optionally describe it. 5. If the project is for a specific client, select a client or create a new one. 6. Choose between self-assign or managed assignment for project assignment. 7. Select the employees to assign to the project. 8. Click 'Create Project' to finish.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
