{"query": "how do i stop free trial", "retrieved_contexts": ["How long is my AttendanceBot trial?", "How do I uninstall AttendanceBot from Google Chat ?", "How to uninstall AttendanceBot from Slack"], "generated_answer": "AttendanceBot offers a 14-day free trial on Slack. If you want to stop using AttendanceBot after the trial, you don't need to do anything specific as we won't auto-charge your credit card. If you have more than 5 users and don't subscribe, the app will simply stop working after the trial. If you want to uninstall AttendanceBot from Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Select the AttendanceBot app on Slack and click on the \u201cAbout\" tab.\n2. Select the \"Configuration\" tab to be redirected to the Slack app directory page.\n3. Scroll down to the Remove Application section and click on the Remove App button.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115577", "reference_answer": "To stop your AttendanceBot free trial, you don't need to take any action as there is no auto-charge. If you have more than 5 users and don't subscribe, the app will stop working after the trial. To uninstall AttendanceBot from Slack, go to the app, click on 'About', then 'Configuration', and remove the app from the Slack app directory.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "stop subscription", "retrieved_contexts": ["Billing - how does adding or removing users affect my billing?", "How do I change my credit card details?", "How to uninstall AttendanceBot from Slack"], "generated_answer": "To stop your AttendanceBot subscription, you will need to uninstall the app from Slack. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n1. Select the AttendanceBot app on Slack and click on the \u201cAbout\" tab.\n2. Select the \"Configuration\" tab to be redirected to the Slack app directory page.\n3. Scroll down to the Remove Application section and click on the Remove App button to remove it from your workspace.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000121227", "reference_answer": "To stop your AttendanceBot subscription, uninstall the app from Slack by going to the AttendanceBot app, clicking on the 'About' tab, then 'Configuration', and finally removing the app from your workspace.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how can i check on slack everyone who is active?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to view employee status on a dashboard or in Slack", "How to check leave balance in Slack with AttendanceBot", "How do I find my missing employee profile on the dashboard? (Slack)"], "generated_answer": "To check who is active on Slack using AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. If your team is auto-syncing their punch status with AttendanceBot, their Slack status will indicate whether they\u2019re in, out, on break/lunch, on leave, or working from home.\n2. To get a text summary of everyone\u2019s status, direct message AttendanceBot with \"punch card.\" This will provide a snapshot of the punch board information in text format.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000052710", "reference_answer": "To check who is active on Slack using AttendanceBot, you can see their Slack status if they are auto-syncing their punch status. You can also DM AttendanceBot with 'punch card' for a summary of everyone's status.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "is there a way to update slack status depending on punch in or out", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to view employee status on a dashboard or in Slack", "How to configure punch in/out alerts for reportees (Slack)", "How to set up punch in/out reminders"], "generated_answer": "Yes, you can update Slack status based on punch in or out using AttendanceBot. If your team is auto-syncing their punch status with AttendanceBot, their Slack status will automatically show whether they\u2019re in, out, on break/lunch, on leave, or working from home (wfh). \n\nTo view a text summary of everyone's status, you can direct message AttendanceBot with \"punch card\" to get a snapshot of punch board information in text format.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000052710", "reference_answer": "Yes, you can update your Slack status based on punch in or out using AttendanceBot. If your team is auto-syncing their punch status, their Slack status will reflect their current state (in, out, on break/lunch, on leave, or working from home). To set this up, go to AttendanceBot's options menu, select 'data and integrations,' then 'Slack Status,' and authorize the integration. You can also DM AttendanceBot with 'punch card' for a summary of everyone's status.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "there's no menu", "retrieved_contexts": ["Getting Started, Action Menu Buttons, and Help Navigation", "How to view and claim open shifts", "How to track time in Slack using AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "To access the AttendanceBot menu in Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Send a direct message with the word \"menu\" to AttendanceBot.\n2. This will open the help menu navigator.\n3. You will see up to four action categories based on your permissions and account features.\n4. Click into a category to see specific actions and use the \"return to menu\" option if needed.\n\nIf you're still having trouble, please ensure you're messaging AttendanceBot directly and check your permissions. If the issue persists, consider opening a support ticket by typing 'ticket'. \n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000137517", "reference_answer": "To access the AttendanceBot menu in Slack, send a direct message with the word 'menu' to AttendanceBot. This will open the help menu navigator where you can see action categories based on your permissions. If you have trouble, check your permissions or open a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "How do I set the timer for out?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to set up auto-punch out for my employees", "How to set up punch in/out reminders", "How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?"], "generated_answer": "To set up a punch-out reminder for your team, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the AttendanceBot dashboard.\n2. Navigate to Settings -> Basic Settings.\n3. Scroll down to the Time Settings section.\n4. Switch the toggle from \"Inactive\" to \"Active.\"\n5. Click on the edit icon and add the punch-out time.\n\nThis will send a reminder to all team members at their respective local times.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000049838", "reference_answer": "To set the timer for 'out' in AttendanceBot, you can simply punch out by typing 'out' in your communication platform (Slack or MS Teams). This will record your punch-out time. For setting up reminders, go to the AttendanceBot dashboard, navigate to Settings -> Basic Settings, and configure the punch-out reminder as needed.", "quality_score": 3.6, "bucket": "partial"}
{"query": "It automatically presses out by 6pm but I want it to be 8pm", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to set up auto-punch out for my employees", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to round Slack punch timings to the nearest minute, 6 minutes, 7 minutes, 15 minutes, or more"], "generated_answer": "To change the auto punch-out time to 8 PM, follow these steps:\n\n1. Type 'settings' in Slack to access the settings panel.\n2. Scroll down to the \"Time Tracking\" section.\n3. Go to \"General Time Settings.\"\n4. Switch the toggle ON for \"Auto punch-out time.\"\n5. Update the time to 8 PM.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118262", "reference_answer": "To change the auto punch-out time to 8 PM, follow these steps: 1. Type 'settings' in Slack to access the settings panel. 2. Scroll down to the 'Time Tracking' section. 3. Go to 'General Time Settings.' 4. Switch the toggle ON for 'Auto punch-out time.' 5. Update the time to 8 PM.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
