{"query": "i want to edit my punches", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?"], "generated_answer": "To edit your punches in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. From the \"Menu,\" select \"Timesheet actions.\"\n2. Click on \u201cEdit\u201d to access your timesheet editor on the dashboard.\n3. Choose the date range using the \u201cDate Range\u201d dropdown.\n4. Click \"expand\" on any day to view the punch history.\n5. To edit a punch, click the pencil icon next to the punch entry, update the details, and hit \"save.\"\n6. To delete a punch, click the trashcan icon and confirm the deletion.\n\nNote: You can only edit punches if your admin has enabled \"Allow self editing of punches\" in the timesheet settings.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118260", "reference_answer": "To edit your punches in AttendanceBot, follow these steps: 1. From the 'Menu,' select 'Timesheet actions.' 2. Click on 'Edit' to access your timesheet editor. 3. Choose the date range using the 'Date Range' dropdown. 4. Click 'expand' on any day to view the punch history. 5. To edit a punch, click the pencil icon next to the punch entry, update the details, and hit 'save.' 6. To delete a punch, click the trashcan icon and confirm the deletion. Note: You can only edit punches if your admin has enabled 'Allow self editing of punches' in the timesheet settings.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how do i setup an hours limit", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to setup lunch hours for your team", "How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?", "How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?"], "generated_answer": "To set up an hours limit in AttendanceBot, you need to configure the work hour periods for each employee. Here's how you can do it:\n\n1. Go to the custom field section of your personnel dashboard.\n2. Browse the relevant fields for \"work hours.\"\n3. Activate the necessary work hour periods: Daily, Weekly, Biweekly, or Monthly.\n4. For each employee, input a numerical value into the appropriate work hour field to set the threshold hours.\n5. Alternatively, use the import/export page to set thresholds in bulk.\n\nNote: Each employee can only have one period active at a time.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000106516", "reference_answer": "To set up an hours limit in AttendanceBot, follow these steps: 1. Go to the custom field section of your personnel dashboard. 2. Browse the relevant fields for 'work hours.' 3. Activate the work hour periods you need (Daily, Weekly, Biweekly, or Monthly). 4. For each employee, input a numerical value into the appropriate work hour field to set the threshold hours. 5. Alternatively, use the import/export page to set thresholds in bulk. Note: Each employee can only have one period active at a time.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how to file pto request", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to request hourly or half day leave", "How to configure and use time-off-in-lieu (TOIL) (Slack)", "How to upload medical certificates for sick time"], "generated_answer": "To file a PTO (Paid Time Off) request using AttendanceBot in Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Message \"menu\" to AttendanceBot to open the options menu navigator.\n2. Select \u2018Apply\u2019 to open a request form.\n3. Choose the leave type as PTO.\n4. Under \u201cLeave Duration,\u201d select the appropriate duration (full day, few hours, or first/second half).\n5. Submit your request.\n\nNote: If you need to request PTO in increments of less than 15 minutes, use the command shortcut by messaging AttendanceBot with the type and timing, like \u201cpto tomorrow 8:30 to 10:20 am\u201d.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000049824", "reference_answer": "To file a PTO request using AttendanceBot in Slack, message 'menu' to open the options menu. Select 'Apply' to access the request form, choose PTO as the leave type, specify the duration, and submit your request. For increments under 15 minutes, use a command like 'pto tomorrow 8:30 to 10:20 am'.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "Is AttendanceBot free for businesses with less than 5 users?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How long is my AttendanceBot trial?", "I don't use Slack or Microsoft Teams. Can I still use AttendanceBot?", "Billing - can I get a discount as a non-profit organization using AttendanceBot?"], "generated_answer": "Yes, AttendanceBot is free for teams with 5 users or less. If you have more than 5 members, you will need to subscribe to the app.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115577", "reference_answer": "Yes, AttendanceBot is free for teams with 5 users or less. For teams with more than 5 members, a subscription is required.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "Is AttendanceBot free for businesses with less than 5 users?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How long is my AttendanceBot trial?", "I don't use Slack or Microsoft Teams. Can I still use AttendanceBot?", "Billing - can I get a discount as a non-profit organization using AttendanceBot?"], "generated_answer": "Yes, AttendanceBot is free for teams with 5 users or less. If your team has more than 5 members, you will need to subscribe to the app. \n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115577", "reference_answer": "Yes, AttendanceBot is free for businesses with 5 users or less. If your team has more than 5 members, you will need to subscribe to the app. For more details, you can check out the pricing plans.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "What features does the free version have for businesses with 5 users or less?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How long is my AttendanceBot trial?", "AttendanceBot Plans and Features", "AttendanceBot Plans and Features"], "generated_answer": "For businesses with 5 users or less, the free version of AttendanceBot includes the following features:\n\n1. Time Tracking & Editing: Basic clock in/out functionality with optional editing of work hours.\n2. Hybrid Statusing: Unlimited hybrid statuses like work from home, office, field, onsite, travel, etc.\n3. Custom Leave Types & Approvals: Manage leave without balance limitations or accruals, with customized leave rules and streamlined approval processes.\n4. Real-time Reports: Download essential reports in CSV/Excel format on demand.\n5. Timely Reminders, Notifications, and Announcements: Receive alerts, reminders, and notifications for shifts, approvals, and daily punches.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000138965", "reference_answer": "For businesses with 5 users or less, the free version of AttendanceBot includes time tracking, hybrid statusing, custom leave types, real-time reports, and timely reminders.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "is there a way to edit punches to do multiple days at once", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?"], "generated_answer": "To edit punches for multiple days at once in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the \"Menu\" and select \"Timesheet actions.\"\n2. Click on \u201cEdit\u201d to access your timesheet editor.\n3. Use the \u201cDate Range\u201d dropdown to select the desired range of days.\n4. Once the data is loaded, expand each day to view or edit specific punches.\n5. Click the pencil icon to edit punches for each day and hit \"save\" after making changes.\n\nNote: You need to edit each day's punches individually within the selected range.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118260", "reference_answer": "To edit punches for multiple days at once in AttendanceBot, go to 'Menu' > 'Timesheet actions', click 'Edit', select a date range, and edit each day's punches individually. Remember to save your changes.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "a new user is not showing here", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I invite new users on my team to start using AttendanceBot?", "Adding New Users to Hangouts/Google Chat", "How to inactivate users?"], "generated_answer": "If a new user is not showing in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open the 'settings' dashboard and go to People --> Personnel tab. You can access this directly by messaging 'profile' to AttendanceBot.\n2. Ensure the \"Show active personnel only\" toggle is turned off to view all users.\n3. Use the search bar or scroll to find the new user profile.\n4. If found, toggle their status to \"Active\".\n5. Optionally, set up additional fields by clicking on their name and inputting relevant information.\n6. Trigger a welcome message by going to the Invite page (People > Invite) and selecting the employee.\n\nIf you still can't find the user, please contact support at support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com or open a support ticket by chatting \"dialm\" to AttendanceBot.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115576", "reference_answer": "If a new user is not showing in AttendanceBot, check the settings under People --> Personnel, ensure the 'Show active personnel only' toggle is off, and search for the user. If found, activate their status and send a welcome message. For further issues, contact support.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how do i remove attendancebot from slack", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to uninstall AttendanceBot from Slack", "How do I install AttendanceBot in Slack?", "How do I uninstall AttendanceBot from Google Chat ?"], "generated_answer": "To uninstall AttendanceBot from Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Select the AttendanceBot app on Slack and click on the \u201cAbout\" tab.\n2. Select the \"Configuration\" tab to be redirected to the Slack app directory page.\n3. Scroll down to the Remove Application section and click on the Remove App button to remove it from your workspace.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000121227", "reference_answer": "To remove AttendanceBot from Slack, follow these steps: 1. Select the AttendanceBot app on Slack and click on the 'About' tab. 2. Select the 'Configuration' tab, which will redirect you to the Slack app directory page. 3. Scroll down to the Remove Application section and click on the Remove App button.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
