{"query": "Where to I see everyone's status?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to view employee status on a dashboard or in Slack", "How to automatically sync AttendanceBot punch and leave data with Slack status", "How do I find my missing employee profile on the dashboard? (Slack)"], "generated_answer": "You can view everyone's status using the live punch board or in Slack:\n\n1. **Live Punch Board:**\n   - Go to the \"Menu\" and select \"Timesheet actions.\"\n   - In the sub-menu, choose \u201cPunchboard\u201d to access the live updating punch board view.\n   - Alternatively, navigate from the dashboard > time tracking > punch board.\n   - The punch board is filterable by office, department, or direct reports and shows the time of the last punch, project details, and current status (leave, office, home, appointment).\n\n2. **Slack:**\n   - If auto-syncing is enabled, Slack status will show if employees are in, out, on break/lunch, on leave, or working from home.\n   - To get a text summary, DM AttendanceBot with \u201cpunch card\u201d for a snapshot of the punch board information.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000052710", "reference_answer": "You can view everyone's status using the live punch board or in Slack. For the punch board, go to 'Timesheet actions' > 'Punchboard' or navigate from the dashboard. In Slack, if auto-syncing is enabled, statuses will reflect in real-time. DM AttendanceBot with 'punch card' for a summary.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "remove admin from list of employees to monitor", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to deactivate a user in AttendanceBot", "How to inactivate users?", "How to delete approved leave for a reportee or employee"], "generated_answer": "To remove an admin or any user from the list of employees to monitor in AttendanceBot, you can deactivate their profile. Follow these steps:\n\n1. Open the settings panel by typing \"Settings\" as a direct message to AttendanceBot and click on the link prompted.\n2. Navigate to the People --> Personnel tab.\n3. Find the admin using the search or scroll through the list.\n4. Click the \"Inactive\" toggle present on the right of the profile tile.\n\nThis will prevent the admin from interacting with AttendanceBot.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131681", "reference_answer": "To remove an admin from the list of employees to monitor in AttendanceBot, deactivate their profile by going to Settings > People > Personnel, finding the admin, and toggling their profile to 'Inactive'.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "setting so admins don't show up on shift management", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to view my shifts and the shifts of my employees", "How to use shift management and create shifts for your team", "How to use shift attributes"], "generated_answer": "To ensure that admins do not show up in shift management, you can configure shift attributes and assign them accordingly. Here's how:\n\n1. Go to your Settings Panel by typing \"settings\" as a direct message to AttendanceBot.\n2. Navigate to People --> Personnel --> Custom field.\n3. Create a new Shift Attribute by clicking \"Add\". Define the attribute, such as \"Role\", and set it to \"Multi Dropdown\".\n4. Enter the dropdown options, such as \"Admin\", \"Employee\", etc., and save.\n5. Head to Shift Management --> Shift Attributes to view and manage these attributes.\n6. Assign the appropriate attribute instances to each employee's profile under People --> Personnel.\n\nBy categorizing users with attributes, you can filter out admins in shift management views.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000094159", "reference_answer": "To ensure that admins do not show up in shift management, you can configure shift attributes and assign them accordingly. Go to your Settings Panel, navigate to People --> Personnel --> Custom field, create a new Shift Attribute, and assign it to each employee's profile. This will allow you to filter out admins in shift management views.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how do i open a ticket", "retrieved_contexts": ["Ticket Response Time", "How can I get help from AttendanceBot support?", "Billing - how do I download past invoices or receipts?"], "generated_answer": "To open a ticket with AttendanceBot support, follow these steps:\n\n1. In Slack, send a direct message to AttendanceBot with the command 'dialm'.\n2. Click on \"Open a ticket\" when prompted.\n3. Your ticket will be visible to the entire support team, and they will respond as soon as possible.\n\nAlternatively, you can email support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com or use the chat bubble on the AttendanceBot dashboard.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118263", "reference_answer": "To open a ticket with AttendanceBot support, send 'dialm' as a direct message to AttendanceBot and click on 'Open a ticket' when prompted. You can also email support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com or use the chat bubble on the AttendanceBot dashboard for assistance.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how to make it where the employee can see the site they are working", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to view my shifts and the shifts of my employees", "How to track time spent on a project, task, or client", "How do I find my missing employee profile on the dashboard? (Slack)"], "generated_answer": "I don't have enough information to answer your question. Please open a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.", "reference_answer": "To allow employees to see the site they are working at, you may need to adjust their profile settings or permissions. Please refer to the AttendanceBot documentation or open a support ticket for detailed assistance.", "quality_score": 2.6, "bucket": "partial"}
{"query": "how do i mark a leave on attendance bot", "retrieved_contexts": ["How can I apply for leave in Slack with AttendanceBot", "How do I delete a leave applied by a member of my team?", "What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?"], "generated_answer": "To mark a leave on AttendanceBot in Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Message \"menu\" to AttendanceBot to open the options menu navigator.\n2. Click the \u2018Apply\u2019 button to open a request form popup.\n3. Complete your request by choosing the leave type, duration, and date, and hit \u201cSubmit\u201d.\n\nEach leave type will display your current balance for reference. You can also shortcut the process by messaging AttendanceBot directly with the leave type and timing, like \u201csick today\u201d or \u201cpto next Thursday\u201d.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131679", "reference_answer": "To mark a leave on AttendanceBot in Slack, message 'menu' to open the options menu. Click 'Apply' to access the request form, select the leave type, duration, and date, then hit 'Submit'. You can also use shortcuts like 'sick today' or 'pto next Thursday'.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "raise ticket", "retrieved_contexts": ["Ticket Response Time", "Billing - can I get a discount as a non-profit organization using AttendanceBot?", "Billing - how do I download past invoices or receipts?"], "generated_answer": "To raise a ticket with AttendanceBot, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. Send a direct message to AttendanceBot with the command \"dialm\".\n2. Alternatively, you can chat live with support using the chat bubble located on the AttendanceBot dashboard or website.\n\nIf you need further assistance, please let me know!\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000138776", "reference_answer": "To raise a ticket with AttendanceBot support, send 'dialm' as a direct message to AttendanceBot or click on 'Open a ticket' on the dashboard. This will notify the support team, and they will respond as soon as possible.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "wie kann ich bei den usern in slack sehen wer eingecheckt ist", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to view employee status on a dashboard or in Slack", "How to track time in Slack using AttendanceBot", "How to check leave balance in Slack with AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "Please chat in English only.", "reference_answer": "You can view who is checked in by using the AttendanceBot dashboard in Slack. Please refer to the article on how to view employee status for detailed steps: https://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000052710.", "quality_score": 2.4, "bucket": "content_gap"}
{"query": "how i can see if a user is checked in in slack", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to view employee status on a dashboard or in Slack", "How do I find my missing employee profile on the dashboard? (Slack)", "How to check leave balance in Slack with AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "To see if a user is checked in using Slack with AttendanceBot, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. If your team is auto-syncing their punch status with AttendanceBot, check the user's Slack status to see if they\u2019re in, out, on break/lunch, on leave, or working from home.\n2. To get a text summary of everyone's status, send a direct message to AttendanceBot with the command \u201cpunch card.\u201d This will provide a snapshot of the punch board information in text format.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000052710", "reference_answer": "To see if a user is checked in using Slack with AttendanceBot, check their Slack status for in/out status or send a direct message to AttendanceBot with 'punch card' for a summary of everyone's status.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how to plot a vacation leave", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to download team vacation data and reporting", "How to apply for recurring leave or hybrid status", "What are the different kinds of leaves?"], "generated_answer": "To apply for a recurring vacation leave in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Type a command in Slack such as \"Vacation every Thursday\" or \"Vacation on every 25th of the month\".\n2. The recurring vacations will appear in the summary and reports like other leaves.\n3. These leaves will be set for 8 weeks. After this period, you'll receive a notification to extend or discontinue the leave.\n\nFor more details on deleting these recurring leaves, refer to the documentation.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000049831", "reference_answer": "To plot a vacation leave in AttendanceBot, type a command in Slack such as 'Vacation every Thursday' or 'Vacation on every 25th of the month'. The recurring vacations will be set for 8 weeks, and you'll receive a notification to extend or discontinue them. For more details, refer to the documentation.", "quality_score": 4.4, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "Taking the day off", "retrieved_contexts": ["Taking time off", "How to apply for time off for half a day or few hours?", "How to request hourly or half day leave"], "generated_answer": "To take a day off using AttendanceBot in Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Type a command with the leave type name, followed by the date. For example, \"Vacation tomorrow\" or \"Sick today\".\n2. Alternatively, use a conversational approach like \"WFH tomorrow\" or \"Vacation 05/04 to 05/07\".\n3. Specify the start and end dates in formats like MM-DD, MM/DD, or phrases like \"today\", \"tomorrow\", \"next week\".\n4. AttendanceBot will verify the date with you before recording your leave request.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000116053", "reference_answer": "To take a day off using AttendanceBot in Slack, type a command with the leave type and date, like 'Vacation tomorrow' or 'Sick today'. You can also use phrases like 'WFH tomorrow' or specify dates in formats like MM-DD. AttendanceBot will confirm the date before recording your request.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how do i lock in", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How do I unlock the timesheet that's approved?", "How to track time in Slack using AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "To lock in or punch in using AttendanceBot in Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Send \"Menu\" as a direct message to AttendanceBot.\n2. In the menu that appears, select the \"In \u2705\" button to start recording your hours.\n3. If you are tracking projects, choose a project from the menu and confirm your selection to complete the punch in.\n\nAlternatively, you can simply type \"in\" as a direct message to AttendanceBot to punch in.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118256", "reference_answer": "To lock in or punch in using AttendanceBot in Slack, send 'Menu' to AttendanceBot and select 'In \u2705' to start recording your hours. You can also type 'in' directly to punch in.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
