{"query": "On our end, we approve leaves by department, which was set up by the Attendancebot team.\n\nI need assistance changing the approval of one team. Can you help?", "retrieved_contexts": ["Approval routing and multi-level approvals for leaves", "How do I delete a leave applied by a member of my team?", "Approval routing and multi-level approvals for leaves"], "generated_answer": "To change the approval settings for a specific team in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Navigate to the approval settings on the AttendanceBot dashboard.\n2. Specify where approvals are routed and how many levels of approval you'd like.\n3. Adjust the settings to change the recipient of the approval for the specific team. You can choose between the default manager or a custom user.\n4. Ensure that each level is activated by toggling it \"on\" if you require multi-level approvals.\n\nIf you encounter any issues or need further assistance, consider reaching out to the support team.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000121266", "reference_answer": "To change the approval settings for a specific team in AttendanceBot, navigate to the approval settings on the AttendanceBot dashboard. Specify where approvals are routed and how many levels of approval you'd like. Adjust the settings to change the recipient of the approval for the specific team, choosing between the default manager or a custom user. Ensure that each level is activated by toggling it 'on' if you require multi-level approvals. If you encounter any issues, reach out to the support team.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
