{"query": "i really want to understand how the attendance channels works.", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to setup Slack channel notifications with AttendanceBot", "How do I learn more about the product?", "How to announce in/out and breaks/lunch on a Slack channel"], "generated_answer": "To set up Slack channel notifications with AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Add AttendanceBot to the desired Slack channel by typing \"/invite @attendancebot\" in the channel.\n2. Navigate to the configuration by pulling up the \"menu\" and selecting \"Settings, people, policy\" > \"Notifications.\"\n3. Click on \"Create new\" to start configuring a new notification rule.\n4. Select the type of notification you want (e.g., \"In/Out Notifications\" or \"Break/Lunch notifications\").\n5. Configure the channel, people, and timing for the notification, then hit \"save changes.\"\n\nYou can create multiple notifications for different channels, personnel, and times of day.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118249", "reference_answer": "To set up Slack channel notifications with AttendanceBot, invite the bot to your channel, navigate to settings, create a notification rule, select the type of notification, configure it, and save changes. You can create multiple notifications for different channels and times.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
