{"query": "I am not able to enable TOIL for my employees", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to configure and use time-off-in-lieu (TOIL) (Slack)", "How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?", "How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?"], "generated_answer": "To enable Time Off in Lieu (TOIL) for your employees, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to Settings -> Time Tracking -> Overtime in AttendanceBot.\n2. Toggle ON the \u201cTime off in lieu (TOIL)\u201d option.\n3. Define the number of hours beyond which overtime starts by creating daily or weekly hours. These extra hours will be banked in \"TOIL\" leave.\n4. A new leave type \u201ctoil\u201d will be created under the vacation management tab.\n\nEnsure that TOIL is activated from the main overtime dashboard to generate TOIL instead of regular overtime.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000112422", "reference_answer": "To enable Time Off in Lieu (TOIL) for your employees, go to Settings -> Time Tracking -> Overtime in AttendanceBot, toggle ON the TOIL option, define the overtime hours, and a new leave type will be created under vacation management.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
