{"query": "not showing Simon Moscovici or Geri Craig when I try to send over the payroll report to Gusto", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do you pass hours for contractors from AttendanceBot to Gusto?", "How to send hours to Gusto for payroll", "How to send hours to Gusto for payroll"], "generated_answer": "To resolve the issue of Simon Moscovici or Geri Craig not appearing when sending the payroll report to Gusto, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure that both Simon Moscovici and Geri Craig are correctly mapped between AttendanceBot and Gusto. Go to the AttendanceBot dashboard, navigate to Settings -> Gusto -> Sync 1099 Employees, and check if they are listed under \"Unmatched Contractors.\" If they are, match them accordingly.\n\n2. Verify that their email addresses in AttendanceBot match those in Gusto, as this is the basis for matching contractors.\n\n3. Ensure that the pay period you are selecting includes the hours worked by Simon Moscovici and Geri Craig.\n\nIf the issue persists, consider opening a support ticket by typing 'ticket' for further assistance.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000119375", "reference_answer": "To resolve the issue of Simon Moscovici or Geri Craig not appearing when sending the payroll report to Gusto, ensure they are correctly mapped in AttendanceBot. Check their mapping under Settings -> Gusto -> Sync 1099 Employees. Verify their email addresses match in both systems and ensure the selected pay period includes their hours. If the issue persists, open a support ticket for further assistance.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
