{"query": "Hi,  our employees submitted their attendance on the attendancebot, but I could only see a few of them on the attendancebot calendar. Only when I did the integration again on my google calander I see all of the submitted days off of our employees. ", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to use and configure the AttendanceBot vacation calendar", "How to integrate your calendar with AttendanceBot for Slack", "How to use and configure the AttendanceBot vacation calendar"], "generated_answer": "It seems like there might be an issue with how the AttendanceBot calendar is displaying the data. Here are a few steps you can take to troubleshoot and ensure all submitted days off are visible:\n\n1. **Check Filters**: Make sure you are not filtering out any employees or leave types on the AttendanceBot calendar. Use the multi-select dropdowns at the top to filter by office or department and ensure \"Show only my team\" is not inadvertently hiding entries.\n\n2. **Calendar Permissions**: Verify that you have the correct viewing permissions set up. Admins can adjust these by clicking the \u201cConfigure\u201d button at the top right of the team calendar.\n\n3. **Re-Integration**: Since re-integrating with Google Calendar helped, ensure that the integration settings are correct and up-to-date. Follow the integration steps for Google Calendar to ensure everything is synced properly.\n\nIf the issue persists, consider opening a support ticket for further assistance.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000138905", "reference_answer": "It seems like there might be an issue with how the AttendanceBot calendar is displaying the data. Here are a few steps you can take to troubleshoot and ensure all submitted days off are visible: 1. Check Filters: Make sure you are not filtering out any employees or leave types on the AttendanceBot calendar. 2. Calendar Permissions: Verify that you have the correct viewing permissions set up. 3. Re-Integration: Since re-integrating with Google Calendar helped, ensure that the integration settings are correct. If the issue persists, consider opening a support ticket for further assistance.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
