{"query": "Hi,  our employees submitted their attendance on the attendancebot, but I could only see a few of them on the attendancebot calendar. Only when I did the integration again on my google calander I see all of the submitted days off of our employees. ", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to use and configure the AttendanceBot vacation calendar", "How to use and configure the AttendanceBot vacation calendar", "How to integrate your calendar with AttendanceBot for Slack"], "generated_answer": "It seems like there might be an issue with the visibility settings or the integration between AttendanceBot and your Google Calendar. Here are some steps you can take to troubleshoot and ensure everything is set up correctly:\n\n1. **Check Calendar Permissions**: Ensure that the viewing permissions on the AttendanceBot calendar are set correctly. Admins can configure these by clicking the \u201cConfigure\u201d button at the top right of the team calendar.\n\n2. **Filter Settings**: Make sure that the filters on the AttendanceBot calendar are not limiting the view to specific offices or departments. Use the multi-select dropdowns at the top to adjust these settings.\n\n3. **Re-integrate Calendar**: If issues persist, try re-integrating your calendar. Go to the \"Menu\" > \"Data & integrations\" > \"Calendar\" and use the \"Get link\" button to copy the ics calendar link. Then, follow the steps to add it to your Google Calendar.\n\nIf these steps do not resolve the issue, you may want to open a support ticket for further assistance.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000138905", "reference_answer": "It seems like there might be an issue with the visibility settings or the integration between AttendanceBot and your Google Calendar. Here are some steps you can take to troubleshoot: 1. Check Calendar Permissions. 2. Filter Settings. 3. Re-integrate Calendar. If issues persist, consider opening a support ticket for further assistance.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "if possible, we don't want people to punch out and in for a lunch break, can a half hour lunch break be included in total hours worked every day (which means at the end of day deduct half hour from total hours worked)", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to request hourly or half day leave", "How to setup lunch hours for your team", "How to round Slack punch timings to the nearest minute, 6 minutes, 7 minutes, 15 minutes, or more"], "generated_answer": "Yes, you can configure AttendanceBot to include a lunch break in the total hours worked. Here\u2019s how to set it up:\n\n1. Type \"settings\" in the AttendanceBot app to access the settings panel.\n2. Navigate to Time Tracking --> General Time Settings.\n3. Scroll down to configure the \"Lunch Duration in Minute.\"\n4. Ensure that \"Include lunch in work hours\" is set according to your preference.\n\nThis setup will automatically account for the lunch break in the total hours worked.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000093813", "reference_answer": "Yes, you can configure AttendanceBot to include a lunch break in the total hours worked. To set it up, go to 'settings' in the AttendanceBot app, navigate to Time Tracking --> General Time Settings, and configure the 'Lunch Duration in Minute.' Ensure 'Include lunch in work hours' is set as needed.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
