{"query": "reports are not working - error messages and I need to pay my contractors", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do you pass hours for contractors from AttendanceBot to Gusto?", "What are my reporting options and what do the different reports do?", "How to schedule reports"], "generated_answer": "I'm sorry to hear you're experiencing issues with reports. To address the problem with paying your contractors, you can manually pass hours from AttendanceBot to Gusto by following these steps:\n\n1. Go to the AttendanceBot dashboard and navigate to Settings -> Gusto -> Sync 1099 Employees tab.\n2. Ensure contractors are matched between AttendanceBot and Gusto. If not, match them under \"Unmatched Contractors.\"\n3. Select the pay period and click \u201cGenerate report\u201d to create a CSV file.\n4. Upload the CSV to contractor payroll on Gusto to process their payroll.\n\nIf the error persists, consider opening a support ticket by typing 'ticket' for further assistance.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000119375", "reference_answer": "I'm sorry to hear you're experiencing issues with reports. To address the problem with paying your contractors, you can manually pass hours from AttendanceBot to Gusto by following these steps: 1. Go to the AttendanceBot dashboard and navigate to Settings -> Gusto -> Sync 1099 Employees tab. 2. Ensure contractors are matched between AttendanceBot and Gusto. If not, match them under 'Unmatched Contractors.' 3. Select the pay period and click 'Generate report' to create a CSV file. 4. Upload the CSV to contractor payroll on Gusto to process their payroll. If the error persists, consider opening a support ticket for further assistance.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
