{"query": "how can i see a summary of where my hours have been used", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I get the summary or report of my time in office?", "How to track time spent on a project, task, or client", "What are my reporting options and what do the different reports do?"], "generated_answer": "To see a summary of where your hours have been used:\n\n1. Type \"timesheet\" in Slack to get a summary of your punch logs for the current day.\n2. For a report of your time in office for the current and previous month, type \"timesheet report\" to receive a downloadable CSV report.\n3. To generate a report for a specific time period, append the date range to the report command, e.g., \"Timesheet Report jan 3 to feb 10\".\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118258", "reference_answer": "To see a summary of where your hours have been used, type 'timesheet' for today's punch logs, 'timesheet report' for a monthly summary, or specify a date range with 'Timesheet Report [start date] to [end date]'.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "Timesheet report feb 2 - feb 14", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I get the summary or report of my time in office?", "How to schedule reports", "Time/Task tracking"], "generated_answer": "To generate a timesheet report for the period from February 2 to February 14, you can use the command \"timesheet report from 02-02 to 02-14\". This will create a report for that specific date range.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115834", "reference_answer": "To generate a Timesheet report for February 2 to February 14 in AttendanceBot, follow these steps: 1. For Slack: Type the command 'report' to the AttendanceBot. 2. Select 'Timesheet Report' as the report type. 3. Set the duration to 'Custom' and enter the date range from February 2 to February 14.", "quality_score": 4.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "i want to see summaries for projects with their hours, not daily breakdown", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to track time spent on a project, task, or client", "How do I get the summary or report of my time in office?", "How to track time spent on a project, task, or client"], "generated_answer": "To view summaries for projects with their hours without a daily breakdown, you can use the Project Report feature. Here's how:\n\n1. Ensure your admin has configured projects or clients in AttendanceBot.\n2. Use the Project Report, which aggregates time by day, employee, and project/task/client.\n3. This report simplifies analysis and can be used for client billables or employee wage calculations if configured.\n\nFor more detailed instructions, you can refer to the documentation.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000051253", "reference_answer": "To view summaries for projects with their hours, use the Project Report feature in AttendanceBot. Ensure your admin has set up projects or clients, then access the Project Report to see aggregated time by project without daily breakdowns. For detailed steps, refer to the documentation.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "HOw do I request sick pay", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to upload medical certificates for sick time", "How to request hourly or half day leave", "How can I apply for leave in Slack with AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "To request sick pay using AttendanceBot in Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Message \"menu\" to AttendanceBot to open the options menu navigator.\n2. Click the \u2018Apply\u2019 button to open a request form popup.\n3. Complete your request by choosing the leave type as \"sick,\" specify the duration and date, and hit \u201cSubmit.\u201d\n\nIf the request requires approval, it will be routed to your manager, and you'll be notified once it's approved or rejected.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131679", "reference_answer": "To request sick pay using AttendanceBot in Slack, message 'menu' to open the options menu, click 'Apply' to access the request form, select 'sick' as the leave type, specify the duration and date, and hit 'Submit.' Your request will be sent to your manager for approval.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
