{"query": "I've noticed two events that haven't synced to the outlook calendar. \n\nApril 6th and April 16 - 19 events aren't showing in my calendar.\n\nI haven't looked through exhaustively, but this does make me lose trust a bit, haha.", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to integrate calendars", "How to integrate your calendar with AttendanceBot for Slack", "How do I find my missing employee profile on the dashboard? (Slack)"], "generated_answer": "To troubleshoot the issue with events not syncing to your Outlook calendar, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure that your calendar integration is correctly set up. Go to the options \"menu\" in AttendanceBot and select \"data & integrations.\"\n2. Select \"Calendar\" on the sub-menu and check if your Outlook calendar is enabled. If not, click \"Enable\" to initiate the sync.\n3. If it's already enabled, try disabling and re-enabling the integration to refresh the connection.\n4. Check if the events are correctly entered in AttendanceBot and ensure there are no errors in the event details.\n5. If the issue persists, consider re-subscribing to the calendar using the \"Get link\" option and follow the steps for Outlook calendar subscription.\n\nIf none of these steps resolve the issue, please open a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000017361", "reference_answer": "To troubleshoot the issue with events not syncing to your Outlook calendar, ensure your calendar integration is set up correctly, check if your Outlook calendar is enabled in AttendanceBot, and verify the event details. If the issue persists, consider re-subscribing to the calendar. If none of these steps resolve the issue, please open a support ticket.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
