{"query": "I am looking for instructions on how to download a report of someone' time for a full year", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I get the summary or report of my time in office?", "How to download team vacation data and reporting", "How to generate a payroll report in Slack with AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "To download a report of someone's time for a full year, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open the \"Menu\" in AttendanceBot and select \"Data & Integrations.\"\n2. Click on \"Reports.\"\n3. In the report menu, select the type of report you need, such as the Timesheet Report.\n4. Choose the date range for the full year you are interested in.\n5. Decide if you'd like to download data for all employees or just one specific employee.\n6. Hit \"Confirm\" to download the report.\n\nAlternatively, you can message \"timesheet report <start_date> to <end_date>\" directly to AttendanceBot, replacing <start_date> and <end_date> with the desired dates for the full year.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118258", "reference_answer": "To download a report of someone's time for a full year, open the 'Menu' in AttendanceBot, select 'Data & Integrations,' then 'Reports.' Choose the Timesheet Report, set the date range for the full year, and confirm to download. Alternatively, message 'timesheet report <start_date> to <end_date>' to AttendanceBot.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
