{"query": "how do i set reminder for punching in?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to set up punch in/out reminders", "How to set up auto-punch out for my employees", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times "], "generated_answer": "To set up a punch-in reminder for your team, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the AttendanceBot dashboard and navigate to Settings -> Basic Settings.\n2. Scroll down to the Time Settings section.\n3. Switch the toggle from \"Inactive\" to \"Active\" for punch reminders.\n4. Click on the edit icon and add the punch-in time.\n\nThis reminder will be sent to all members of the Slack team at their respective local time.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000049838", "reference_answer": "To set a reminder for punching in using AttendanceBot, follow these steps: 1. Go to the AttendanceBot dashboard for your team. 2. Navigate to Settings -> Basic Settings and scroll down to the Time Settings. 3. Switch the toggle from 'Inactive' to 'Active.' 4. Click on the edit icon and add the punch-in time. This reminder will be sent to all members of the Slack team at their respective local time.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
