{"query": "How do I add PTO for the future? ", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to configure and use time-off-in-lieu (TOIL) (Slack)", "How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?", "Understanding future balance deduction against payroll versus instant deduction"], "generated_answer": "To add PTO for a future date, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open AttendanceBot in Slack.\n2. Type \"apply\" and select the leave type (e.g., PTO).\n3. Enter the future date for which you want to apply the leave.\n4. Submit the request.\n\nAttendanceBot will deduct the leave balance at the time of the relevant accrual period rather than instantly. For example, if you apply for leave next year, the balance will be deducted from next year's leave balance once it is accrued.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131738", "reference_answer": "To add PTO for a future date in AttendanceBot, open Slack, type 'apply', select the leave type (e.g., PTO), enter the future date, and submit the request. The leave balance will be deducted at the relevant accrual period.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
