{"query": "how does gusto integration work", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to send hours to Gusto for payroll", "How to send hours to Gusto for payroll", "How do you pass hours for contractors from AttendanceBot to Gusto?"], "generated_answer": "To integrate Gusto with AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the settings page in AttendanceBot by typing \"settings\" in your chat app (Slack, MS Teams, or Google Chat).\n2. Click on Integrations and select \"Integrate with Gusto.\"\n3. Enter your Gusto credentials and authorize the connection.\n4. Map your employees from Gusto to AttendanceBot by reviewing and syncing them.\n5. To send timesheet data to Gusto, go to the Payroll tab, select the pay period, and click \"Sync.\"\n\nNote: Gusto integration is available on the pro plan.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000112898", "reference_answer": "To integrate Gusto with AttendanceBot, follow these steps: 1. Go to the settings page in AttendanceBot by typing 'settings' in your chat app (Slack, MS Teams, or Google Chat). 2. Click on Integrations and select 'Integrate with Gusto.' 3. Enter your Gusto credentials and authorize the connection. 4. Map your employees from Gusto to AttendanceBot by reviewing and syncing them. 5. To send timesheet data to Gusto, go to the Payroll tab, select the pay period, and click 'Sync.' Note: Gusto integration is available on the pro plan.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
