{"query": "how to manage attendance and leaves in it", "retrieved_contexts": ["What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?", "How can I apply for leave in Slack with AttendanceBot", "How to apply for leave next year or any future year"], "generated_answer": "To manage attendance and leaves in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Approve Leave**: Managers can approve leave requests by typing \"pending leaves\" to see requests awaiting approval.\n2. **Check Reportees**: Type \"my reportees\" to view your team members.\n3. **Team Reports**: For absence reports, type \"team report\" and specify the department. For timesheet reports, type \"timesheet team report\" and specify details like office or project.\n4. **Individual Reports**: Get a summary by typing \"summary @reportee\" or a timesheet report with \"timesheet @reportee\".\n5. **Apply Leave for Others**: Use \"@reportee vacation tomorrow\" or the \"apply\" command to apply leave on behalf of an employee.\n6. **Edit Punches**: Go to the settings dashboard, navigate to Time Tracking, and select Edit Timesheet to add or edit punches.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118266", "reference_answer": "To manage attendance and leaves in AttendanceBot, you can approve leave requests, check reportees, generate team and individual reports, apply leave for others, and edit punches through the settings dashboard.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
