{"query": "Can we have separate OT presets for seperate employees? ", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?", "How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?", "How to create employee specific work schedules?"], "generated_answer": "Yes, you can set separate overtime (OT) presets for individual employees using employee profiles. Here's how:\n\n1. Go to the custom field section of your personnel dashboard.\n2. Activate the work hour periods you need (Daily, Weekly, Biweekly, or Monthly Work Hours).\n3. For each employee, set threshold hours by inputting a numerical value into the appropriate work hour field in their profile.\n4. Alternatively, use the import/export page to set thresholds in bulk.\n\nNote: This method overrides any office-level settings. TOIL must be activated from the main overtime dashboard to generate TOIL instead of overtime.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000106516", "reference_answer": "Yes, you can set separate overtime (OT) presets for individual employees using employee profiles. Go to the custom field section of your personnel dashboard, activate the necessary work hour periods, and set threshold hours for each employee. You can also use the import/export page for bulk settings. Note that this overrides office-level settings, and TOIL must be activated to generate TOIL instead of overtime.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
