{"query": "How can I edit a vacation date for an employee", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to use and configure the AttendanceBot vacation calendar", "How to create employee specific work schedules?", "How to change or edit an existing approved leave"], "generated_answer": "To edit a vacation date for an employee, you generally need to delete the existing leave and submit a new request. However, if the leave type is \"available\" such as work from home (wfh), work from office (wfo), or remote work, you can override the existing request with the new one without needing to cancel first. If you need to delete a past leave, you must be a manager or admin.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131566", "reference_answer": "To edit a vacation date for an employee, you can delete the existing leave and submit a new request. If the leave type is 'available' (like work from home or remote work), you can override the existing request without canceling it. Only managers or admins can delete past leaves.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "Hello, could you please check the timezone again, it is messing me up", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to manage AttendanceBot timezone for Slack employees", "Time/Task tracking", "Time/Task tracking"], "generated_answer": "To update your timezone in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Click on your profile image in Slack.\n2. Select the \"Preferences\" tab from the dropdown list.\n3. Click on the \"Language & Region\" tab.\n4. Select the timezone of your choice.\n\nAttendanceBot will automatically pick up the timezone from your Slack account.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000093806", "reference_answer": "To update your timezone in AttendanceBot, follow these steps: 1. Click on your profile image in Slack. 2. Select the 'Preferences' tab from the dropdown list. 3. Click on the 'Language & Region' tab. 4. Select the timezone of your choice. AttendanceBot will automatically pick up the timezone from your Slack account.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "my work is supposed to be and i always set the 8am - 4pm EST, but now it changes again", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to define your team work week", "How to create employee specific work schedules?", "How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?"], "generated_answer": "To set your work schedule to 8 AM - 4 PM EST, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the work schedule section under the People tab on the settings dashboard.\n2. Select your profile and click on the edit button.\n3. Adjust the start time to 8 AM and the end time to 4 PM.\n4. Save the changes.\n\nIf the schedule keeps changing, ensure that no templates or bulk assignments are overriding your settings. You might also want to check if any admin settings are affecting your schedule.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000142683", "reference_answer": "To set your work schedule to 8 AM - 4 PM EST, go to the work schedule section under the People tab on the settings dashboard, select your profile, click edit, adjust the times, and save. If it keeps changing, check for templates or admin settings that might be overriding your schedule.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
