{"query": "issues with timesheet approvals not matching timesheets with total hours worked. ", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to approve the timesheets of my reportees", "How to approve the timesheets of my reportees", "How to approve the timesheets of my reportees"], "generated_answer": "To address issues with timesheet approvals not matching the total hours worked, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Access Timesheet Approvals**: Open the dashboard by typing \"settings\" as a DM to the app. Navigate to Time tracking -> Timesheet Approvals.\n2. **Review Timesheets**: In the \"Approvals\" tab, select the employee tile to review individual timesheets.\n3. **Check Details**: Expand the timesheet period to view a summary of hours and overtime. Further expand to see day-by-day summaries and punch history.\n4. **Edit Punches**: If discrepancies are found, visit the timesheet editor to make necessary changes before approving the full timesheet.\n\nEnsure that the timesheet editor is used to correct any punch errors before final approval.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000134394", "reference_answer": "To resolve timesheet approval discrepancies, access the Timesheet Approvals section, review individual timesheets for errors, and edit any incorrect punches before final approval.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
