{"query": "new project", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to Configure Project, Client, and Task / Subproject Tracking in AttendanceBot", "How to Configure Project, Client, and Task / Subproject Tracking in AttendanceBot", "How to track time spent on a project, task, or client"], "generated_answer": "To create a new project in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to your dashboard and find the \"Time Tracking\" section.\n2. Click on \"Projects and Clients.\"\n3. If you don't see \"Time Tracking,\" enable it in the general settings.\n4. Click the blue \"Create New\" button at the top right.\n5. Assign a name to your project and optionally describe it.\n6. (Optional) Select a client or create a new one if the project is client-specific.\n7. Choose between self-assign or managed assign for project assignment.\n8. Select the employees to assign to the project.\n9. Click \"Create Project\" to finalize.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000138976", "reference_answer": "To create a new project in AttendanceBot, follow these steps: 1. Go to your dashboard and find the 'Time Tracking' section. 2. Click on 'Projects and Clients.' 3. If 'Time Tracking' isn't visible, enable it in general settings. 4. Click the blue 'Create New' button at the top right. 5. Assign a name to your project and optionally describe it. 6. (Optional) Select a client or create a new one if the project is client-specific. 7. Choose between self-assign or managed assign for project assignment. 8. Select the employees to assign to the project. 9. Click 'Create Project' to finalize.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how to set up a schedule", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to schedule reports", "How to create employee specific work schedules?", "How to manage hybrid work schedules (WFO/WFH days) in Slack using AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "To set up a schedule in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open the \"menu\" and select \"Data and integrations\" > \"Schedule report emails\" to access the scheduled reporting section.\n2. Click on \"Schedule New Report.\"\n3. Choose the report type, frequency, time, and data.\n4. Hit \"Schedule Report\" to finalize.\n\nYou can schedule reports with four frequency options: First day of every month, Last day of every month, Fixed date of every month, or Day of the week. Note that only payroll, vacation (leave), and timesheet reports can be scheduled.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000116147", "reference_answer": "To set up a schedule in AttendanceBot, open the menu, select 'Data and integrations' > 'Schedule report emails', click 'Schedule New Report', choose the report type, frequency, time, and data, then hit 'Schedule Report'. You can choose from four frequency options: First day of every month, Last day of every month, Fixed date of every month, or Day of the week. Only payroll, vacation, and timesheet reports can be scheduled.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
