{"query": "for a particular employee i need to assign different timing and view it on dashboard", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to create employee specific work schedules?", "How to view my shifts and the shifts of my employees", "How to approve the timesheets of my reportees"], "generated_answer": "To assign different timings for a particular employee, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the work schedule section under the People tab on the settings dashboard.\n2. Select the employee and click on the edit button.\n3. Edit the working days and start time, or add different start times and work hours for different days.\n4. Click on save changes. A personal tag will be added to the employee profile.\n\nTo view this on the dashboard:\n\n1. From the \"Menu,\" select \"Timesheet actions.\"\n2. Click on \u201cShifts\u201d to view the shift calendar, which includes daily, weekly, and monthly views.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000142683", "reference_answer": "To assign different timings for a particular employee and view it on the dashboard, follow these steps: 1. Go to the work schedule section under the People tab on the settings dashboard. 2. Select the employee and click on the edit button. 3. Edit the working days and start time, or add different start times and work hours for different days. 4. Click on save changes. A personal tag will be added to the employee profile. To view this on the dashboard: 1. From the 'Menu,' select 'Timesheet actions.' 2. Click on 'Shifts' to view the shift calendar, which includes daily, weekly, and monthly views.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
