{"query": "how can I enter my hours from yesterday", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to send hours to Gusto for payroll", "How do I get the summary or report of my time in office?", "How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?"], "generated_answer": "To enter your hours from yesterday in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open your chat app (Slack, MS Teams, or Google Chat).\n2. Type \"in\" followed by the time you started working yesterday.\n3. Type \"out\" followed by the time you finished working yesterday.\n\nThis will log your hours for the previous day. If you need to make any corrections, you can reach out to your manager or admin for assistance.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118258", "reference_answer": "To enter your hours from yesterday in AttendanceBot, open your chat app and type 'in' followed by your start time and 'out' followed by your end time for yesterday. For more details, refer to the support article: https://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118258.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "I forgot to enter my hours yesterday", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to send hours to Gusto for payroll", "How to request hourly or half day leave", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times "], "generated_answer": "To add a missing punch entry for your hours, follow these steps:\n\n1. Click on the green \u201cadd punches\u201d button in AttendanceBot.\n2. Choose the type of entry you need (e.g., punch in/out pair, single punch in, etc.).\n3. Enter the dates, times, any project tags, and remarks.\n4. Hit \u201csave\u201d to create the punch entry.\n\nNote: Ensure your admin has enabled \"Allow self editing of punches\" in the timesheet settings for you to update your punches.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118260", "reference_answer": "To add a missing punch entry for your hours, follow these steps: 1. Click on the green 'add punches' button in AttendanceBot. 2. Choose the type of entry you need (e.g., punch in/out pair, single punch in, etc.). 3. Enter the dates, times, any project tags, and remarks. 4. Hit 'save' to create the punch entry. Note: Ensure your admin has enabled 'Allow self editing of punches' in the timesheet settings for you to update your punches.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "can I make adjustments to my timesheet", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to approve the timesheets of my reportees", "How to approve the timesheets of my reportees"], "generated_answer": "Yes, you can make adjustments to your timesheet in AttendanceBot. Follow these steps:\n\n1. From the \"Menu,\" select \"Timesheet actions\" and click on \u201cEdit\u201d to access your timesheet editor on the dashboard.\n2. Choose the date range you want to edit by clicking on the blue \u201cDate Range\u201d dropdown.\n3. Once your selection is submitted, expand any day to view or edit specific punches.\n4. To edit a punch, click the pencil icon, update the details, and hit \"save.\" To delete a punch, click the trashcan icon. To add a new entry, click the green \u201cadd punches\u201d button.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118260", "reference_answer": "Yes, you can make adjustments to your timesheet in AttendanceBot. To do this, go to 'Timesheet actions' in the menu, select 'Edit', choose your date range, and then you can edit, delete, or add punches as needed.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "I need to edit my timesheet in attendancebot", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?", "Time/Task tracking"], "generated_answer": "To edit your timesheet in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. From the \"Menu,\" select \"Timesheet actions.\"\n2. Click on \u201cEdit\u201d to open your timesheet editor on the dashboard.\n3. Choose the date range using the \u201cDate Range\u201d dropdown.\n4. If needed, select another employee if you have reportees.\n5. Click \"expand\" on any day to view or edit specific punches.\n6. To change a punch time, click the pencil icon, update the details, and hit \"save.\"\n7. To delete a punch, click the trashcan icon and confirm the deletion.\n8. To add a new entry, click the green \u201cadd punches\u201d button and fill out the details.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118260", "reference_answer": "To edit your timesheet in AttendanceBot, go to 'Timesheet actions' in the menu, click 'Edit', select the date range, and make your changes. You can edit, delete, or add punches as needed.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "edit timesheet", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to approve the timesheets of my reportees", "How to approve the timesheets of my reportees"], "generated_answer": "To edit your timesheet in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. From the \"Menu,\" select \"Timesheet actions\" and click on \u201cEdit\u201d to access your timesheet editor on the dashboard.\n2. Choose the date range using the blue \u201cDate Range\u201d dropdown if needed.\n3. View or edit specific punches by clicking \"expand\" on any day to open the punch history.\n4. To change a punch time, click the pencil icon, update the details, and hit \"save.\"\n5. To delete a punch, click the trashcan icon and confirm the deletion.\n6. To add a new entry, click the green \u201cadd punches\u201d button and fill in the details.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118260", "reference_answer": "To edit your timesheet in AttendanceBot, go to 'Timesheet actions' in the Menu, select 'Edit', choose the date range, expand the day to edit punches, and use the pencil icon to update or the trashcan icon to delete. You can also add new entries with the 'add punches' button.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
