{"query": "I'd like to set \"Leave Types\" in detail.\nFor example, Staff A can take vacation 20 days but Staff B can take it 15 days.\n\nDo I need to select PRO Plan?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to setup accrual rules and leave quotas based on company policy", "How to setup accrual rules and leave quotas based on company policy", "What are the different kinds of leaves?"], "generated_answer": "To set up different leave quotas for different employees, you need to configure leave policies for specific employee sets. Here's how you can do it:\n\n1. Navigate to the \"accrual settings\" tab in the edit screen.\n2. Decide if you want to configure a universal leave policy or a policy for a specific employee set.\n3. Click \"Create New Set\" to create a policy for a specific group, such as Staff A and Staff B.\n4. Set the leave quotas for each set, e.g., 20 days for Staff A and 15 days for Staff B.\n\nThe documentation does not specify if a PRO Plan is required for this feature. If you need more information, consider opening a support ticket.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000051255", "reference_answer": "To set different leave quotas for Staff A and Staff B, navigate to the 'accrual settings' tab, create a new set for each employee group, and specify their leave days. The documentation does not clarify if a PRO Plan is necessary for this feature. For further assistance, consider opening a support ticket.", "quality_score": 4.6, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "what is free trial? i believed there's free plan right?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How long is my AttendanceBot trial?", "AttendanceBot Plans and Features", "Billing - how does adding or removing users affect my billing?"], "generated_answer": "AttendanceBot offers a 14-day free trial on Slack and Microsoft Teams. During this period, you can explore all features without any charges. The app is free for teams with 5 users or less. If your team has more than 5 members, you will need to subscribe after the trial ends. Note that AttendanceBot will not auto-charge your credit card after the trial; you will be explicitly asked to subscribe.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115577", "reference_answer": "AttendanceBot offers a 14-day free trial on Slack and Microsoft Teams, allowing you to explore all features. The app is free for teams with 5 users or less. For teams with more than 5 members, a subscription is required after the trial. No auto-charge occurs after the trial; you will be prompted to subscribe.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "Attendancebot is being weird again. Plz fix", "retrieved_contexts": ["I'm getting an error message \"You are viewing the archives of a deactivated account\" while accessing AttendanceBot in Slack. What should I do?", "AttendanceBot Plans and Features", "How do I add admin users?"], "generated_answer": "I need more information to assist you effectively. Could you please describe the specific issue you're experiencing with AttendanceBot?", "reference_answer": "I'm sorry to hear that AttendanceBot is acting up. Here are some steps you can take to get help: 1. Email support at support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com or contact the support lead at sarah@harmonizehq.com. 2. Raise a ticket by sending 'dialm' as a direct message to AttendanceBot and click on 'Open'. If you are experiencing a specific error, please provide details for more targeted assistance.", "quality_score": 2.6, "bucket": "partial"}
{"query": "what happened to edit punches", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?"], "generated_answer": "To edit punches in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the AttendanceBot dashboard and select \"Timesheet actions\" from the \"Menu\".\n2. Click on \u201cEdit\u201d to access your timesheet editor.\n3. Choose the date range and, if applicable, the employee whose timesheet you want to edit.\n4. Expand the specific day to view minute-by-minute punch history.\n5. Click the pencil icon next to the punch you want to edit, update the details, and hit \"save\".\n\nYou can also delete punches by clicking the trashcan icon and confirming the deletion.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118260", "reference_answer": "To edit punches in AttendanceBot, follow these steps: 1. Go to the AttendanceBot dashboard and select 'Timesheet actions' from the 'Menu'. 2. Click on 'Edit' to access your timesheet editor. 3. Choose the date range and, if applicable, the employee whose timesheet you want to edit. 4. Expand the specific day to view minute-by-minute punch history. 5. Click the pencil icon next to the punch you want to edit, update the details, and hit 'save'. You can also delete punches by clicking the trashcan icon and confirming the deletion.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
