{"query": "What happened to edit punches in our timesheets?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?"], "generated_answer": "To edit punches in your timesheet using AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. From the \"Menu,\" select \"Timesheet actions\" and click \u201cEdit\u201d to access your timesheet editor on the dashboard.\n2. Choose your date range using the \u201cDate Range\u201d dropdown, and if needed, select another employee if you have reportees.\n3. Submit your selection to view daily summaries. Click \"expand\" on any day to see detailed punch history.\n4. To edit a punch, click the pencil icon, update details, and hit \"save.\" To delete, click the trashcan icon and confirm. To add a new entry, use the green \u201cadd punches\u201d button.\n\nNote: Editing is possible only if your admin has enabled \"Allow self editing of punches.\"\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118260", "reference_answer": "To edit punches in your timesheet using AttendanceBot, go to 'Timesheet actions' in the Menu, select 'Edit', choose your date range, and view daily summaries. Click 'expand' to see punch history. Edit a punch by clicking the pencil icon, or delete it with the trashcan icon. Ensure your admin has enabled 'Allow self editing of punches.'", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how to reflect google calendar automatically?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to integrate calendars", "How to integrate your calendar with AttendanceBot for Slack", "How to integrate your calendar with AttendanceBot for Slack"], "generated_answer": "To integrate your Google Calendar with AttendanceBot and reflect it automatically, follow these steps:\n\n1. In Slack, type \"cal\" as a direct message to AttendanceBot.\n2. Choose Google Calendar from the options and click \"Enable\" to sync.\n3. Alternatively, subscribe to a public calendar by clicking \"Get Link\" and follow these steps:\n   - Go to your Google Calendar.\n   - Click the down arrow next to \u201cOther calendars\u201d and select \u201cAdd by URL\u201d.\n   - Paste the URL and click \u201cAdd calendar\u201d.\n\nThis will keep your calendar updated with your team's leave information.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000017361", "reference_answer": "To automatically reflect your Google Calendar with AttendanceBot, follow these steps: 1. In Slack, type 'cal' as a direct message to AttendanceBot. 2. Choose Google Calendar from the options and click 'Enable' to sync. 3. Alternatively, go to your Google Calendar, click the down arrow next to 'Other calendars', select 'Add by URL', paste the URL provided by AttendanceBot, and click 'Add calendar'. This will keep your calendar updated with your team's leave information.", "quality_score": 4.6, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "I wanna quit Attendancebot", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to uninstall AttendanceBot from Slack", "How to deactivate a user in AttendanceBot", "How do I uninstall AttendanceBot from Google Chat ?"], "generated_answer": "To uninstall AttendanceBot from your Slack account, follow these steps:\n\n1. Select the AttendanceBot app on Slack and click on the \u201cAbout\" tab.\n2. Select the \"Configuration\" tab to be redirected to the Slack app directory page.\n3. Scroll down to the Remove Application section and click on the Remove App button to remove it from your workspace.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000121227", "reference_answer": "To uninstall AttendanceBot from your Slack account, follow these steps: 1. Select the AttendanceBot app on Slack and click on the 'About' tab. 2. Select the 'Configuration' tab to be redirected to the Slack app directory page. 3. Scroll down to the Remove Application section and click on the Remove App button to remove it from your workspace.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
