{"query": "add employee", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to bulk update employee data using import / export functionality", "How do I assign managers for my employees?", "How do I invite new users on my team to start using AttendanceBot?"], "generated_answer": "To add a new employee to AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure the employee is already a member of your Slack workspace.\n2. Go to your main 'settings' dashboard in AttendanceBot.\n3. If you want new workspace members to automatically become AttendanceBot users, toggle on \"Activate new users.\"\n4. Alternatively, manually activate them by going to People > Personnel, ensuring \"Show active personnel only\" is off, and toggling their status to \"Active.\"\n5. Optionally, set up additional fields like manager, office, department, and join date by clicking on their name.\n6. To send a welcome message, go to People > Invite, select the employee, and send the default or a custom message.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115576", "reference_answer": "To add a new employee to AttendanceBot, ensure they are in your Slack workspace, go to the settings dashboard, and either activate them automatically or manually. You can also set additional fields and send a welcome message.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
