{"query": " 'ticket' to get human support over email", "retrieved_contexts": ["How can I get help from AttendanceBot support?", "Ticket Response Time", "Billing - how do I download past invoices or receipts?"], "generated_answer": "To get human support over email, you can raise a ticket by:\n\n1. Sending a direct message with the command 'dialm' to AttendanceBot in Slack.\n2. Alternatively, email support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com or sarah@harmonizehq.com.\n\nThis will notify the support team, and they will respond as soon as possible.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118263", "reference_answer": "To get human support over email for AttendanceBot, you can follow these steps: 1. Email the support team at support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com. 2. Alternatively, email the support lead directly at sarah@harmonizehq.com. 3. To raise a ticket, send 'dialm' as a direct message to AttendanceBot.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "my attendance bot is not working", "retrieved_contexts": ["I'm getting an error message \"You are viewing the archives of a deactivated account\" while accessing AttendanceBot in Slack. What should I do?", "I don't use Slack or Microsoft Teams. Can I still use AttendanceBot?", "How do I install AttendanceBot in Slack?"], "generated_answer": "If AttendanceBot is not working, it might be due to a deactivated account or installation issues. Here's what you can do:\n\n1. Check if you see the message \"You are viewing the archives of a deactivated account.\" If so, the workspace might have been removed.\n2. Reinstall AttendanceBot by going to www.attendancebot.com, clicking on GET STARTED, and selecting TRY FOR SLACK.\n3. If AttendanceBot is not visible in Slack, click on the Apps icon, search for AttendanceBot in the App Directory, and add it to your Recent Apps list.\n\nYour data will remain safe, and once reinstalled, everyone can interact with AttendanceBot as usual.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000098428", "reference_answer": "If your AttendanceBot is not working, check if you see the message 'You are viewing the archives of a deactivated account.' This indicates the workspace may have been removed. To resolve this, reinstall AttendanceBot by visiting www.attendancebot.com, clicking on GET STARTED, and selecting TRY FOR SLACK. If AttendanceBot is not visible in Slack, search for it in the App Directory and add it to your Recent Apps list. Your data will remain safe, and everyone can interact with AttendanceBot as usual.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
