{"query": "1. Punch in/out reminder scheduled for 9:00 AM and 5:00 PM but the system doesn't send them.\n2. Lunch reminder scheduled for 12:00 PM but system doesn't send.\n3. Punch Card notification scheduled for 9:05 AM but it doesn't send.\n\nThe notifications are not working.", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to set up punch in/out reminders", "How to configure punch in/out alerts for reportees (Slack)", "What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?"], "generated_answer": "To troubleshoot the issue with notifications not being sent, please follow these steps:\n\n1. **Punch In/Out Reminders:**\n   - Go to Settings -> Basic Settings in the AttendanceBot dashboard.\n   - Scroll down to Time Settings and ensure the toggle is set to \"Active.\"\n   - Verify that the punch in/out times are correctly set to 9:00 AM and 5:00 PM.\n\n2. **Lunch Reminder:**\n   - Check if the lunch reminder is set up correctly in the dashboard.\n   - Ensure the time is set to 12:00 PM and the toggle is active.\n\n3. **Punch Card Notification:**\n   - Navigate to the Notifications section in the dashboard.\n   - Ensure the Punch Card notification is scheduled for 9:05 AM and the toggle is active.\n\nIf the settings are correct and the issue persists, consider opening a support ticket for further assistance.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000049838", "reference_answer": "To troubleshoot the issue with notifications not being sent, please follow these steps: 1. Punch In/Out Reminders: Go to Settings -> Basic Settings in the AttendanceBot dashboard. Scroll down to Time Settings and ensure the toggle is set to 'Active.' Verify that the punch in/out times are correctly set to 9:00 AM and 5:00 PM. 2. Lunch Reminder: Check if the lunch reminder is set up correctly in the dashboard. Ensure the time is set to 12:00 PM and the toggle is active. 3. Punch Card Notification: Navigate to the Notifications section in the dashboard. Ensure the Punch Card notification is scheduled for 9:05 AM and the toggle is active. If the settings are correct and the issue persists, consider opening a support ticket for further assistance.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
