{"query": "how can I automatically broadcast sick status updates to a channel.?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to configure shift alerts", "How to setup Slack channel notifications with AttendanceBot", "How to announce in/out and breaks/lunch on a Slack channel"], "generated_answer": "To automatically broadcast sick status updates to a Slack channel using AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure AttendanceBot is added to the relevant Slack channel by typing \"/invite @attendancebot\" in the channel.\n2. Navigate to the \"menu\" and select \"Settings, people, policy\" > \"Notifications.\"\n3. Click on \"Create new\" to configure a new notification rule.\n4. Select the appropriate notification type (e.g., \"In/Out Notifications\") and configure it to include sick status updates.\n5. Choose the channel, specify the people, and set the timing for the notification.\n6. Save the changes to activate the notification.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000049835", "reference_answer": "To automatically broadcast sick status updates to a Slack channel using AttendanceBot, ensure AttendanceBot is added to the channel, navigate to 'Settings, people, policy' > 'Notifications', create a new notification rule for sick status updates, choose the channel and timing, and save the changes.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
