{"query": "this is not free?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How long is my AttendanceBot trial?", "Billing - can I get a discount as a non-profit organization using AttendanceBot?", "Billing - how does adding or removing users affect my billing?"], "generated_answer": "AttendanceBot offers a 14-day free trial on Slack and Microsoft Teams. After the trial, if your team has more than 5 users, you will need to subscribe to continue using the app. Teams with 5 users or less can use AttendanceBot for free. \n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115577", "reference_answer": "AttendanceBot offers a 14-day free trial on Slack and Microsoft Teams. After the trial, if your team has more than 5 users, you will need to subscribe to continue using the app. Teams with 5 users or less can use AttendanceBot for free.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how do i create tasks for the day?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to create employee specific work schedules?", "How to Configure Project, Client, and Task / Subproject Tracking in AttendanceBot", "Time/Task tracking"], "generated_answer": "To create tasks for the day in AttendanceBot, you need to configure project, client, and task tracking. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n1. From your dashboard, go to the \u201cTime Tracking\u201d section.\n2. Click on the \u201cProjects and Clients\u201d page.\n3. If you haven\u2019t set up projects yet, click the blue \u201cCreate New\u201d button to create a project.\n4. Assign a name to the project and optionally describe it.\n5. If the project is for a specific client, select a client or create a new one.\n6. Choose between self-assign or managed assign for project assignment.\n7. Select the employee(s) to assign the project to.\n8. Click \u201cCreate Project\u201d to finish.\n\nOnce projects and clients are set up, users can select a project/client when they punch in.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000138976", "reference_answer": "To create tasks for the day in AttendanceBot, go to the 'Time Tracking' section, click on 'Projects and Clients', and create a project if needed. Assign it to employees, and they can select it when they punch in.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "How to I disable and remove attendancebot?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to deactivate a user in AttendanceBot", "How to uninstall AttendanceBot from Slack", "How do I uninstall AttendanceBot from Google Chat ?"], "generated_answer": "To disable and remove AttendanceBot from Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Deactivate a User**: \n   - Open the settings panel by typing \"Settings\" as a direct message to AttendanceBot and click the link prompted.\n   - Go to the dashboard, navigate to the people --> personnel tab, find the employee, and click the \"Inactive\" toggle next to the profile tile.\n\n2. **Uninstall AttendanceBot**:\n   - Select the AttendanceBot app on Slack and click on the \u201cAbout\" tab.\n   - Select the \"Configuration\" tab to be redirected to the Slack app directory page.\n   - Scroll down to the Remove Application section and click on the Remove App button.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131681", "reference_answer": "To disable and remove AttendanceBot from Slack, follow these steps: 1. Deactivate a User: Open the settings panel by typing 'Settings' as a direct message to AttendanceBot, go to the dashboard, navigate to the personnel tab, find the employee, and click the 'Inactive' toggle. 2. Uninstall AttendanceBot: Select the AttendanceBot app on Slack, click on the 'About' tab, go to 'Configuration', scroll down to the Remove Application section, and click 'Remove App'.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
