{"query": "hoe should i create all off the my employe attendance", "retrieved_contexts": ["What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?", "How to view my shifts and the shifts of my employees", "How to bulk update employee data using import / export functionality"], "generated_answer": "To create attendance records for all your employees in AttendanceBot, you can use the bulk update feature to import employee data. Here's how:\n\n1. Go to the dashboard and navigate to People >> Import Team Data.\n2. Download the current employee data to export it.\n3. Edit or populate the employee details in the spreadsheet, ensuring you don't add new rows or columns.\n4. Upload the updated file back to AttendanceBot to update the data in bulk.\n\nFor more detailed guidance, you can refer to the documentation or contact support.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000124709", "reference_answer": "To create attendance records for all your employees in AttendanceBot, use the bulk update feature. Go to People >> Import Team Data, download the current employee data, edit it, and upload the updated file back to AttendanceBot.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
