{"query": "will my plan automatically go onto  a paid plan", "retrieved_contexts": ["Billing - how does adding or removing users affect my billing?", "How long is my AttendanceBot trial?", "Billing - how does adding or removing users affect my billing?"], "generated_answer": "No, your plan will not automatically transition to a paid plan after the trial period ends. AttendanceBot explicitly asks you to subscribe to the app. If you have more than 5 members, you will need to subscribe to continue using the app beyond the 14-day free trial.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115577", "reference_answer": "No, your plan will not automatically transition to a paid plan after the trial period ends. AttendanceBot requires you to subscribe to continue using the app if you have more than 5 members after the 14-day free trial.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how do I export how many days I worked in 2025", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I get the summary or report of my time in office?", "How to download team vacation data and reporting", "How to apply for recurring leave or hybrid status"], "generated_answer": "To export the number of days you worked in 2025, you can generate a timesheet report for the specific period. Follow these steps:\n\n1. Type \"Timesheet Report [start_date] to [end_date]\" in Slack, replacing [start_date] and [end_date] with the desired dates in 2025.\n2. You will receive a CSV report to download, which includes your workdays for the specified period.\n\nIf you need further assistance, please open a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118258", "reference_answer": "To export the number of days you worked in 2025, generate a timesheet report by typing 'Timesheet Report [start_date] to [end_date]' in Slack. Replace [start_date] and [end_date] with your desired dates in 2025. You will receive a CSV report with your workdays for that period. For further assistance, open a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how to file for leave", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to apply for leave next year or any future year", "How can I apply for leave in Slack with AttendanceBot", "How to apply leave on behalf of employee on Slack as admin/manager"], "generated_answer": "To file for leave using AttendanceBot in Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Message \"menu\" to AttendanceBot to open the options menu navigator.\n2. Click the \u2018Apply\u2019 button to open a request form popup.\n3. Complete your request by choosing the leave type, duration, and date, and hit \u201cSubmit\u201d.\n\nYou can also shortcut the process by messaging AttendanceBot directly with the leave type and timing, such as \"sick today\" or \"pto next Thursday\".\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131679", "reference_answer": "To file for leave using AttendanceBot in Slack, type 'Apply' to open the request form. Fill in the leave type, duration, and dates, then hit 'Confirm' to submit. You can also message AttendanceBot directly with your leave details, like 'sick today'.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how to file for leave", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to apply for leave next year or any future year", "How can I apply for leave in Slack with AttendanceBot", "How to apply leave on behalf of employee on Slack as admin/manager"], "generated_answer": "To file for leave using AttendanceBot in Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Message \"menu\" to AttendanceBot to open the options menu navigator.\n2. Click the \u2018Apply\u2019 button to open a request form popup.\n3. Complete your request by selecting the leave type, duration, and date, then hit \u201cSubmit\u201d.\n\nYour current leave balance will be displayed for each leave type. If approval is required, you'll be notified once your manager approves or rejects the request. For non-approvals, the leave is auto-approved, and your manager will receive an FYI alert.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131679", "reference_answer": "To file for leave using AttendanceBot in Slack, follow these steps: 1. Message 'menu' to AttendanceBot to open the options menu navigator. 2. Click the \u2018Apply\u2019 button to open a request form popup. 3. Complete your request by selecting the leave type, duration, and date, then hit 'Submit'. Your current leave balance will be displayed for each leave type. If approval is required, you'll be notified once your manager approves or rejects the request. For non-approvals, the leave is auto-approved, and your manager will receive an FYI alert.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "open a ticket", "retrieved_contexts": ["Ticket Response Time", "How can I get help from AttendanceBot support?", "How to view and claim open shifts"], "generated_answer": "To open a ticket with AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Send a direct message with the text 'dialm' to AttendanceBot in Slack or Teams.\n2. Click on \"Open a ticket\" when prompted.\n\nAlternatively, you can email support at support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com or chat live with support using the chat bubble on the AttendanceBot dashboard.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118263", "reference_answer": "To open a ticket with AttendanceBot support, send 'dialm' as a direct message to AttendanceBot in Slack or Teams, then click on 'Open a ticket' when prompted. Alternatively, you can email support at support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com or use the live chat on the AttendanceBot dashboard.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
