{"query": "hello, I am unable to edit the punnches for 3 of my staff members, jaden, blake and thomas", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?"], "generated_answer": "To edit punches for your staff members in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the AttendanceBot dashboard and navigate to \"Time Tracking\" and then \"Edit Timesheet.\"\n2. Select the date range and the employee (Jaden, Blake, or Thomas) from the dropdown menu.\n3. Click on the \"Expand\" option for the specific date you want to edit.\n4. Click on the pencil icon to edit the punches.\n5. Update the punches as needed and hit \"save.\"\n\nEnsure that the \"Allow self editing of punches\" option is enabled in the timesheet settings if employees need to edit their own punches.\n\nIf you are still unable to edit, it might be a permissions issue, and you may need to check with your admin or open a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118266", "reference_answer": "To edit punches for your staff members in AttendanceBot, go to the dashboard, navigate to 'Time Tracking' > 'Edit Timesheet', select the employee and date range, expand the date, click the pencil icon to edit, and save your changes. Ensure 'Allow self editing of punches' is enabled if needed. If issues persist, check permissions or open a support ticket.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "make someone admin", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to change account admin", "How do I add admin users?", "How leave approval works in Slack"], "generated_answer": "To make someone an admin in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Send the command \"settings\" to the AttendanceBot in Slack to access the Settings Panel.\n2. In the Settings Panel, navigate to the Basic Settings page.\n3. Scroll down to the \"Other Settings\" section.\n4. Enter the username or select the name from the dropdown to add them as an admin.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000093468", "reference_answer": "To make someone an admin in AttendanceBot, send 'settings' to the bot in Slack, access the Settings Panel, go to Basic Settings, and select the user in the 'Other Settings' section.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "Can a supervisor clock in for an employee's sick leave?", "retrieved_contexts": ["What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?", "How to apply leave on behalf of employee on Slack as admin/manager", "Taking time off"], "generated_answer": "No, a supervisor cannot clock in for an employee's sick leave. However, a manager can apply for time off on behalf of their reporting employees, including sick leave, by typing the command \"Apply @Username\" in Slack, choosing the leave type, duration, and date from the dropdown menu, and then submitting it. The leave gets recorded without needing further approval, and the employee is notified about their time off.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000029132", "reference_answer": "No, a supervisor cannot clock in for an employee's sick leave. However, a manager can apply for sick leave on behalf of an employee using the command 'Apply @Username' in Slack.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "How do vacation leaves get calculated together with the hours so that you get the amount earned that month", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to setup accrual rules and leave quotas based on company policy", "What are the different kinds of leaves?", "How to apply for recurring leave or hybrid status"], "generated_answer": "To calculate vacation leave accrual with hours, follow these steps:\n\n1. Determine the annual leave count in days, which is the total number of days accrued annually.\n2. Configure the number of hours in a day in the general settings (default is 8 hours).\n3. Choose the accrual period (e.g., monthly, quarterly).\n4. AttendanceBot will automatically divide the annual leave count by the number of periods in a year to calculate the amount accrued each period.\n5. If using hourly accrual, leave is accrued based on time worked on the timesheet.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000051255", "reference_answer": "To calculate vacation leave accrual with hours, determine the annual leave count in days, configure the number of hours in a day, choose the accrual period, and AttendanceBot will automatically calculate the amount accrued each period based on your settings.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "The reports are not too friendly. Is there a way for us to customize a report?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to generate a report with specific filters", "How can I generate reports?", "How to schedule reports"], "generated_answer": "I don't have enough information on customizing reports beyond the available filters and scheduling options. You might consider opening a support ticket for further assistance by typing 'ticket'. \n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000116052", "reference_answer": "You can customize reports in AttendanceBot using available filters and scheduling options. For more detailed customization, I recommend opening a support ticket for further assistance. You can do this by typing 'ticket'. For more information, check the documentation here: https://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000116052.", "quality_score": 3.6, "bucket": "partial"}
{"query": "add punch in punch out", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to set up auto-punch out for my employees", "How to set up punch in/out reminders"], "generated_answer": "To add a new punch entry in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Click on the green \u201cadd punches\u201d button to open the punch entry menu.\n2. Choose the type of entry: punch in/out pair, punch out/in pair, single punch in, single punch out, or lunch/break.\n3. Enter the dates, times, any project tags, and remarks.\n4. Click \u201csave\u201d to create the punch entry.\n\nNote: Ensure that your admin has enabled \"Allow self editing of punches\" in timesheet settings for you to update punches.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118260", "reference_answer": "To add a punch in or punch out, follow these steps: 1. Go to the AttendanceBot dashboard. 2. Navigate to Time Tracking and select Edit Timesheet for the specific user. 3. Alternatively, use the command 'add punches @User' in Slack or MS Teams and follow the prompt. For more detailed instructions, visit the AttendanceBot support page.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
