{"query": "Sick leave notification sent to an unexpected channel", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to announce in/out and breaks/lunch on a Slack channel", "How to enable and understand leave privacy and hidden leave types", "How to setup Slack channel notifications with AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "If a sick leave notification is being sent to an unexpected channel, you might need to review the notification settings in AttendanceBot. Here's how you can manage leave type visibility:\n\n1. Go to \"Vacation Management\" -> \"Leaves\" -> \"Leave Types and Quotas.\"\n2. Click on the \"Edit\" icon for the sick leave type.\n3. Ensure \"show leave type\" is disabled to hide it from public interfaces like channel notifications.\n\nThis will ensure that the leave type is hidden, and notifications will only indicate that a user is on leave, not specifying the type.\n\nIf the issue persists, consider reviewing the channel notification settings to ensure they are configured correctly.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000105285", "reference_answer": "If a sick leave notification is being sent to an unexpected channel, review the notification settings in AttendanceBot. Go to 'Vacation Management' -> 'Leaves' -> 'Leave Types and Quotas.' Click on the 'Edit' icon for the sick leave type and ensure 'show leave type' is disabled. This will hide the leave type from public interfaces. If the issue persists, check the channel notification settings for proper configuration.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "On my quotas and balance page, is there a way to only see the active typles of leaves, or have the active types all at the top?", "retrieved_contexts": ["Checking Your Leave Balance", "How to enable and understand leave privacy and hidden leave types", "How to setup accrual rules and leave quotas based on company policy"], "generated_answer": "The documentation does not specify a way to filter or reorder leave types to show only active ones or to have active types appear at the top on the quotas and balance page. You may want to open a support ticket for further assistance.\n\nticket", "reference_answer": "Currently, there is no documented way to filter or reorder leave types on the quotas and balance page to show only active types or have them at the top. For further assistance, please consider opening a support ticket.", "quality_score": 3.4, "bucket": "partial"}
{"query": "how to add ms teams people to bot", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I invite new users on my team to start using AttendanceBot?", "Adding New Users to Hangouts/Google Chat", "How do I add admin users?"], "generated_answer": "To add new users from Microsoft Teams to AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure the new users are already members of your Microsoft Teams workspace.\n2. Go to your main 'settings' dashboard in AttendanceBot.\n3. Choose one of the following options:\n   - **Option 1**: Automatically activate new users by toggling on \"Activate new users\". Optionally, also toggle on \"Auto invite new users\" for a welcome message.\n   - **Option 2**: Manually activate users by going to the 'settings' dashboard, navigating to People --> Personnel tab, ensuring \"Show active personnel only\" is off, and toggling the new user's status to \"Active\".\n\nFor any issues, contact support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com or chat \"dialm\" to AttendanceBot to open a support ticket.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115576", "reference_answer": "To add new users from Microsoft Teams to AttendanceBot, ensure they are members of your Teams workspace, then go to AttendanceBot's settings dashboard. You can either automatically activate new users or manually activate them by adjusting their status in the personnel tab.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
