{"query": "One of our colleagues is experiencing challenges while trying to apply for leave", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to apply leave on behalf of employee on Slack as admin/manager", "How to apply for leave next year or any future year", "How can I apply for leave in Slack with AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "To apply for leave in Slack using AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Message \"menu\" to AttendanceBot to open the options menu navigator.\n2. Click the \u2018Apply\u2019 button to open a request form popup.\n3. Complete your request by choosing the leave type, duration, and date, and hit \u201cSubmit\u201d.\n\nIf the request type requires approval, it will be routed to the manager, and the employee will be notified once it's approved or rejected. For non-approvals, the leave is auto-approved, and the manager receives an FYI alert.\n\nIf further assistance is needed, you can open a support ticket by typing \"Dialm\" to AttendanceBot.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131679", "reference_answer": "To apply for leave in Slack using AttendanceBot, message 'menu' to open the options menu, click 'Apply', fill out the form with leave type, duration, and date, then hit 'Submit'. If approval is needed, it will be sent to the manager. For further help, type 'Dialm' to open a support ticket.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
