{"query": "One of my colleague got zero off days left where in reality he is supposed to have 18 off days. So he is not able to apply for off.", "retrieved_contexts": ["Taking time off", "How to setup accrual rules and leave quotas based on company policy", "How to apply for time off for half a day or few hours?"], "generated_answer": "It seems there might be an issue with the leave balance setup for your colleague. Here's how you can address it:\n\n1. Check the accrual rules and leave quotas set up in AttendanceBot to ensure they align with your company's policy.\n2. Verify if there is a cap on the annual leave count or if rollover settings are affecting the balance.\n3. Ensure that the \"Allow negative balance\" option is configured correctly if needed.\n4. If the issue persists, consider adjusting the leave balance manually or contact support for further assistance.\n\nIf these steps do not resolve the issue, please open a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000051255", "reference_answer": "It seems there might be an issue with the leave balance setup for your colleague. Please check the accrual rules and leave quotas in AttendanceBot to ensure they align with your company's policy. If the issue persists, consider adjusting the leave balance manually or contact support for further assistance. You can also open a support ticket for immediate help.", "quality_score": 4.6, "bucket": "well_answered"}
