{"query": "Hello,\n\nI am trying to configure a leave type and enable it to go on a negative balance.\n\nI have set the days allowed to go negative to \"15\", while my current balance is \"2.08\". \n\nWhen I prompt for a 7 day vacation the bot gives me the following response:\n\n\"You are trying to apply for On vacation for 7 days starting tomorrow, ending on Monday, 26 January, 2026 which exceeds your remaining balance of 2.08 days. Please try applying for a different leave type or fewer days. Type Quotas to know more.\"\n\nHow can I go about that?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to setup accrual rules and leave quotas based on company policy", "How to setup accrual rules and leave quotas based on company policy", "Checking Your Leave Balance"], "generated_answer": "To enable a leave type to go into a negative balance, follow these steps:\n\n1. Navigate to the leave type settings in your AttendanceBot dashboard.\n2. Ensure the leave type you want to configure is active.\n3. Locate the option to allow a negative balance and enable it.\n4. Set the minimum negative threshold to the desired value (e.g., -15 days).\n\nIf you've already set the negative threshold to 15 days and it's not working, double-check that the setting is saved correctly. If issues persist, consider opening a support ticket for further assistance.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000051255", "reference_answer": "To enable a leave type to go into a negative balance, navigate to the leave type settings in your AttendanceBot dashboard, ensure the leave type is active, enable the option for negative balance, and set the minimum negative threshold to your desired value. If the issue persists, check if the settings are saved correctly or open a support ticket for assistance.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how to request leave ", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to request hourly or half day leave", "How to apply for leave next year or any future year", "Taking time off"], "generated_answer": "To request leave using AttendanceBot in Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Type \"menu\" in a message to AttendanceBot to open the options menu navigator.\n2. Select \u2018Apply\u2019 to open a request form.\n3. Choose the leave type and specify the leave duration and dates.\n4. Hit \"Confirm\" to submit your leave request.\n\nAlternatively, you can use a direct command by typing the leave type and date, such as \"Vacation 05/04 to 05/07\" for a four-day leave.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000116053", "reference_answer": "To request leave using AttendanceBot in Slack, type 'menu' to open the options menu, select 'Apply' to fill out the request form, choose the leave type, specify the duration and dates, and hit 'Confirm' to submit. You can also use a direct command like 'Vacation 05/04 to 05/07'.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
