{"query": "how do i apply for h9olidays", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to add a team holiday", "How to apply for leave next year or any future year", "How to apply for recurring leave or hybrid status"], "generated_answer": "To apply for holidays, you should use the \"apply\" command with AttendanceBot. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n1. Send a direct message to AttendanceBot with the word \"apply\".\n2. Select the details such as leave type, leave duration, and dates.\n3. Hit \"Confirm\" to submit your holiday application.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118253", "reference_answer": "To apply for holidays, send a direct message to AttendanceBot with the word 'apply'. Follow the prompts to enter leave type, duration, and dates, then hit 'Confirm' to submit your application. For more details, visit the support article: https://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118253.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "How do i export time sheets", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I get the summary or report of my time in office?", "How to approve the timesheets of my reportees", "How to approve the timesheets of my reportees"], "generated_answer": "To export timesheets, follow these steps:\n\n1. For employees, type \"timesheet report\" in Slack to receive a CSV report for the current and previous month.\n2. To generate a report for a specific time period, append the date range to the command. Example: \"Timesheet Report Jan 3 to Feb 10\".\n3. For managers, type \"Report\" and select the report type as Timesheet Report/Timesheet Summary Report, choose the relevant details, and hit \"Confirm\" to download the CSV report.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118258", "reference_answer": "To export timesheets in AttendanceBot, type 'timesheet report' in Slack for a CSV report of the current and previous month. For a specific date range, use 'Timesheet Report [start date] to [end date]'. Managers can type 'Report', select Timesheet Report, and confirm to download.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "can you cancel approved pto request", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to change or edit an existing approved leave", "How to cancel / retract / rescind / delete a leave request", "How to approve the timesheets of my reportees"], "generated_answer": "Yes, you can cancel an approved PTO request in AttendanceBot. Here\u2019s how:\n\n1. Open the \"Menu\" in AttendanceBot.\n2. Select \"Time off & hybrid work\".\n3. You will see an option labeled \u201cDelete\u201d for your approved or pending upcoming leaves.\n4. Click \u201cDelete\u201d below the leave details to cancel it. This action will notify both you and your manager.\n\nNote: If you need to delete a past leave that has already elapsed, you must ask your manager or an admin.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000121203", "reference_answer": "Yes, you can cancel an approved PTO request in AttendanceBot. To do this, open the 'Menu', select 'Time off & hybrid work', and click 'Delete' next to your approved leave. This will notify you and your manager. For past leaves, contact your manager or admin.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
