{"query": "i want to change workday work start time but i dont see options to change it, do i need to be an admin ?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to create employee specific work schedules?", "How to define your team work week", "How to change account admin"], "generated_answer": "To change the work start time for an employee, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the work schedule section under the People tab on the settings dashboard.\n2. Select the employee and click on the edit button.\n3. Edit the working days and start time, or add different start times and work hours for different days.\n4. Click on save changes.\n\nYou do not necessarily need to be an admin to perform these actions, but you need access to the settings dashboard. If you cannot access it, you might need to contact your admin.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000142683", "reference_answer": "To change the work start time for an employee, go to the work schedule section under the People tab on the settings dashboard. Select the employee, click edit, and adjust the working days and start time. You don't need to be an admin, but you need access to the settings dashboard. If you can't access it, contact your admin.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "can i connect my outlook callendar ?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to integrate your calendar with AttendanceBot for Slack", "How to integrate calendars", "How to integrate your calendar with AttendanceBot for Slack"], "generated_answer": "Yes, you can connect your Outlook calendar with AttendanceBot. Here's how:\n\n1. Go to the options \"menu\" in AttendanceBot and select \"data & integrations.\"\n2. Choose \"Calendar\" from the sub-menu.\n3. Click \"Enable\" to initiate an Outlook permissions grant for personal calendar sync. If it's already enabled, it will show \"Disable.\"\n4. For Outlook.com, log in to your calendar, click \u201cimport,\u201d paste the URL into \u201cCalendar URL,\u201d enter a name, and click \u201cSubscribe.\u201d\n5. For Office 365/Outlook 365, sign in, click on \u201cOther Calendars,\u201d choose \u201cOpen Calendar,\u201d enter the URL into \u201cInternet Calendar,\u201d and click \u201cOpen.\u201d\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000017361", "reference_answer": "Yes, you can connect your Outlook calendar with AttendanceBot. To do this, go to the options menu, select 'data & integrations,' then 'Calendar.' Click 'Enable' to grant permissions for syncing. For Outlook.com, log in, click 'import,' paste the URL, and subscribe. For Office 365, sign in, go to 'Other Calendars,' choose 'Open Calendar,' enter the URL, and click 'Open.'", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
