{"query": "I want to make a new employee an admin", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I add admin users?", "What are the different roles?", "How do I invite new users on my team to start using AttendanceBot?"], "generated_answer": "To make a new employee an admin in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Send the command \"settings\" to the bot to access the Settings Panel.\n2. Navigate to Settings --> Basic Settings.\n3. Scroll down to the \"Other Settings\" section.\n4. Enter the username or select the name from the dropdown to add the employee as an admin.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000093468", "reference_answer": "To make a new employee an admin in AttendanceBot, send the command 'settings' to access the Settings Panel. Navigate to Settings --> Basic Settings, scroll down to 'Other Settings', and enter the username or select the name from the dropdown to add the employee as an admin. For more details, visit: https://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000093468.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how to add new personnel", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I assign managers for my employees?", "How to bulk update employee data using import / export functionality", "How do I invite new users on my team to start using AttendanceBot?"], "generated_answer": "To add new personnel to AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure the new users are already members of your Slack or Microsoft Teams workspace.\n2. Option 1: Automatically activate new users.\n   - Go to your main 'settings' dashboard.\n   - Scroll down and toggle on \"Activate new users\".\n   - Optionally, toggle on \"Auto invite new users\" for a welcome message.\n3. Option 2: Manually activate new users.\n   - Open the 'settings' dashboard and go to People > Personnel tab.\n   - Ensure \"Show active personnel only\" is turned off.\n   - Search for the new user profile and toggle their status to \"Active\".\n   - Optionally, set up additional fields like manager, office, and department.\n   - Send a welcome message via People > Invite.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115576", "reference_answer": "To add new personnel to AttendanceBot, ensure they are members of your Slack or Microsoft Teams workspace. You can either automatically activate them through the settings dashboard or manually activate them by searching for their profile in the People > Personnel tab. Optionally, you can send a welcome message.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "add new employees", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I invite new users on my team to start using AttendanceBot?", "How do I assign managers for my employees?", "How to bulk update employee data using import / export functionality"], "generated_answer": "To add new employees to AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n**Option 1: Automatic Activation**\n1. Go to your main 'settings' dashboard.\n2. Scroll down and toggle on \"Activate new users\".\n3. Optionally, toggle on \"Auto invite new users\" for a welcome message.\n\n**Option 2: Manual Activation**\n1. Open the 'settings' dashboard and go to People > Personnel tab.\n2. Ensure \"Show active personnel only\" is turned off.\n3. Search for the new user and toggle their status to \"Active\".\n4. Optionally, set up additional fields like manager, office, etc.\n5. To send a welcome message, go to People > Invite, select the employee, and send a message.\n\nIf you encounter issues, contact support at support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com or chat \"dialm\" to open a support ticket.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115576", "reference_answer": "To add new employees to AttendanceBot, go to your settings dashboard. You can either activate new users automatically or manually by searching for them in the personnel tab. Ensure to send a welcome message if desired. For more details, visit the support portal.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
