{"query": "notify when someone clocks in or out", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to announce in/out and breaks/lunch on a Slack channel", "How to configure punch in/out alerts for reportees (Slack)", "How to set up punch in/out reminders"], "generated_answer": "To notify when someone clocks in or out on a Slack channel, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure AttendanceBot is added to the relevant Slack channels by typing `@attendancebot` or sending `/invite @attendancebot` in the channel.\n2. Navigate to \"Settings, people, policy\" > \"Notifications\" in the AttendanceBot menu.\n3. Click \"Create new\" to configure a new notification rule.\n4. Select the \"In/Out Notifications\" tile, configure the channel, people, and timing, and hit \"save changes.\"\n\nFor more detailed instructions, refer to the article linked below.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000049835", "reference_answer": "To notify when someone clocks in or out on a Slack channel, ensure AttendanceBot is added to the channel, navigate to 'Settings, people, policy' > 'Notifications', create a new notification rule, select 'In/Out Notifications', configure the details, and save changes. For more details, refer to the AttendanceBot documentation.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
