{"query": "Personel only needs to be employees we are tracking time for? ", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to track time spent on a project, task, or client", "How to track time spent on a project, task, or client", "Time/Task tracking"], "generated_answer": "Yes, personnel tracked in AttendanceBot should be those employees for whom you need to track time. Once projects and clients are set up, admins can assign these projects to specific employees. These employees will then select the relevant project or client when they punch in, ensuring that time is tracked accurately for the designated personnel.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000051253", "reference_answer": "Yes, personnel tracked in AttendanceBot should be those employees for whom you need to track time. Admins can assign projects to these employees, who will select the relevant project or client when they punch in.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "Can employees swap shifts without manager approval?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to cancel, re-assign, or swap shifts as an employee", "How to swap or reassign shifts", "How leave approval works in Slack"], "generated_answer": "No, employees cannot swap shifts without manager approval. When an employee submits a shift swap request, it is sent to their manager for approval. The manager can then approve, deny, or assign the shift to someone else. \n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131564", "reference_answer": "Employees cannot swap shifts without manager approval. They must submit a shift swap request, which is reviewed by the manager who can approve, deny, or assign the shift to someone else.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "We don't understand how to get started.  We chose Slack and got an error message.  Then we chose Teams and it just opened Teams", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I invite new users on my team to start using AttendanceBot?", "How do I install AttendanceBot in Slack?", "How to use Slack onboarding functionality"], "generated_answer": "To get started with AttendanceBot on Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Search for \"AttendanceBot\" under Apps in Slack.\n2. Click \"Add to Slack\" and follow the prompts.\n3. Once added, the app will onboard the admin and request permission to introduce itself to the team. Accept this request.\n4. After that, everyone will receive a direct message from AttendanceBot and can begin using it for leave and time tracking.\n\nIf you're facing issues, you can open a support ticket by typing 'dialm' to AttendanceBot for live chat assistance.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118255", "reference_answer": "To get started with AttendanceBot on Slack, search for 'AttendanceBot' under Apps in Slack, click 'Add to Slack', and follow the prompts. If you encounter issues, type 'dialm' for live chat assistance.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
