{"query": "i need to take off the working in office status off of myself. Where are all of the approved leaves? I need to cancel them all.", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to cancel / retract / rescind / delete a leave request", "How to change or edit an existing approved leave", "How to delete approved leave for a reportee or employee"], "generated_answer": "To cancel your own leave requests, including work statuses like \"working in office,\" follow these steps:\n\n1. Open the \"Menu\" in AttendanceBot.\n2. Select \"Time off & hybrid work.\"\n3. You will see an option labeled \u201cDelete\u201d for each approved or pending upcoming leave.\n4. Click \u201cDelete\u201d to cancel the leave. Both you and your manager will be notified.\n\nIf you need to delete a past leave that has already elapsed, you will need to ask your manager or an admin to do it for you.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000121203", "reference_answer": "To cancel your own leave requests, including work statuses like 'working in office,' follow these steps: 1. Open the 'Menu' in AttendanceBot. 2. Select 'Time off & hybrid work.' 3. Click 'Delete' for each approved or pending leave. 4. Both you and your manager will be notified. For past leaves, contact your manager or admin.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "I need to turn off hybrid everything. How do i turn off the \"working in the office\" status?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to configure hybrid work policies", "Work Model - Hybrid or Fully Remote", "Work Model - Hybrid or Fully Remote"], "generated_answer": "To turn off the \"working in the office\" status and disable hybrid work settings, follow these steps:\n\n1. Access the AttendanceBot settings in your Slack workspace.\n2. Navigate to the hybrid work model settings.\n3. Remove or disable any existing WFO (Work From Office) policies, including office capacity limits and minimum days in-office requirements.\n4. Ensure that all custom notifications related to hybrid work are turned off.\n5. Save your changes to ensure the settings are updated.\n\nIf you need further assistance, consider opening a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000117213", "reference_answer": "To turn off the 'working in the office' status, go to AttendanceBot settings in your Slack workspace, navigate to hybrid work model settings, disable WFO policies, turn off notifications, and save your changes.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "The vacation accrual interval is being wrong calculated", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to setup accrual rules and leave quotas based on company policy", "How to setup accrual rules and leave quotas based on company policy", "How to setup accrual rules and leave quotas based on company policy"], "generated_answer": "To address issues with vacation accrual intervals, ensure the following settings are correctly configured:\n\n1. **Accrual Period**: Verify the selected accrual period (e.g., annual, half-yearly) matches your policy.\n2. **Annual Leave Count**: Check the annualized number of days set for accrual.\n3. **Rollover Settings**: Confirm the rollover days and cap on annual leave count are correctly set.\n4. **Pro Rata**: Ensure pro rata is enabled if applicable for new joiners.\n5. **General Settings**: Verify the number of hours in a day is set correctly, typically 8 hours.\n\nIf the issue persists, consider opening a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000051255", "reference_answer": "To address issues with vacation accrual intervals, ensure the following settings are correctly configured: 1. Accrual Period: Verify the selected accrual period matches your policy. 2. Annual Leave Count: Check the annualized number of days set for accrual. 3. Rollover Settings: Confirm the rollover days and cap on annual leave count are correctly set. 4. Pro Rata: Ensure pro rata is enabled if applicable for new joiners. 5. General Settings: Verify the number of hours in a day is set correctly. If the issue persists, consider opening a support ticket.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "I have work in office leaves showing up and i need to know how to take that off", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to enable and understand leave privacy and hidden leave types", "How do I delete a leave applied by a member of my team?", " How to view overlapping leaves as an approving manager"], "generated_answer": "To hide a leave type such as \"work in office\" from public interfaces like channel notifications, summaries, and calendars, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to Vacation Management -> Leaves -> Leave Types and Quotas.\n2. Select the leave type you want to hide by clicking on the \"Edit\" icon.\n3. Disable \"show leave type\" for that leave type.\n\nOnce disabled, the leave type will be hidden from all public interfaces. Managers will still be able to see the leave type when approving leaves.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000105285", "reference_answer": "To hide the 'work in office' leave type, go to Vacation Management -> Leaves -> Leave Types and Quotas. Select the leave type and disable 'show leave type'. This will hide it from public interfaces while still allowing managers to see it.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "How do i turn off the hybrid settings?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to configure hybrid work policies", "How to manage hybrid work schedules (WFO/WFH days) in Slack using AttendanceBot", "Work Model - Hybrid or Fully Remote"], "generated_answer": "To turn off hybrid settings in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the \"Menu\" and select \"Time off and hybrid work.\"\n2. Look for the option to manage your weekly hybrid \u201cSchedule.\u201d\n3. Choose the \u201cDelete\u201d option to eliminate the schedule entirely.\n\nNote: Ensure that office capacities are set to unlimited and WFH/WFO requests are configured to allow unlimited requests without requiring approval for the schedule function to be available.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131569", "reference_answer": "To turn off hybrid settings in AttendanceBot, go to the 'Menu', select 'Time off and hybrid work', manage your weekly hybrid 'Schedule', and choose 'Delete' to eliminate it. Ensure office capacities are set to unlimited and WFH/WFO requests allow unlimited requests without approval.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
