{"query": "How do i add a new employee", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I invite new users on my team to start using AttendanceBot?", "How do I assign managers for my employees?", "How do I add admin users?"], "generated_answer": "To add a new employee to AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure the new employee is a member of your Slack or Teams workspace.\n2. Option 1: Automatically activate new users:\n   - Go to your main 'settings' dashboard.\n   - Scroll down and toggle on \"Activate new users\".\n   - Optionally, toggle on \"Auto invite new users\" for a welcome message.\n3. Option 2: Manually activate new users:\n   - Open the 'settings' dashboard and go to People > Personnel tab.\n   - Turn off \"Show active personnel only\" to view new users.\n   - Search for the new user and toggle their status to \"Active\".\n   - Optionally, set up additional fields like manager, office, etc.\n   - Send a welcome message via People > Invite.\n\nIf you encounter issues, contact support at support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com or chat \"dialm\" to open a support ticket.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115576", "reference_answer": "To add a new employee to AttendanceBot, ensure they are in your Slack or Teams workspace. You can either automatically activate them via the settings dashboard or manually activate them by searching in the People > Personnel tab. For more details, visit the support portal.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
