{"query": "add to workflow", "retrieved_contexts": ["Automate time-off requests using Slack's workflow builder", "How do I add or change my approving manager?", "How to create employee specific work schedules?"], "generated_answer": "To add a workflow using Slack's workflow builder, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open Slack\u2019s workflow builder by selecting it under Tools in the workspace menu or by clicking the Shortcut lightning icon from any channel.\n2. Choose to create a workflow from scratch or select a template.\n3. Connect the apps you want to automate with Slack.\n4. Follow the workflow builder's guidance to select and create a workflow for your task.\n5. Publish the workflow.\n6. Access the workflow from the Shortcut icon or under Tools.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000110882", "reference_answer": "To add a workflow using Slack's workflow builder, follow these steps: 1. Open Slack\u2019s workflow builder by selecting it under Tools in the workspace menu or by clicking the Shortcut lightning icon from any channel. 2. Choose to create a workflow from scratch or select a template. 3. Connect the apps you want to automate with Slack. 4. Follow the workflow builder's guidance to select and create a workflow for your task. 5. Publish the workflow. 6. Access the workflow from the Shortcut icon or under Tools.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
