{"query": "i dnont want to create country holiday manually.", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to add a team holiday", "How to set up offices and regional holiday calendars", "How to use and configure the AttendanceBot vacation calendar"], "generated_answer": "To avoid manually creating country holidays, you can set up regional holiday calendars by creating offices and mapping holidays to them. Here's how:\n\n1. Type \"settings\" in a direct message to AttendanceBot.\n2. Go to the settings panel and click on the \"Offices\" section in the sidebar.\n3. Use the \"Create new\" option to create a new office.\n4. Assign offices to employees by going to the \"People\" option in the sidebar and updating their profiles on the Personnel page.\n5. Create holidays for each office.\n\nThis setup allows you to manage regional holidays without manual entry for each country.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000051706", "reference_answer": "To avoid manually creating country holidays, set up regional holiday calendars by creating offices and mapping holidays to them. Type 'settings' in a direct message to AttendanceBot, go to the 'Offices' section, create a new office, assign it to employees, and create holidays for each office.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how to set nationa holidays", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to add a team holiday", "How to set up offices and regional holiday calendars", "How to use and configure the AttendanceBot vacation calendar"], "generated_answer": "To set national holidays for your team, follow these steps:\n\n1. Type \"settings\" in a direct message to AttendanceBot.\n2. Navigate to Vacation Management -> Calendar -> Holidays tab.\n3. For regional holidays, create offices and map holidays to them by clicking on the Offices section in the settings panel.\n4. Use the \"Create new\" option to create a new office and assign it to employees via the People option in their profile.\n5. Create holidays for each office as needed.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118248", "reference_answer": "To set national holidays for your team, type 'settings' in a direct message to AttendanceBot. Navigate to Vacation Management -> Calendar -> Holidays tab. Create holidays for your team by specifying the office or multiple offices if needed. For more details, refer to the article link: https://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118248", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "can we setup a work schedule for my team members in your app?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to create employee specific work schedules?", "How to define your team work week", "How to view my shifts and the shifts of my employees"], "generated_answer": "Yes, you can set up customized work schedules for your team members in AttendanceBot. Here's how:\n\n1. Go to the work schedule section under the People tab on the settings dashboard.\n2. Select the employee and click on the edit button.\n3. Edit the working days and start time, or add different start times and work hours for different days.\n4. Click on save changes to apply the schedule.\n\nYou can also create a workday template and assign it to employees in bulk by opening the \"Template\" section under work schedule and clicking on \"Create new.\"\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000142683", "reference_answer": "Yes, you can set up customized work schedules for your team members in AttendanceBot. Here's how: 1. Go to the work schedule section under the People tab on the settings dashboard. 2. Select the employee and click on the edit button. 3. Edit the working days and start time, or add different start times and work hours for different days. 4. Click on save changes to apply the schedule. You can also create a workday template and assign it to employees in bulk by opening the 'Template' section under work schedule and clicking on 'Create new.'", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
