{"query": "I need to see the plans for purchase", "retrieved_contexts": ["AttendanceBot Plans and Features", "How to schedule reports", "How to Configure Project, Client, and Task / Subproject Tracking in AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "AttendanceBot offers three plans: \n\n1. **Standard Plan**: Includes essentials like time tracking & editing, unlimited hybrid statuses, custom leave types & approvals, real-time reports, and timely reminders & notifications.\n\n2. **Pro Plan**: Includes everything in the Standard Plan plus features like overtime calculation and a live punch board for real-time status updates.\n\nFor more details on the features of each plan, please visit the link below.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000138965", "reference_answer": "AttendanceBot offers three plans: Standard, Pro, and Enterprise. The Standard Plan includes time tracking, unlimited hybrid statuses, and real-time reports. The Pro Plan adds overtime calculation and a live punch board. For more details, visit: https://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000138965.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "Won\u2019t let me edit timesheet ", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How do I unlock the timesheet that's approved?", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times "], "generated_answer": "If you're unable to edit your timesheet, it might be because the \"Allow self editing of punches\" setting is not enabled by your admin. Here\u2019s what you can do:\n\n1. Check with your admin to ensure that the \"Allow self editing of punches\" option is enabled in the timesheet settings.\n2. If the setting is enabled and you still can't edit, try accessing the timesheet editor through the \"Menu\" and selecting \"Timesheet actions\" to make your changes.\n3. If the issue persists, consider opening a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118260", "reference_answer": "If you're unable to edit your timesheet, it might be because the 'Allow self editing of punches' setting is not enabled by your admin. Check with your admin to ensure this option is enabled. If it is and you still can't edit, try accessing the timesheet editor through the 'Menu' and selecting 'Timesheet actions'. If the issue persists, consider opening a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
