{"query": "I looked into this about a year ago but did not follow through. Under my Chats there is one for attendancebot. I need to pay for this attach it to our company teams and setup my employees.", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to setup Slack channel notifications with AttendanceBot", "AttendanceBot Plans and Features", "Installing AttendanceBot in Google Chat & Introducing New Users"], "generated_answer": "To set up AttendanceBot for your company and manage your employees, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Install AttendanceBot**: Ensure AttendanceBot is installed in your Slack or Google Workspace. For Google Chat, follow the \"find a bot\" procedure to install it. For Slack, use the command `/invite @attendancebot` in the desired channel.\n\n2. **Choose a Plan**: Review the available plans and features to select the one that best fits your company's needs. You can find detailed information about the plans and features on the pricing page or by contacting support.\n\n3. **Set Up Teams and Employees**: Once installed, you can start setting up your teams and adding employees. This may involve configuring specific rules like Time-off-in-Lieu, probation periods, and differential leave policies.\n\n4. **Configure Notifications**: Set up channel notifications to keep your team informed about key events like vacations, birthdays, and shift changes.\n\nIf you need further assistance, consider reaching out to the support desk at support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000138965", "reference_answer": "To set up AttendanceBot for your company, install it in your Slack or Google Workspace, choose a suitable plan, set up your teams and employees, and configure notifications. For detailed guidance, refer to the AttendanceBot support articles.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
