{"query": "I set me as the manager of Kent Chen, but his leaving approval still goes to Pop", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I add or change my approving manager?", "How leave approval works in Slack", "Approval routing and multi-level approvals for leaves"], "generated_answer": "To change the manager for Kent Chen so that leave approvals go to you instead of Pop, follow these steps:\n\n1. In Slack, type \"change manager @KentChen\".\n2. Select your name from the dropdown menu to set yourself as the manager.\n3. Ensure that the change is saved, and future leave requests from Kent Chen should now be directed to you for approval.\n\nIf the issue persists, consider using the import/export feature or visit the personnel page to verify the manager assignment.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131996", "reference_answer": "To change the manager for Kent Chen so that leave approvals go to you instead of Pop, follow these steps: 1. In Slack, type 'change manager @KentChen'. 2. Select your name from the dropdown menu to set yourself as the manager. 3. Ensure that the change is saved. If the issue persists, check the personnel page or contact support.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
