{"query": "I want to know how the team will be invited to set up attendance bot", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I install AttendanceBot in Slack?", "How do I invite new users on my team to start using AttendanceBot?", "How to setup Slack channel notifications with AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "To invite your team to start using AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure all team members are part of your Slack workspace, as AttendanceBot syncs directly with Slack.\n2. Option 1: Automatically activate new users.\n   - Go to your main 'settings' dashboard.\n   - Scroll down and toggle on \"Activate new users.\"\n   - Optionally, toggle on \"Auto invite new users\" for a welcome message.\n3. Option 2: Manually activate new users.\n   - Open the 'settings' dashboard and go to People > Personnel tab.\n   - Ensure \"Show active personnel only\" is turned off.\n   - Search for the new user and toggle their status to \"Active.\"\n   - Optionally set up additional fields like manager, office, etc.\n   - Send a welcome message via People > Invite page.\n\nIf you encounter issues, contact support at support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com or chat \"dialm\" to AttendanceBot for assistance.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115576", "reference_answer": "To invite your team to start using AttendanceBot, ensure all members are in your Slack workspace. You can either automatically activate new users through the settings dashboard or manually activate them by searching for their names in the personnel tab. For assistance, contact support at support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
