{"query": "how do we enter hours for a specific project in the timesheet?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to track time spent on a project, task, or client", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times "], "generated_answer": "To enter hours for a specific project in the timesheet, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure your admin has configured projects or clients by creating and optionally assigning them.\n2. During the punch in process, select the client, project, or task from the available options. This will tag your punch to the specific project.\n3. If you prefer, you can directly type \"in\" or \"out\" to AttendanceBot to toggle across projects quickly.\n4. Once time is tracked, it will be reflected in the timesheet report, project report, and project tracking dashboard for analysis.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000051253", "reference_answer": "To enter hours for a specific project in the timesheet, ensure your admin has configured projects. Use the punch in workflow to select the project, and type 'in' to start tracking time. Your tracked time will be reflected in reports.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how do I add a new project for timesheets as an admin?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to approve the timesheets of my reportees", "How to approve the timesheets of my reportees", "How to track time spent on a project, task, or client"], "generated_answer": "To add a new project for timesheets as an admin, follow these steps:\n\n1. Navigate to the settings section of AttendanceBot.\n2. Go to the \"Projects\" or \"Clients\" configuration area.\n3. Create a new project by entering the necessary details.\n4. Optionally, assign the project to specific employees or teams.\n\nOnce projects are configured, they will be available for selection during the punch-in workflow, allowing time tracking against specific projects, clients, or tasks.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000051253", "reference_answer": "To add a new project for timesheets as an admin, log in to the admin panel of AttendanceBot, navigate to the project configuration section, create a new project by entering the necessary details, optionally assign the project to specific clients or tasks, and save the changes. The new project will then be available for time tracking.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "where can i find the project tracking dashboard", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to track time spent on a project, task, or client", "How to track time spent on a project, task, or client", "How to Configure Project, Client, and Task / Subproject Tracking in AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "To find the project tracking dashboard in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the \"dashboard\" in AttendanceBot.\n2. Navigate to \"time tracking.\"\n3. Select \"project tracking.\"\n\nThis dashboard provides tools for analyzing time usage with visualizations like pie charts and area charts, which can be toggled between daily, weekly, and monthly views.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000051253", "reference_answer": "To find the project tracking dashboard in AttendanceBot, go to the dashboard, navigate to time tracking, and select project tracking. This dashboard offers tools for analyzing time usage with visualizations that can be toggled between daily, weekly, and monthly views.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "can we connect the team calendar to google calendar?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to integrate calendars", "How to integrate your calendar with AttendanceBot for Slack", "How to use and configure the AttendanceBot vacation calendar"], "generated_answer": "Yes, you can connect your team calendar to Google Calendar. Here's how:\n\n1. Type \"cal\" as a direct message (DM) in Slack.\n2. Choose Google Calendar and click on \"Enable\" to sync.\n3. Alternatively, you can get a public calendar link by clicking \"Get Link.\"\n4. In Google Calendar, click the down arrow next to \u201cOther calendars\u201d and select \u201cAdd by URL.\u201d\n5. Paste the URL and click \u201cAdd calendar.\u201d\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000116056", "reference_answer": "Yes, you can connect your team calendar to Google Calendar. Here are the steps: 1. Type 'cal' as a direct message (DM) in Slack. 2. Choose Google Calendar and click on 'Enable' to sync. 3. Alternatively, get a public calendar link by clicking 'Get Link.' 4. In Google Calendar, click the down arrow next to 'Other calendars' and select 'Add by URL.' 5. Paste the URL and click 'Add calendar.' For more details, visit the AttendanceBot support page.", "quality_score": 4.4, "bucket": "well_answered"}
