{"query": "how do i invite the users?", "retrieved_contexts": ["Adding New Users to Hangouts/Google Chat", "How do I invite new users on my team to start using AttendanceBot?", "How do I add admin users?"], "generated_answer": "To invite new users to start using AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure the new users are members of your Slack or Microsoft Teams workspace.\n2. Option 1: Automatically activate new users.\n   - Go to your main 'settings' dashboard.\n   - Scroll down and toggle on \"Activate new users\".\n   - Optionally, toggle on \"Auto invite new users\" to send a welcome message.\n3. Option 2: Manually activate new users.\n   - Open the 'settings' dashboard and go to People --> Personnel tab.\n   - Ensure \"Show active personnel only\" is turned off.\n   - Search for the new user profile and toggle their status to \"Active\".\n   - Optionally, set up additional fields like manager, office, etc.\n   - Send a welcome message via the Invite page.\n\nFor further assistance, contact support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115576", "reference_answer": "To invite new users to AttendanceBot, ensure they are members of your Slack or Microsoft Teams workspace. You can either automatically activate them by toggling on 'Activate new users' in the settings dashboard or manually activate them by searching for their profile in the Personnel tab and changing their status to 'Active'. Optionally, send a welcome message.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": " please give me the report of the each employees working hours in each project ( how much they worked in each projects from jan 2025 to dec 2025 )", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I get the summary or report of my time in office?", "How to track time spent on a project, task, or client", "What are my reporting options and what do the different reports do?"], "generated_answer": "To generate a report of each employee's working hours on each project from January 2025 to December 2025, follow these steps:\n\n1. Use the command \"Report\" in Slack.\n2. Select the report type as Timesheet Report or Timesheet Summary Report.\n3. Specify the date range from January 2025 to December 2025.\n4. Confirm your selection to download the CSV report.\n\nIf you need a detailed breakdown by project, ensure your projects are configured correctly. For further assistance, you may need to contact support.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118258", "reference_answer": "To generate a report of each employee's working hours on each project from January 2025 to December 2025, use the Timesheet Report feature in AttendanceBot. Specify the date range and ensure your projects are configured correctly. For detailed instructions, refer to the documentation.", "quality_score": 4.4, "bucket": "well_answered"}
