{"query": "Hi, I thought we set up our leave balances to reset each year but people are getting errors when they apply for leaves they're taking in 2026. Do we need to initiate something else to make that happen? ", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to apply for leave next year or any future year", "How to setup accrual rules and leave quotas based on company policy", "How to setup accrual rules and leave quotas based on company policy"], "generated_answer": "To ensure leave balances reset each year, you need to configure the rollover settings properly. Here's how you can do it:\n\n1. Go to the settings where you configure accrual rules.\n2. Set the \"Rollover in days\" to 0 if you want a \"use it or lose it\" policy, meaning all leave expires each year.\n3. Ensure that the \"Cap on annual leave count\" is set to 365 if rollover is 0.\n4. Check if the accrual period is set to \"Calendar year\" to ensure it resets on January 1st each year.\n\nIf these settings are correct and you're still facing issues, consider opening a support ticket for further assistance.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000051255", "reference_answer": "To ensure leave balances reset each year, configure the rollover settings: set 'Rollover in days' to 0 for a 'use it or lose it' policy, ensure 'Cap on annual leave count' is 365, and check that the accrual period is 'Calendar year'. If issues persist, open a support ticket.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
