{"query": "I want to know the leave each team member took in this year", "retrieved_contexts": ["Checking Your Leave Balance", "How to enable and understand leave privacy and hidden leave types", "How do I delete a leave applied by a member of my team?"], "generated_answer": "To view the leave each team member took this year, you can use the AttendanceBot features to access their leave balances. As a manager, you can check the leave balances for your team members by following these steps:\n\n1. Type `balance @username` to the AttendanceBot, replacing `@username` with the specific team member's username.\n2. This will display the leave balance for that user, including details of leaves taken.\n\nIf you need further details or a summary, you might need to access additional reports or settings within the AttendanceBot system.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000116112", "reference_answer": "To view the leave each team member took this year, you can use the AttendanceBot features to access their leave balances. As a manager, type `balance @username` to check the leave balance for each team member.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how to configure leave for members?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to setup accrual rules and leave quotas based on company policy", "How to setup accrual rules and leave quotas based on company policy", "How to enable and understand leave privacy and hidden leave types"], "generated_answer": "To configure leave for members in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Navigate to the leave type tab in your settings dashboard by typing 'settings' and then going to Vacation Management -> Leaves -> Leave Types and Quotas.\n2. Here, you can view and edit all active and inactive leave types. Enable or disable any leave type by toggling its status.\n3. To create a custom leave type, click \"Create New\", title the leave, and assign synonyms from the keywords section.\n4. For specific leave accrual rules, go to the \"accrual settings\" tab in the edit screen. Decide between a universal policy or one for specific employee sets.\n5. Adjust settings such as approval requirements and minimum request length as needed.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000051255", "reference_answer": "To configure leave for members in AttendanceBot, follow these steps: 1. Navigate to the leave type tab in your settings dashboard. 2. Go to Vacation Management -> Leaves -> Leave Types and Quotas. 3. View and edit active and inactive leave types. 4. Enable or disable leave types by toggling their status. 5. Create a custom leave type if needed and set accrual rules. 6. Adjust approval requirements and request lengths as necessary.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
