{"query": "how to invite team members", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I invite new users on my team to start using AttendanceBot?", "How to add a team holiday", "Installing AttendanceBot in Google Chat & Introducing New Users"], "generated_answer": "To invite new team members to use AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure the new users are already members of your Slack workspace.\n2. Option 1: Automatically activate new users.\n   - Go to the 'settings' dashboard.\n   - Scroll down and toggle on \"Activate new users\".\n   - Optionally, toggle on \"Auto invite new users\" for a welcome message.\n\n3. Option 2: Manually activate new users.\n   - Open 'settings' and go to People > Personnel tab.\n   - Ensure \"Show active personnel only\" is off.\n   - Search for the new user and toggle their status to \"Active\".\n   - Optionally, set up additional fields by clicking their name.\n   - Trigger a welcome message by going to People > Invite and sending a message.\n\nIf you encounter issues, contact support at support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com or type \"dialm\" to open a support ticket.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115576", "reference_answer": "To invite new team members to use AttendanceBot, ensure they are members of your Slack workspace. You can either automatically activate them through the settings dashboard or manually activate them by searching for their name in the personnel tab. For more details, visit the AttendanceBot support page.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how do i add holidays", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to add a team holiday", "How to set up offices and regional holiday calendars", "How to use and configure the AttendanceBot vacation calendar"], "generated_answer": "To add holidays for your team, follow these steps:\n\n1. Type \"settings\" as a direct message in Slack.\n2. Go to Vacation Management.\n3. Click on Calendar.\n4. Navigate to the Holidays tab to add company holidays.\n\nFor regional holidays:\n\n1. Type \"settings\" and go to the settings panel.\n2. Click on the Offices section in the sidebar.\n3. Use \"Create new\" to set up multiple offices.\n4. Assign offices to employees via the People option in the sidebar.\n5. Create holidays for each office.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118248", "reference_answer": "To add holidays for your team, type 'settings' in Slack, go to Vacation Management, then Calendar, and select the Holidays tab to add company holidays. For regional holidays, create offices and assign them to employees before adding holidays for each office.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how do i add holidays to just my timesheet", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to add a team holiday", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to approve the timesheets of my reportees"], "generated_answer": "To add holidays for your team, you need to use the settings dashboard. Here\u2019s how:\n\n1. Type \"settings\" as a direct message in Slack.\n2. Navigate to Vacation Management --> Calendar --> Holidays tab.\n\nNote: This process is for adding company-wide holidays. If you want to apply for a personal holiday, type \"apply\" to AttendanceBot.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118248", "reference_answer": "To add holidays to just your timesheet, you can apply for a personal holiday by typing 'apply' to AttendanceBot. For company-wide holidays, use the settings dashboard: Type 'settings' in Slack, then go to Vacation Management --> Calendar --> Holidays tab.", "quality_score": 3.8, "bucket": "partial"}
{"query": "Does AttendanceBot also keep track of vacation?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to use and configure the AttendanceBot vacation calendar", "How to use and configure the AttendanceBot vacation calendar", "AttendanceBot Plans and Features"], "generated_answer": "Yes, AttendanceBot keeps track of vacations using a vacation calendar. This calendar provides a visual representation of team schedules, making it easy to understand and coordinate around each other's availability. You can open the vacation calendar by selecting \"Data & integrations\" from the \"Menu\" and clicking on \"Calendar\" to receive a link to your team calendar. The calendar allows you to browse, filter by office or department, and configure permissions for viewing. Admins can also create company holidays, events, and add blackout dates.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000138905", "reference_answer": "Yes, AttendanceBot keeps track of vacations using a vacation calendar, which allows you to request and approve leave, inform your team, and configure leave policies. You can access it via 'Data & integrations' in the menu.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
