{"query": "we have a stuff member that worked for us few years ago and rejoined the company, we tried to reactivate her attendancebot account but it doesn't sync with it", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I find my missing employee profile on the dashboard? (Slack)", "I'm getting an error message \"You are viewing the archives of a deactivated account\" while accessing AttendanceBot in Slack. What should I do?", "How to deactivate a user in AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "To reactivate an employee's AttendanceBot account, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the \"Settings\" panel in AttendanceBot.\n2. Navigate to People --> Personnel.\n3. Toggle off \"Show active personnel only\" to see all profiles.\n4. If you find the employee's profile, check \"active\" on the right. \n5. If the profile is not visible, click the top teal \"RE-SYNC\" button.\n6. Wait 1-4 hours and retry the process.\n\nIf the issue persists, consider opening a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131680", "reference_answer": "To reactivate an employee's AttendanceBot account, go to Settings > People > Personnel, toggle off 'Show active personnel only', check the employee's profile, and ensure it's marked as active. If not visible, click 'RE-SYNC' and wait 1-4 hours. If issues persist, open a support ticket.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
