{"query": "why do I have a total of 6:57 weekly overtime hrs when i did not hit 40 hrs last week? is there a way to schedule holiday hours so my totals match my physical timecard?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?", "How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?", "What are my reporting options and what do the different reports do?"], "generated_answer": "The discrepancy in your weekly overtime hours could be due to how your overtime rules are configured. AttendanceBot allows for various overtime thresholds such as daily, daily double, consecutive daily, or weekly. If your overtime is set to calculate based on daily thresholds, you might accumulate overtime even if you don't hit 40 hours in a week.\n\nTo align your totals with your physical timecard, you can configure holiday hours as part of your regular or overtime hours. Here's how you can manage it:\n\n1. Go to the overtime dashboard.\n2. Check your current overtime configuration to ensure it matches your expectations (e.g., daily vs. weekly).\n3. For holiday hours, ensure they are included in your regular hours or adjust your overtime rules to account for them.\n\nIf further customization is needed, consider setting individual rules in employee profiles.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000106516", "reference_answer": "Your weekly overtime hours may be calculated based on daily thresholds, which can lead to overtime even if you don't reach 40 hours. To align your totals with your physical timecard, check your overtime configuration and ensure holiday hours are included correctly. You can adjust these settings in the overtime dashboard.", "quality_score": 4.6, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "Edit timesheet", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to approve the timesheets of my reportees", "How to approve the timesheets of my reportees"], "generated_answer": "To edit your timesheet in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. From the \"Menu\", select \"Timesheet actions\" and click \u201cEdit\u201d to access your timesheet editor.\n2. Choose your date range using the \u201cDate Range\u201d dropdown. You can select options like \u201cthis week\u201d or \u201cthis month\u201d or specify a custom range.\n3. After submitting your selection, each day will be shown as a tile. Click \"expand\" on any day to view or edit specific punches.\n4. To edit a punch, click the pencil icon, update the details, and hit \"save\". To delete a punch, click the trashcan icon. To add a new entry, click the green \u201cadd punches\u201d button.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118260", "reference_answer": "To edit your timesheet in AttendanceBot, go to 'Timesheet actions' in the Menu, select 'Edit', choose your date range, expand the days to view punches, and use the pencil icon to edit or the trashcan icon to delete. You can also add new entries with the 'add punches' button.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
