{"query": "I want to edit timecard", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to approve the timesheets of my reportees"], "generated_answer": "To edit your timecard in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. From the \"Menu,\" select \"Timesheet actions\" and click on \u201cEdit\u201d to access your timesheet editor on the dashboard.\n2. Choose your desired date range using the \u201cDate Range\u201d dropdown.\n3. If you have reportees, you can select another employee to view and edit their timesheet.\n4. Expand any day to view or edit specific punches.\n5. To change a punch time, click the pencil icon, update the details, and hit \"save.\"\n6. To delete a punch, click the trashcan icon and confirm the deletion.\n7. To add a new punch, click the green \u201cadd punches\u201d button, fill in the details, and hit \u201csave.\u201d\n\nNote: You can only edit punches if your admin has enabled the \"Allow self editing of punches\" setting.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118260", "reference_answer": "To edit your timecard in AttendanceBot, go to the dashboard, select 'Timesheet actions,' and click 'Edit.' Choose the date range, expand the day to edit punches, and use the pencil icon to update or the trashcan icon to delete. Ensure your admin allows self-editing of punches.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how do i edit one of my teammembers time", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?"], "generated_answer": "To edit a team member's timesheet in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the AttendanceBot dashboard and navigate to \"Time Tracking\" and then \"Edit Timesheet.\"\n2. Select the date range and the employee from the dropdown menu.\n3. Click \"Expand\" for the specific date you want to edit.\n4. Click on the pencil icon next to the punch you want to edit.\n5. Update the punch details as needed and hit \"Save.\"\n\nThis will update the timesheet with the changes, and a note with the edit details will be recorded.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118266", "reference_answer": "To edit a team member's timesheet in AttendanceBot, go to the dashboard, navigate to 'Time Tracking' > 'Edit Timesheet', select the employee and date range, expand the date, click the pencil icon next to the punch, update the details, and hit 'Save'.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
