{"query": "PTO balances for my staff are not listed. When I click into each record it says there is unlimited PTO, which is not the case. How do I fix the PTO balances?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?", "Checking Your Leave Balance", "How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?"], "generated_answer": "To fix the PTO balances, you need to ensure that accruals are set for the leave types. Here's how you can do it:\n\n1. Go to the leave type configuration settings in AttendanceBot.\n2. Verify that the accruals for each leave type, including PTO, are correctly set.\n3. If accruals are not set, configure them to reflect the correct leave balances.\n4. Once configured, the leave balances should update and no longer show as unlimited.\n\nIf the issue persists, consider checking the employee profiles to ensure they are correctly associated with the configured leave types.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000116112", "reference_answer": "To fix the PTO balances, ensure that accruals are set for the leave types in AttendanceBot. Go to the leave type configuration settings, verify the accruals for each leave type, and configure them if necessary. Check employee profiles to ensure correct association with leave types. For more details, refer to the article on checking your leave balance: https://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000116112.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "How do I edit people", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How do I assign managers for my employees?"], "generated_answer": "To edit people in AttendanceBot, you can assign managers using the following methods:\n\n1. **Via the settings panel:**\n   - Go to People > Personnel on your dashboard.\n   - Search for the employee and open their profile.\n   - Find the manager field and select a name from the dropdown menu.\n   - Hit save.\n\n2. **Via Slack or Teams:**\n   - Message AttendanceBot with \"Change manager @username\" and select the new manager from the dropdown menu.\n\n3. **Via bulk upload:**\n   - Go to People > Imported Team Data on your dashboard.\n   - Download the current personnel data.\n   - Edit the \"manager email\" field and save the document.\n   - Upload the updated file.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000132179", "reference_answer": "To edit people in AttendanceBot, you can assign managers via the settings panel, Slack or Teams, or through bulk upload. For detailed steps, visit the support portal: https://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000132179.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
