{"query": "I'm unable to generate a report for contractors in order to pay them.", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do you pass hours for contractors from AttendanceBot to Gusto?", "How to generate a payroll report in Slack with AttendanceBot", "How can I generate reports?"], "generated_answer": "To generate a report for contractors to pay them, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the AttendanceBot dashboard and navigate to Settings -> Gusto -> Sync 1099 Employees tab.\n2. Ensure contractors are matched between AttendanceBot and Gusto by their email address. Match any unmatched contractors under \u201cUnmatched Contractors.\u201d\n3. Select the pay period for which you want to generate their hours and click \u201cGenerate report.\u201d\n4. Upload the generated hours CSV to contractor payroll on Gusto to process their payroll.\n\nIf you encounter any issues, consider opening a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000119375", "reference_answer": "To generate a report for contractors to pay them, go to the AttendanceBot dashboard, navigate to Settings -> Gusto -> Sync 1099 Employees tab, match contractors by email, select the pay period, and click 'Generate report.' Upload the CSV to Gusto for payroll processing. If issues arise, open a support ticket.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "Can I move calendar details in behalf of the team if im manager?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to configure calendar permissions", "How to use and configure the AttendanceBot vacation calendar", "How to add a team holiday"], "generated_answer": "I don't have enough information to determine if a manager can move calendar details on behalf of the team. You may want to open a support ticket for further assistance. Please type 'ticket' to proceed.", "reference_answer": "As a manager, you may have the ability to move calendar details on behalf of your team, but this depends on the specific permissions set in your AttendanceBot configuration. I recommend checking the calendar permissions article for more details: https://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000124502. If you need further assistance, please open a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.", "quality_score": 4.0, "bucket": "partial"}
{"query": "Also can I have calendar attached to google calendar?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to integrate your calendar with AttendanceBot for Slack", "How to integrate calendars", "How to integrate your calendar with AttendanceBot for Slack"], "generated_answer": "Yes, you can integrate AttendanceBot with Google Calendar. Follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to your Google Calendar.\n2. Click the down arrow next to \u201cOther calendars\u201d and select \u201cAdd by URL\u201d.\n3. Paste the URL provided by AttendanceBot and click \u201cAdd calendar\u201d.\n\nThis will subscribe your Google Calendar to the AttendanceBot calendar, allowing you to view your team's leave and other events.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000017361", "reference_answer": "Yes, you can integrate AttendanceBot with Google Calendar by adding the provided URL to your Google Calendar under 'Add by URL'.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how to add a leave", "retrieved_contexts": ["What are the different kinds of leaves?", "How do I delete a leave applied by a member of my team?", "How to setup accrual rules and leave quotas based on company policy"], "generated_answer": "To add a new leave type in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Navigate to the leave type tab in your settings dashboard by typing \"settings\" and then go to Vacation Management --> Leaves --> Leave Types and Quotas.\n2. Click on \"Create New\" to add a new leave type.\n3. Title the leave and assign synonyms associated with the leave from the keywords section. These synonyms can be used while applying for leave.\n4. Save your changes.\n\nFor more detailed instructions, refer to the documentation.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000051255", "reference_answer": "To add a leave in AttendanceBot, follow these steps: 1) Message 'menu' to AttendanceBot to open the options menu navigator. 2) Click the \u2018Apply\u2019 button to open a request form popup. 3) Complete your request by choosing the leave type, duration, and date, and hit 'Submit.' For more details, refer to the documentation.", "quality_score": 3.8, "bucket": "partial"}
