{"query": "Me gustar\u00eda saber si es posible exportar el hist\u00f3rico de todos los timesheets. Tambi\u00e9n me gustar\u00eda entender por qu\u00e9 no puedo hacer approval de timesheets antiguos que no hab\u00eda aprobado. Tengo un gap de junio a agosto en el cual no tengo timesheets para aprobar. ", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to approve the timesheets of my reportees", "How to approve the timesheets of my reportees", "How to approve the timesheets of my reportees"], "generated_answer": "Please chat in English only. \n\nTo export the historical timesheets, once approved, the downloadable timesheet report will display relevant approval data. If you need to unapprove or retract an approval, use the \u201capproval log\u201d tab to view historical approved timesheets. \n\nRegarding the gap from June to August, if you cannot approve timesheets from that period, it might be due to system settings or restrictions. I recommend opening a support ticket for further assistance.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000138877", "reference_answer": "Yes, you can export historical timesheets once they are approved. For timesheets from June to August, if you cannot approve them, it may be due to system restrictions. Please open a support ticket for further assistance.", "quality_score": 4.0, "bucket": "partial"}
{"query": "can one employee have two shifts", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to create and manage open shifts and shift templates", "How to view my shifts and the shifts of my employees", "How to swap or reassign shifts"], "generated_answer": "Yes, an employee can have multiple shifts. You can assign different shifts to an employee by creating open shifts and assigning them as needed. If you need to manage or view shifts, you can do so from the Shift Management page or by using the shift calendar to see all assigned shifts. \n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000112956", "reference_answer": "Yes, an employee can have multiple shifts in AttendanceBot. You can manage this through the Shift Management page or the shift calendar.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "i want one employee to have a morning and afternoon shift", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to create and manage open shifts and shift templates", "How to view my shifts and the shifts of my employees", "How to create open shifts for specific departments or roles"], "generated_answer": "To assign both a morning and an afternoon shift to an employee, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the Shift Management page on your dashboard.\n2. Click on the \u201cCreate Shift\u201d button.\n3. Create two separate shifts: one for the morning and one for the afternoon.\n4. For each shift, enter the shift name, timings, and any necessary attributes.\n5. Once the shifts are created, click on \u201cAssign\u201d for each shift and select the employee you want to assign them to.\n\nAttendanceBot will notify the employee about the assigned shifts.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000112956", "reference_answer": "To assign both a morning and an afternoon shift to an employee in AttendanceBot, follow these steps: 1. Go to the Shift Management page on your dashboard. 2. Click on the 'Create Shift' button. 3. Create two separate shifts: one for the morning and one for the afternoon. 4. For each shift, enter the shift name, timings, and any necessary attributes. 5. Once the shifts are created, click on 'Assign' for each shift and select the employee you want to assign them to. AttendanceBot will notify the employee about the assigned shifts.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how can i can time sheets", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to approve the timesheets of my reportees", "How to approve the timesheets of my reportees", "How do I get the summary or report of my time in office?"], "generated_answer": "To approve timesheets for your reportees, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open the dashboard by typing \"settings\" as a DM to the app.\n2. Navigate to the Time tracking -> Timesheet Approvals section.\n3. The approval page has two tabs: \"Approvals\" for pending timesheets and \"Approval log\" for approved ones.\n4. Use the \u201cselect all\u201d button to approve all timesheets or the \u201capprove employee\u201d button for specific employees.\n5. To review individual timesheets, click \u201cExpand\u201d on the employee tile.\n6. You can view detailed summaries and approve at the timesheet level.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000134394", "reference_answer": "To generate timesheets using AttendanceBot, clock in and out using the app in Slack or Microsoft Teams. Ensure your work hours are tracked accurately by setting up projects or tasks if needed. Review your time in the dashboard under Time tracking.", "quality_score": 3.6, "bucket": "partial"}
{"query": "Where do I find \"data and integrations\"", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to integrate calendars", "How to download team vacation data and reporting", "Time/Task tracking"], "generated_answer": "To find \"Data & Integrations\" in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open the \"Menu\" in AttendanceBot.\n2. Select \"Data & Integrations.\"\n3. From there, you can click on \"Reports\" to access various reporting options.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000063984", "reference_answer": "To find 'Data & Integrations' in AttendanceBot, open the 'Menu' and select 'Data & Integrations.' You can then access various reporting options.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
