{"query": "how can someone add their availability on the team calendar?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to use and configure the AttendanceBot vacation calendar", "How to integrate calendars", "How to add a team holiday"], "generated_answer": "To add your availability on the team calendar, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open the vacation calendar by selecting \"Data & integrations\" from the \"Menu\" and clicking on \u201cCalendar\u201d to receive a link to your team calendar.\n2. Navigate to the specific day you want to update by cycling through the months at the top left.\n3. Click on the specific day to pop out a detailed view where you can update your available/unavailable status.\n4. Configure the type of leave or availability (e.g., WFH, PTO) and add any comments if necessary.\n\nFor more detailed configuration options, refer to the calendar permissions settings.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000138905", "reference_answer": "To add your availability on the team calendar, open the vacation calendar from the 'Menu', navigate to the desired day, click to update your status, and configure your availability type. For more details, check the calendar permissions settings.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "How to request time off", "retrieved_contexts": ["Taking time off", "How to request hourly or half day leave", "How to apply for time off for half a day or few hours?"], "generated_answer": "To request time off using AttendanceBot in Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Type a command with the leave type name, followed by the date. For example, \"Vacation 05/04 to 05/07\" for a 4-day leave.\n2. Alternatively, use a conversational approach, such as \"WFH tomorrow\" or \"Sick\" for a sick day today.\n3. Specify the start and end dates in various formats like \"MM-DD\", \"today\", \"tomorrow\", or \"next week\".\n4. AttendanceBot will verify the actual date with you before recording your leave request.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000116053", "reference_answer": "To request time off using AttendanceBot in Slack, you can either type a command with the leave type and dates (e.g., 'Vacation 05/04 to 05/07') or use conversational phrases like 'WFH tomorrow' or 'Sick'. AttendanceBot will confirm the dates before finalizing your request.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "hi, i am noticing that the hours calculated on top does not match my punch in hours. How can this be fixed? ", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?"], "generated_answer": "To fix discrepancies in your punch hours, you can edit your timesheet:\n\n1. Go to the \"Menu\" and select \"Timesheet actions.\"\n2. Click on \u201cEdit\u201d to access your timesheet editor on the dashboard.\n3. Adjust the date range if needed using the \u201cDate Range\u201d dropdown.\n4. Expand the specific day to view the punch history.\n5. Click the pencil icon next to the punch you want to edit, update the details, and hit \"save.\"\n6. If necessary, add missing punches using the \u201cadd punches\u201d button.\n\nEnsure your admin has enabled \"Allow self editing of punches\" in timesheet settings.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118260", "reference_answer": "To fix discrepancies in your punch hours, you can edit your timesheet by going to 'Menu' > 'Timesheet actions' > 'Edit'. Adjust the date range if needed, expand the specific day to view punch history, and edit or add punches as necessary. Ensure your admin has enabled 'Allow self editing of punches' in timesheet settings.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
