{"query": "hi, i am noticing that the hours calculated on top does not match my punch in hours. How can this be fixed? ", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?"], "generated_answer": "To fix discrepancies in your punch in hours, you can edit your timesheet in AttendanceBot. Here's how:\n\n1. From the \"Menu,\" select \"Timesheet actions\" and click on \u201cEdit\u201d to access your timesheet editor.\n2. Adjust the date range if needed by clicking on the blue \u201cDate Range\u201d dropdown.\n3. Click \"expand\" on any day to view the minute-by-minute punch history.\n4. To edit a punch, click the pencil icon in the punch row, update the details, and hit \"save.\"\n5. To delete a punch, click the trashcan icon and confirm the deletion.\n6. To add a new entry, click the green \u201cadd punches\u201d button, fill in the details, and save.\n\nEnsure that \"Allow self editing of punches\" is enabled by your admin to make these changes.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118260", "reference_answer": "To fix discrepancies in your punch in hours, edit your timesheet in AttendanceBot by accessing the timesheet editor, adjusting the date range, and editing or adding punches as needed. Ensure 'Allow self editing of punches' is enabled by your admin.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
