{"query": "we have someone in Teams but they're not showing up on attendance bot ", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I find my missing employee profile on the dashboard? (Slack)", "How do I invite new users on my team to start using AttendanceBot?", "How to inactivate users?"], "generated_answer": "If someone is in your Teams workspace but not showing up in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to your AttendanceBot 'Settings' dashboard.\n2. Navigate to People --> Personnel.\n3. Ensure the \"Show active personnel only\" toggle is turned off.\n4. Search for the user's profile. If found, toggle their status to \"Active.\"\n5. If you can't find their profile, click the top teal \"RE-SYNC\" button and wait 1-4 hours before retrying or contacting support.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131680", "reference_answer": "If someone is in your Teams workspace but not showing up in AttendanceBot, ensure they are active in the AttendanceBot settings. Check the personnel list, toggle their status to active if necessary, and re-sync if they are not found.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "i am unable to remove myself as admin", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to change account admin", "I'm getting an error message \"You are viewing the archives of a deactivated account\" while accessing AttendanceBot in Slack. What should I do?", "How do I uninstall AttendanceBot from Google Chat ?"], "generated_answer": "To remove yourself as an admin, you can add a new secondary admin through the settings dashboard. Here\u2019s how:\n\n1. Type \"Settings\" as a direct message to the AttendanceBot app in Slack.\n2. Click on the URL prompted to open the settings dashboard.\n3. Scroll to the basic settings page, then go to \"Other Settings\" and select \"Administrator.\"\n4. Search for the person you want to add as a secondary admin and select their name from the dropdown menu.\n\nIf you need to change the primary admin, please raise a support ticket by typing \"Dialm\" as a message to the app or reach out through live chat support.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131567", "reference_answer": "To remove yourself as an admin, add a new secondary admin through the settings dashboard. Type 'Settings' to the AttendanceBot app in Slack, open the settings dashboard, go to 'Other Settings' > 'Administrator', and select a new admin. For primary admin changes, type 'Dialm' for support.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "I didn't saw dashboard ", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I find my missing employee profile on the dashboard? (Slack)", "How to view employee status on a dashboard or in Slack", "How to approve the timesheets of my reportees"], "generated_answer": "If you are unable to see the dashboard, please ensure you are following these steps:\n\n1. Type \"settings\" as a direct message to AttendanceBot in Slack.\n2. This should open the dashboard for you.\n\nIf you still cannot access the dashboard, there may be an issue with your permissions or setup. In that case, I suggest opening a support ticket by typing 'ticket'. \n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000134394", "reference_answer": "If you are unable to see the dashboard, please ensure you are following these steps: 1. Type 'settings' as a direct message to AttendanceBot in Slack. 2. This should open the dashboard for you. If you still cannot access the dashboard, there may be an issue with your permissions or setup. In that case, I suggest opening a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how can someone request a half day of vacation time?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to request hourly or half day leave", "How to apply for time off for half a day or few hours?", "Taking time off"], "generated_answer": "To request a half day of vacation time, follow these steps:\n\n1. Message \"menu\" to AttendanceBot to open the options menu.\n2. Select \u2018Apply\u2019 to open a request form.\n3. Choose the leave type (e.g., vacation) and under \u201cLeave Duration,\u201d select \u201cfirst half\u201d or \u201csecond half.\u201d\n\nAlternatively, you can type a command directly, such as \"second half leave\" followed by the date, and hit \"confirm.\"\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000116054", "reference_answer": "To request a half day of vacation time, message 'menu' to AttendanceBot, select 'Apply', choose the leave type, and under 'Leave Duration', select 'first half' or 'second half'. You can also type 'second half leave' followed by the date and hit 'confirm.'", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how to delete approved leave days", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to change or edit an existing approved leave", "How to delete approved leave for a reportee or employee", "How do I delete a leave applied by a member of my team?"], "generated_answer": "To delete approved leave days for a reportee or employee, follow these steps:\n\n1. Type the command \"delete @username\" in Slack, where \"@username\" is the Slack username of the team member.\n2. You'll see a list of approved leaves for that user in reverse chronological order.\n3. Click the Delete button below the leave you wish to cancel.\n4. You'll receive a Slack confirmation, and the reportee will be notified of the cancellation.\n\nIf you need to delete your own leave, follow the appropriate article for guidance.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000093812", "reference_answer": "To delete approved leave days for a reportee or employee, type 'delete @username' in Slack. A list of approved leaves will appear. Click the Delete button for the leave you wish to cancel. You'll receive a confirmation, and the reportee will be notified.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
