{"query": "what happens when my trial ends", "retrieved_contexts": ["How long is my AttendanceBot trial?", "Billing - how does adding or removing users affect my billing?", "Billing - how does adding or removing users affect my billing?"], "generated_answer": "When your AttendanceBot trial ends, you will not be automatically charged. The admin of the account will receive a direct message from the app as you approach the end of the trial. If your team has more than 5 users, you will need to subscribe to continue using the app. For teams with 5 users or less, the app remains free. You can view pricing plans here: https://www.attendancebot.com/pricing/\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115577", "reference_answer": "When your AttendanceBot trial ends, the admin will receive a DM from the app. If your team has more than 5 users, you will need to subscribe to continue using the app. For teams with 5 users or less, the app remains free. You will not be auto-charged after the trial period.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how to add a PTO for an agent", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?", "How to configure and use time-off-in-lieu (TOIL) (Slack)", "How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?"], "generated_answer": "To add a PTO (Paid Time Off) for an agent in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open your Slack workspace and navigate to the AttendanceBot app.\n2. Type \"apply\" in the direct message with AttendanceBot.\n3. Select the leave type as \"PTO\" from the options provided.\n4. Enter the duration for which you want to apply the PTO.\n5. Submit the request.\n\nIf you need further assistance, please open a support ticket by typing 'ticket'. \n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000112422", "reference_answer": "To add a PTO (Paid Time Off) for an agent in AttendanceBot, open your Slack workspace, navigate to the AttendanceBot app, type 'apply', select 'PTO', enter the duration, and submit the request. For more help, type 'ticket' or visit the support portal.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "cancel a request in attendance bot", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to cancel / retract / rescind / delete a leave request", "How to deactivate a user in AttendanceBot", "How to inactivate users?"], "generated_answer": "To cancel your own leave request in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open the \"Menu\" and select \"Time off & hybrid work\".\n2. You will see an option labeled \u201cDelete\u201d for your requested leave.\n3. This will display all approved or pending upcoming leaves.\n4. Click the \u201cdelete\u201d button below the leave details to cancel it.\n\nThis action will immediately notify both you and your manager. Note that if you want to delete a past leave, you need to ask your manager or an admin.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000121203", "reference_answer": "To cancel your own leave request in AttendanceBot, open the 'Menu', select 'Time off & hybrid work', find the 'Delete' option for your requested leave, and click the 'delete' button below the leave details. This will notify you and your manager. For past leaves, contact your manager or admin.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "How do I inform my manager that I am attending a full day webinar?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How can I apply for leave in Slack with AttendanceBot", "How do I add or change my approving manager?", "How to manage hybrid work schedules (WFO/WFH days) in Slack using AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "To inform your manager about attending a full-day webinar using AttendanceBot, you can apply for leave or update your work schedule accordingly. Here's how you can do it:\n\n1. Message \"menu\" to AttendanceBot to open the options menu navigator.\n2. Click the \u2018Apply\u2019 button to open a request form popup.\n3. Choose the appropriate leave type (e.g., \"Webinar\") and set the duration and date.\n4. Add a comment to specify that you are attending a full-day webinar, if necessary.\n5. Submit the request.\n\nIf the request type requires approval, it will be routed to your manager, and you will be notified once it's approved or rejected.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131679", "reference_answer": "To inform your manager about attending a full-day webinar using AttendanceBot, you can apply for leave or update your work schedule. Message 'menu' to AttendanceBot, click 'Apply', choose 'Webinar' as the leave type, set the date, and submit the request. If approval is needed, it will be routed to your manager.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
