{"query": "how to select choose working hours", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?", "How to view and claim open shifts", "How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?"], "generated_answer": "To select and configure working hours in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Visit the custom field section of your personnel dashboard.\n2. Browse the relevant fields for \"work hours.\"\n3. Activate the desired work hour period: \"Daily Work Hours,\" \"Weekly Work Hours,\" \"Biweekly Work Hours,\" or \"Monthly Work Hours.\"\n4. For each employee, set threshold hours by inputting a numerical value into the appropriate work hour field in their profile.\n5. Alternatively, use the import/export page to set thresholds in bulk.\n\nNote: Each employee can only have one active work hour period at a time.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000106516", "reference_answer": "To select and configure working hours in AttendanceBot, visit the custom field section of your personnel dashboard, activate the desired work hour period, and set threshold hours for each employee. You can also use the import/export page for bulk settings.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
