{"query": "how to add people?", "retrieved_contexts": ["Adding New Users to Hangouts/Google Chat", "How do I add admin users?", "How do I invite new users on my team to start using AttendanceBot?"], "generated_answer": "To add new users to AttendanceBot in Slack or Microsoft Teams, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure the new users are members of your Slack or Teams workspace.\n2. Option 1: Automatically activate new users.\n   - Go to your main 'settings' dashboard.\n   - Scroll down and toggle on \"Activate new users\".\n   - Optionally, toggle on \"Auto invite new users\" for a welcome message.\n3. Option 2: Manually activate new users.\n   - Open the 'settings' dashboard and go to People > Personnel tab.\n   - Ensure \"Show active personnel only\" is turned off.\n   - Search for the new user and toggle their status to \"Active\".\n   - Optionally, set up additional fields by clicking their name.\n   - Send a welcome message via People > Invite.\n\nFor more details, visit the link below.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115576", "reference_answer": "To add new users to AttendanceBot in Slack or Microsoft Teams, ensure they are members of your workspace. You can activate them automatically in the settings or manually by searching for them in the personnel tab and toggling their status to 'Active'. For more details, visit the support portal.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
