{"query": "We test the app in slack and have decided not to continue on to the paid version.  How do i cancel the free trial?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How long is my AttendanceBot trial?", "How to uninstall AttendanceBot from Slack", "I'm getting an error message \"You are viewing the archives of a deactivated account\" while accessing AttendanceBot in Slack. What should I do?"], "generated_answer": "To cancel the free trial of AttendanceBot in Slack, you need to uninstall the app. Follow these steps:\n\n1. Select the AttendanceBot app on Slack and click on the \u201cAbout\" tab.\n2. Select the \"Configuration\" tab to be redirected to the Slack app directory page.\n3. Scroll down to the Remove Application section and click on the Remove App button to remove it from your workspace.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000121227", "reference_answer": "To cancel the free trial of AttendanceBot in Slack, uninstall the app by going to the AttendanceBot app, clicking on the 'About' tab, selecting 'Configuration', and then clicking 'Remove App' in the Slack app directory.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "invite someone how to", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I invite new users on my team to start using AttendanceBot?", "Adding New Users to Hangouts/Google Chat", "How do I install AttendanceBot in Slack?"], "generated_answer": "To invite someone to use AttendanceBot in Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure the person is already a member of your Slack workspace.\n2. Go to your main 'settings' dashboard in AttendanceBot.\n3. Option 1: To automatically activate new users, toggle on \"Activate new users\" in the settings. Optionally, toggle on \"Auto invite new users\" to send a welcome message.\n4. Option 2: To manually activate users, go to the personnel tab, ensure \"Show active personnel only\" is off, find the user, and toggle their status to \"Active\".\n5. Optionally, send a welcome message by going to the Invite page, selecting the employee, and sending a default or custom message.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115576", "reference_answer": "To invite someone to use AttendanceBot in Slack, ensure they are a member of your workspace. Go to the settings dashboard, toggle on 'Activate new users' for automatic activation, or manually activate them in the personnel tab. Optionally, send a welcome message from the Invite page.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "inviting a user", "retrieved_contexts": ["Adding New Users to Hangouts/Google Chat", "How do I invite new users on my team to start using AttendanceBot?", "Installing AttendanceBot in Google Chat & Introducing New Users"], "generated_answer": "To invite a new user to start using AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure the user is a member of your Slack or Microsoft Teams workspace.\n2. Option 1: Automatically activate new users.\n   - Go to your main 'settings' dashboard.\n   - Scroll down and toggle on \"Activate new users\".\n   - Optionally, toggle on \"Auto invite new users\" for a welcome message.\n3. Option 2: Manually activate new users.\n   - Open the 'settings' dashboard and go to People > Personnel tab.\n   - Ensure \"Show active personnel only\" is off.\n   - Search for the new user profile and toggle their status to \"Active\".\n   - Optionally, set up additional fields like manager, office, etc.\n   - Trigger a welcome message from the Invite page.\n\nIf you encounter issues, contact support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com or chat \"dialm\" to open a support ticket.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115576", "reference_answer": "To invite a new user to AttendanceBot, ensure they are a member of your Slack or Teams workspace. You can either automatically activate new users by toggling on 'Activate new users' in the settings dashboard or manually activate them by searching for their profile in the People tab and setting their status to 'Active'. Optionally, you can send a welcome message.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
