{"query": "where do i enter an employees pay?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to use AttendanceBot to calculate employee wage?", "How to send hours to Gusto for payroll", "What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?"], "generated_answer": "To enter an employee's hourly wage in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to your dashboard's personnel section.\n2. Select the employee for whom you want to set the hourly wage.\n3. Look for the \"Hourly Wage\" field.\n4. Enter the hourly wage in this field.\n\nAttendanceBot will then automatically calculate the employee's overall wage, which can be viewed on the timesheet and payroll reports.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131997", "reference_answer": "To enter an employee's hourly wage in AttendanceBot, go to the personnel section of your dashboard, select the employee, find the 'Hourly Wage' field, and enter the wage. AttendanceBot will calculate the overall wage for you.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "where do I put in an employees hourly rate?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to use AttendanceBot to calculate employee wage?", "How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?", "How to send hours to Gusto for payroll"], "generated_answer": "To set an employee's hourly wage in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the dashboard's personnel section.\n2. Select the employee for whom you want to set the hourly wage.\n3. Look for the \"Hourly Wage\" field.\n4. Enter the hourly wage for the employee.\n\nOnce set, AttendanceBot will automatically calculate the overall wage, which can be viewed on the timesheet and payroll reports.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131997", "reference_answer": "To set an employee's hourly wage in AttendanceBot, go to the dashboard's personnel section, select the employee, find the 'Hourly Wage' field, and enter the hourly wage. AttendanceBot will then calculate the overall wage for timesheets and payroll reports.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "can you tell me more about the reports that we can generate?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How can I generate reports?", "How to generate a report with specific filters", "How to schedule reports"], "generated_answer": "Could you please specify what details you are looking for about the reports? For example, are you interested in how to generate them, specific filters, or scheduling options?", "reference_answer": "AttendanceBot allows you to generate various reports, including attendance summaries, leave reports, and more. You can apply specific filters to customize your reports and even schedule them for regular delivery. For detailed instructions, you can refer to the following articles: [How to generate reports](https://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000116052), [Generate reports with filters](https://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000093467), and [Schedule reports](https://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000116147).", "quality_score": 3.6, "bucket": "partial"}
{"query": "how do I set what attendancebot reports in a channel?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to setup Slack channel notifications with AttendanceBot", "How can I generate reports?", "How to schedule reports"], "generated_answer": "To set up what AttendanceBot reports in a Slack channel, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure AttendanceBot is added to the channel by typing \"/invite @attendancebot\".\n2. Create alerts or notifications for the desired events such as upcoming vacations, birthdays, or availability.\n3. For different team announcements, create separate channels and invite AttendanceBot to each.\n4. To explore different channel notifications, click on \"Create new\" in the channel notification settings.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118249", "reference_answer": "To set what AttendanceBot reports in a channel, follow these steps: 1. Ensure AttendanceBot is added to the channel by typing '/invite @attendancebot'. 2. Create alerts or notifications for events like vacations or birthdays. 3. For different team announcements, create separate channels and invite AttendanceBot to each. 4. Customize notifications by clicking 'Create new' in the channel notification settings.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
