{"query": "How to check my leaves summary", "retrieved_contexts": ["Checking Your Leave Balance", "How to check leave balance in Slack with AttendanceBot", "What are the different kinds of leaves?"], "generated_answer": "To check your leave summary in Slack using AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open a direct message with AttendanceBot.\n2. Type \"balance\" and send the message.\n3. You will receive a summary of your leave balances, including details like \"Carry forwarded\", \"Days Taken\", \"Accrued\", and \"Annual count\".\n4. Leave types with unlimited balance will be listed at the end.\n\nIf you are a manager, you can also check the leave balance of your team members by typing \"balance @username\".\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000094186", "reference_answer": "To check your leave summary in Slack using AttendanceBot, open a direct message with AttendanceBot and type 'balance'. You'll receive a summary of your leave balances, including details like 'Carry forwarded', 'Days Taken', 'Accrued', and 'Annual count'. Managers can check their team members' balances by typing 'balance @username'.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "I added Attendance bot to my teams account how do i invite my whole team into it", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I invite new users on my team to start using AttendanceBot?", "How do I install AttendanceBot in Slack?", "How do I add admin users?"], "generated_answer": "To invite your team to use AttendanceBot on Microsoft Teams, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure all team members are already part of your Microsoft Teams workspace.\n2. Go to your main 'settings' dashboard.\n3. Scroll down and toggle on \"Activate new users\" to automatically activate new workspace members as AttendanceBot users.\n4. Optionally, toggle on \"Auto invite new users\" if you want them to receive a welcome message from AttendanceBot.\n\nIf you prefer to manually activate users:\n\n1. Open the 'settings' dashboard and go to People --> Personnel tab.\n2. Ensure \"Show active personnel only\" is turned off.\n3. Search for the new user's profile and toggle their status to \"Active.\"\n4. Optionally, set up additional profile fields and send a welcome message from the Invite page.\n\nFor further assistance, contact support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com or chat \"dialm\" to AttendanceBot.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115576", "reference_answer": "To invite your whole team to AttendanceBot on Microsoft Teams, ensure all members are part of your Teams workspace, go to the main 'settings' dashboard, and toggle on 'Activate new users' to automatically activate them. Optionally, enable 'Auto invite new users' for a welcome message.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
