{"query": "unable to invite a team member ", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I invite new users on my team to start using AttendanceBot?", "How do I delete a leave applied by a member of my team?", "Adding New Users to Hangouts/Google Chat"], "generated_answer": "To invite a team member to use AttendanceBot on Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure the team member is already a member of your Slack workspace.\n2. Go to your main 'settings' dashboard in AttendanceBot.\n3. Option 1: Toggle on \"Activate new users\" to automatically activate new workspace members.\n4. Option 2: Manually activate the user by going to the 'people' --> 'personnel' tab.\n5. Ensure \"Show active personnel only\" is turned off.\n6. Search for the new user and toggle their status to \"Active\".\n7. Optionally, send a welcome message by going to People > Invite and selecting the employee.\n\nIf you still face issues, contact support at support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com or open a support ticket by chatting \"dialm\" to AttendanceBot.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115576", "reference_answer": "To invite a team member to use AttendanceBot on Slack, ensure they are part of your Slack workspace. Then, go to the 'settings' dashboard, navigate to 'people' > 'personnel', and ensure 'Show active personnel only' is toggled off. Search for the user and toggle their status to 'Active'. Optionally, send a welcome message. If issues persist, contact support.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "Followed the steps and its not showing up the user name in search", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I find my missing employee profile on the dashboard? (Slack)", "Installing AttendanceBot in Google Chat & Introducing New Users", "Adding New Users to Hangouts/Google Chat"], "generated_answer": "If you've followed the steps and the user's name is not showing up in the search, try the following troubleshooting steps:\n\n1. Go to the \"Settings\" panel and navigate to people --> personnel.\n2. Toggle off \"Show active personnel only.\"\n3. If you still can't find their profile, click the top teal \"RE-SYNC\" button.\n4. Wait 1-4 hours and then retry the process.\n\nIf the issue persists, consider contacting support.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131680", "reference_answer": "If you've followed the steps and the user's name is not showing up in the search, try the following troubleshooting steps: 1. Go to the 'Settings' panel and navigate to people --> personnel. 2. Toggle off 'Show active personnel only.' 3. If you still can't find their profile, click the top teal 'RE-SYNC' button. 4. Wait 1-4 hours and then retry the process. If the issue persists, consider contacting support.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
