{"query": "can individual team members edit their work schedules?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to create employee specific work schedules?", "How to define your team work week", "How to view my shifts and the shifts of my employees"], "generated_answer": "No, individual team members cannot edit their own work schedules. Only administrators or managers with access to the settings dashboard can customize workweek schedules for specific employees. They can do this by navigating to the work schedule section under the People tab, selecting the employee, and clicking the edit button to make changes.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000142683", "reference_answer": "No, individual team members cannot edit their own work schedules. Only administrators or managers can customize workweek schedules for specific employees through the settings dashboard.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "can you give me more info on work schedules?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to create employee specific work schedules?", "Work Model - Hybrid or Fully Remote", "What are my reporting options and what do the different reports do?"], "generated_answer": "To create employee-specific work schedules, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the work schedule section under the People tab on the settings dashboard.\n2. Select the employee and click on the edit button.\n3. Edit the working days and start time, or add different start times and work hours for different days.\n4. Click on save changes. A personal tag will be added to the employee profile.\n\nYou can also create a workday template:\n\n1. Open the \"Template\" section under work schedule and click on \"Create new\".\n2. Select the details and assign it to employees in bulk.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000142683", "reference_answer": "To learn more about work schedules in AttendanceBot, you can create employee-specific work schedules by editing their details in the work schedule section. You can also create templates for bulk assignments. For more information, visit the AttendanceBot support articles on work schedules and hybrid work models.", "quality_score": 4.6, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "Build roster for 8 engineers in noc work 24\u00d77 ", "retrieved_contexts": ["Work Model - Hybrid or Fully Remote", "AttendanceBot Plans and Features", "Work Model - Hybrid or Fully Remote"], "generated_answer": "To build a 24x7 roster for 8 engineers in a Network Operations Center (NOC) using AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Shift Planning**: Determine the shift duration and number of shifts per day. For 24x7 coverage, you might consider three 8-hour shifts or two 12-hour shifts.\n\n2. **Shift Assignment**: Assign engineers to shifts ensuring that each shift is covered. Rotate engineers to ensure fair distribution of night and weekend shifts.\n\n3. **Use Shift Rostering Feature**: Utilize AttendanceBot's shift rostering feature to create and manage shifts. This includes a color-coded shift calendar with daily/weekly/monthly views.\n\n4. **Set Up Notifications**: Configure notifications for shift reminders and updates to keep engineers informed of their schedules.\n\n5. **Monitor and Adjust**: Regularly review and adjust the roster as needed to accommodate changes or engineer availability.\n\nFor detailed guidance on using AttendanceBot for shift rostering, refer to the documentation or consider opening a support ticket if you need further assistance.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000138965", "reference_answer": "To build a 24x7 roster for 8 engineers in a NOC, determine shift durations, assign shifts, use AttendanceBot's rostering feature, set up notifications, and monitor the roster regularly. For detailed guidance, refer to the AttendanceBot documentation.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
