{"query": "if I invite it to a channel, what kinds of updates can it provide?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to setup Slack channel notifications with AttendanceBot", "How to announce in/out and breaks/lunch on a Slack channel", "How to configure shift alerts"], "generated_answer": "Once you invite AttendanceBot to a Slack channel, it can provide various updates, including:\n\n1. Upcoming vacations or work-from-office/home schedules for the week.\n2. Birthdays and work anniversaries.\n3. Availability updates, such as who\u2019s in, out, on lunch, or on break.\n4. Alerts for overtime assignments or key shift reassignments.\n\nTo set up these notifications, ensure AttendanceBot is added to the channel by typing \"/invite @attendancebot\". You can then configure specific notifications based on your needs.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118249", "reference_answer": "Once you invite AttendanceBot to a Slack channel, it can provide updates on upcoming vacations, WFO/WFH schedules, birthdays, work anniversaries, availability (who\u2019s in, out, lunching, or breaking), and alerts for overtime assignments or key shift reassignments. To set up these notifications, type '/invite @attendancebot' in the channel.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "am I able to sync my google calendar with attendancebot?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to integrate your calendar with AttendanceBot for Slack", "How to integrate your calendar with AttendanceBot for Slack", "I don't use Slack or Microsoft Teams. Can I still use AttendanceBot?"], "generated_answer": "Yes, you can sync your Google Calendar with AttendanceBot. Follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the \"menu\" in AttendanceBot and select \"data & integrations.\"\n2. Choose \"Calendar\" from the sub-menu.\n3. Use the \"Get link\" button to copy an ICS calendar link.\n4. Open Google Calendar.\n5. Click the down arrow next to \u201cOther calendars\u201d and select \u201cAdd by URL.\u201d\n6. Paste the URL and click \u201cAdd calendar.\u201d\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000017361", "reference_answer": "Yes, you can sync your Google Calendar with AttendanceBot. Here are the steps: 1. Go to the 'menu' in AttendanceBot and select 'data & integrations.' 2. Choose 'Calendar' from the sub-menu. 3. Use the 'Get link' button to copy an ICS calendar link. 4. Open Google Calendar. 5. Click the down arrow next to 'Other calendars' and select 'Add by URL.' 6. Paste the URL and click 'Add calendar.'", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "is there a feature that would allow for managers to prospectively see when people would have availability? So for example, if I know someone will be available on Monday, I am more likely to delegate something that is time sensitive. However, if they are not, I would take care of it myself.", "retrieved_contexts": [" How to view overlapping leaves as an approving manager", "What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?", "How to view and claim open shifts"], "generated_answer": "I don't have enough information to determine if AttendanceBot has a specific feature for prospectively viewing employee availability for future delegation purposes. You might consider opening a support ticket for more detailed assistance.\n\nticket", "reference_answer": "AttendanceBot does not currently have a specific feature that allows managers to view future employee availability for delegation purposes. However, you can check overlapping leaves and manage shifts through the available features. For more detailed assistance, consider opening a support ticket.", "quality_score": 3.0, "bucket": "partial"}
{"query": "How can I change sick leave of a team member", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I delete a leave applied by a member of my team?", "How to change or edit an existing approved leave", "How to enable and understand leave privacy and hidden leave types"], "generated_answer": "To change a sick leave for a team member, follow these steps:\n\n1. Delete the existing sick leave by typing the command \"delete @username\" to AttendanceBot, where \"@username\" is the team member's name.\n2. You will see a list of approved leaves for that user. Click the Delete button for the sick leave you wish to change.\n3. Once deleted, resubmit a fresh leave request with the updated details.\n\nNote: If the leave type is \"sick\" and you want to hide it from public interfaces, you can manage this under Vacation Management -> Leaves -> Leave Types and Quotas.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000105285", "reference_answer": "To change the sick leave of a team member, follow these steps: 1. Delete the existing sick leave by typing 'delete @username' to AttendanceBot. 2. Click the Delete button for the sick leave you wish to change. 3. Resubmit a fresh leave request with the updated details. For more details, refer to the AttendanceBot documentation.", "quality_score": 4.2, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how can I edit the sick leave of a team member who made a mistake", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I delete a leave applied by a member of my team?", "How to change or edit an existing approved leave", "How to delete approved leave for a reportee or employee"], "generated_answer": "To edit an existing approved leave, you generally need to delete the leave and resubmit a new request. Here\u2019s how you can delete a leave for a team member:\n\n1. Type the command \"delete @username\" in Slack, where \"@username\" is the team member's Slack username.\n2. You will see a list of approved leaves for that user, with a Delete button below each leave.\n3. Click the Delete button for the leave you wish to delete. You will receive a confirmation notification.\n\nAfter deleting, you can submit a new leave request with the correct details.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131566", "reference_answer": "To edit a sick leave for a team member, you generally need to delete the existing leave and resubmit a new request. Type 'delete @username' in Slack to see a list of approved leaves for that user, then click the Delete button for the leave you wish to remove. After that, submit a new leave request with the correct details. If the leave type is 'available' (like wfh, wfo, or remote work), you can override the existing request without canceling.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "How can I delete a sick leave for a team member", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I delete a leave applied by a member of my team?", "How to delete approved leave for a reportee or employee", "How to cancel / retract / rescind / delete a leave request"], "generated_answer": "To delete a sick leave for a team member in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Type the command \"delete @username\" in Slack, where \"@username\" is the Slack username of the team member.\n2. You will see a list of approved leaves for that user, both past and upcoming, with a Delete button below each leave.\n3. Click on the Delete button for the sick leave you wish to delete.\n4. You will receive a Slack notification confirming the cancellation, and the team member will be notified of the cancellation.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000116057", "reference_answer": "To delete a sick leave for a team member in AttendanceBot, type 'delete @username' in Slack. You'll see a list of approved leaves for that user. Click the Delete button next to the sick leave you want to remove. A confirmation notification will be sent to you and the team member.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
