{"query": "how a user to check in", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to track time in Slack using AttendanceBot", "Adding New Users to Hangouts/Google Chat", "Time/Task tracking"], "generated_answer": "To check in using AttendanceBot in Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Send \"Menu\" as a direct message to AttendanceBot to open the options menu.\n2. Select the \"In \u2705\" button to start recording your hours. If the button says \"Out \u274c\", you are already signed in.\n3. For project tracking, selecting \"In \u2705\" will display a menu of assigned projects or clients. Choose a project and confirm to complete your punch in.\n\nAlternatively, you can type \"in\" as a direct message to AttendanceBot to quickly punch in.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118256", "reference_answer": "To check in using AttendanceBot in Slack, send 'Menu' as a direct message to AttendanceBot. Select the 'In \u2705' button to start recording your hours. If you're tracking projects, choose a project from the menu that appears after selecting 'In \u2705'. Alternatively, you can type 'in' to quickly punch in.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how the user will clock in", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to track time in Slack using AttendanceBot", "Time/Task tracking", "How to set up auto-punch out for my employees"], "generated_answer": "To clock in using AttendanceBot in Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Send \"Menu\" as a direct message to AttendanceBot.\n2. In the menu that appears, select the \"In \u2705\" button to start recording your hours. If it says \"Out \u274c\", you're already signed in.\n3. If you're tracking projects, selecting \"In \u2705\" will prompt you to choose a project/client and task. Confirm your selection to complete the punch in.\n4. Alternatively, you can simply type \"in\" as a direct message to AttendanceBot to clock in.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118256", "reference_answer": "To clock in using AttendanceBot in Slack, send 'Menu' as a direct message to AttendanceBot. Select the 'In \u2705' button to start recording your hours. If prompted, choose your project/client and task. Alternatively, you can type 'in' to clock in directly.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
