{"query": "How to remove approved pto", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to change or edit an existing approved leave", "How do I unlock the timesheet that's approved?", "How to delete approved leave for a reportee or employee"], "generated_answer": "To remove an approved PTO, you need to delete the existing leave and resubmit a new request if necessary. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n1. If you're deleting your own leave, use the command \"delete @yourusername\" in Slack to AttendanceBot.\n2. You'll see a list of your approved leaves. Find the PTO you want to delete.\n3. Click the \"Delete\" button next to the leave you wish to cancel.\n4. Confirm the deletion. You'll receive a Slack confirmation, and the cancellation will be processed.\n\nIf you are a manager deleting a leave for a reportee, use the command \"delete @username\" where \"@username\" is the Slack username of the employee.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000093812", "reference_answer": "To remove an approved PTO, you need to delete the existing leave and resubmit a new request if necessary. Here\u2019s how you can do it: 1. If you're deleting your own leave, use the command 'delete @yourusername' in Slack to AttendanceBot. 2. You'll see a list of your approved leaves. Find the PTO you want to delete. 3. Click the 'Delete' button next to the leave you wish to cancel. 4. Confirm the deletion. You'll receive a Slack confirmation, and the cancellation will be processed. If you are a manager deleting a leave for a reportee, use the command 'delete @username' where '@username' is the Slack username of the employee.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "How to remove approved pto non admin", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to change or edit an existing approved leave", "How do I unlock the timesheet that's approved?", "How to delete approved leave for a reportee or employee"], "generated_answer": "To remove an approved PTO as a non-admin, you generally cannot edit it directly. Instead, you need to delete the existing leave and resubmit a new request. However, if the leave type is \"available\" like work from home or remote work, you can override it with a new request without canceling. If you need to delete a past leave, you will need to ask a manager or admin to do it for you.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131566", "reference_answer": "As a non-admin, you cannot directly remove approved PTO. You need to delete the existing leave and submit a new request. For certain leave types like work from home, you can override it with a new request. For deleting past leave, contact a manager or admin.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "i am unable to get the free version to install", "retrieved_contexts": ["I'm getting an error message \"You are viewing the archives of a deactivated account\" while accessing AttendanceBot in Slack. What should I do?", "How long is my AttendanceBot trial?", "How do I uninstall AttendanceBot from Google Chat ?"], "generated_answer": "If you're having trouble installing the free version of AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to www.attendancebot.com.\n2. Click on \"GET STARTED\" and then \"TRY FOR SLACK\" to install AttendanceBot in your workspace.\n3. If you can't see AttendanceBot in Slack, click on the Apps icon on the left side of the screen and search for AttendanceBot in the App Directory. Click on it to add it under the Recent Apps list.\n\nIf you continue to face issues, please open a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000098428", "reference_answer": "If you're having trouble installing the free version of AttendanceBot, follow these steps: 1. Go to www.attendancebot.com. 2. Click on 'GET STARTED' and then 'TRY FOR SLACK' to install AttendanceBot in your workspace. 3. If you can't see AttendanceBot in Slack, click on the Apps icon on the left side of the screen and search for AttendanceBot in the App Directory. Click on it to add it under the Recent Apps list. If you continue to face issues, please open a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
