{"query": "How to install atandancebot", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I install AttendanceBot in Slack?", "Installing AttendanceBot in Google Chat & Introducing New Users", "How to uninstall AttendanceBot from Slack"], "generated_answer": "To install AttendanceBot in Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Search for \"AttendanceBot\" under Apps in Slack.\n2. Click \"Add to Slack\" and follow the prompts.\n3. Once added, the app will onboard the admin and ask for permission to introduce itself to the team. It's recommended to say yes.\n4. Everyone will receive a direct message from AttendanceBot and can start using it for leave and time tracking.\n\nFor further assistance, you can say \"help\" in the app or \"dialm\" to connect with support.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118255", "reference_answer": "To install AttendanceBot in Slack, search for 'AttendanceBot' under Apps in Slack, click 'Add to Slack', and follow the prompts. The app will onboard the admin and request permission to introduce itself to the team. It's recommended to say yes. Everyone will receive a direct message from AttendanceBot to start using it for leave and time tracking. For further assistance, type 'help' in the app or 'dialm' to connect with support.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
