{"query": "inivite people to my team", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I invite new users on my team to start using AttendanceBot?", "How to add a team holiday", "How to integrate calendars"], "generated_answer": "To invite new users to your team in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure the users are already members of your Slack or Microsoft Teams workspace.\n2. Option 1: Automatically activate new users:\n   - Go to your main 'settings' dashboard.\n   - Scroll down and toggle on \"Activate new users\".\n   - Optionally, toggle on \"Auto invite new users\" to send a welcome message.\n\n3. Option 2: Manually activate new users:\n   - Open the 'settings' dashboard and go to People --> Personnel tab.\n   - Ensure \"Show active personnel only\" is toggled off.\n   - Search for the new user and toggle their status to \"Active\".\n   - Optionally, set up additional fields by clicking on their name.\n   - Trigger a welcome message by going to the Invite page (People > Invite).\n\nIf you encounter issues, contact support at support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com or chat \"dialm\" to open a support ticket.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115576", "reference_answer": "To invite new users to your team in AttendanceBot, ensure they are members of your Slack or Microsoft Teams workspace. You can either automatically activate new users through the settings dashboard or manually activate them by searching for their name in the personnel tab. For more details, visit the support article: https://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115576.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "where can I see my PTO", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to view my shifts and the shifts of my employees", "How to configure and use time-off-in-lieu (TOIL) (Slack)", "How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?"], "generated_answer": "To view your PTO (Paid Time Off) balance, you can type \"balance\" as a direct message (DM) to AttendanceBot in Slack. This will show you your current PTO balance. If you need more detailed information, you might want to check your company's specific settings or contact your HR department.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000112422", "reference_answer": "To view your PTO balance, send a direct message to AttendanceBot in Slack with the word 'balance'. This will provide you with your current PTO balance. For more details, check your company's settings or contact HR.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "why is Guest services and maintenance shits not posting in the channel #shift-schedule-notifications ?\\", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to configure shift alerts", "How to announce in/out and breaks/lunch on a Slack channel", "How to setup Slack channel notifications with AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "To ensure that shift notifications are posted in the channel #shift-schedule-notifications, follow these steps:\n\n1. Confirm that AttendanceBot is added to the channel by typing `/invite @attendancebot` in the channel.\n2. Navigate to the Notification section in AttendanceBot and select \"Channel Announcements.\"\n3. Click \"Create New\" and select \u2018Shift assignment alert\u2019.\n4. Choose the channel #shift-schedule-notifications for the notification.\n5. Ensure you have set up the correct alert type (e.g., Self assignment alerts, Re-assignment alerts, or Shifts with Attributes) for the shifts you want to notify about.\n\nIf the issue persists, verify that the shifts in question have the correct attributes set for notification.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131995", "reference_answer": "To ensure that shift notifications are posted in the channel #shift-schedule-notifications, confirm AttendanceBot is added to the channel, set up the correct alert type, and verify shift attributes. For detailed steps, refer to the AttendanceBot documentation.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
