{"query": "trying to add a new staff.Can't find the add employee tab", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I find my missing employee profile on the dashboard? (Slack)", "How do I assign managers for my employees?", "How do I add admin users?"], "generated_answer": "To add a new employee, ensure they are already present in your Slack workspace. AttendanceBot syncs with your platform and identifies employees using that workspace. If an employee is added to your workspace but not visible on the dashboard, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the \"Settings\" panel and navigate to People > Personnel.\n2. Toggle off \"Show active personnel only.\"\n3. If you find their profile, check \"active\" on the right. \n4. If you can't find their profile, click the top teal \"RE-SYNC\" button and wait 1-4 hours before retrying or contacting support.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131680", "reference_answer": "To add a new employee, ensure they are already present in your Slack workspace. AttendanceBot syncs with your platform and identifies employees using that workspace. If an employee is added to your workspace but not visible on the dashboard, go to the 'Settings' panel, navigate to People > Personnel, toggle off 'Show active personnel only,' check their profile, and if not found, click 'RE-SYNC' and wait 1-4 hours.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
