{"query": "channel not list in notification", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to announce in/out and breaks/lunch on a Slack channel", "How to setup Slack channel notifications with AttendanceBot", "How to configure shift alerts"], "generated_answer": "If a channel is not listed in the notification options, ensure that AttendanceBot is added to that channel. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n1. Go to the Slack channel where you want notifications.\n2. Type `/invite @attendancebot` in the channel to add AttendanceBot.\n3. Once added, navigate to the \"Settings, people, policy\" > \"Notifications\" in AttendanceBot's menu.\n4. Click on \"Create new\" to configure a new notification rule.\n\nIf the channel still doesn't appear, try refreshing your Slack workspace or check if you have the necessary permissions to add apps to the channel.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000049835", "reference_answer": "If a channel is not listed in the notification options, ensure that AttendanceBot is added to that channel. Type `/invite @attendancebot` in the channel, then configure notifications in AttendanceBot's settings. If the channel still doesn't appear, refresh your Slack workspace or check your permissions.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
