{"query": "how do i edit personnel punch card?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?"], "generated_answer": "To edit a personnel punch card in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the AttendanceBot dashboard and select \"Time Tracking\" then \"Edit Timesheet.\"\n2. Choose the date range and employee from the dropdown menu.\n3. Click on \"Expand\" for the specific date you want to edit.\n4. Click the pencil icon next to the punch you want to edit.\n5. Update the punch details as needed and hit \"save.\"\n\nThis will automatically flag the change on reporting, including the editor and timestamp of the edit.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118266", "reference_answer": "To edit a personnel punch card in AttendanceBot, go to the dashboard, select 'Time Tracking' then 'Edit Timesheet.' Choose the date range and employee, expand the specific date, click the pencil icon next to the punch, update the details, and hit 'save.' Changes will be flagged in reporting.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "Motivate me to get my work done", "retrieved_contexts": ["Time/Task tracking", "Automate time-off requests using Slack's workflow builder", "How to create employee specific work schedules?"], "generated_answer": "I'm here to assist with AttendanceBot-related queries. For motivation, consider setting clear goals, breaking tasks into smaller steps, and rewarding yourself for completing them. If you have any questions about AttendanceBot, feel free to ask!", "reference_answer": "To stay motivated, break your work into smaller tasks, set specific goals with deadlines, and reward yourself for completing them. Eliminate distractions and remind yourself of the benefits of completing your work. If you need help with AttendanceBot features, let me know!", "quality_score": 3.2, "bucket": "partial"}
{"query": "changing leave quota", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to setup accrual rules and leave quotas based on company policy", "How to setup accrual rules and leave quotas based on company policy", "How to setup accrual rules and leave quotas based on company policy"], "generated_answer": "To change leave quotas in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Navigate to the \"accrual settings\" tab in the edit screen.\n2. Decide if you want a universal leave policy or a policy for a specific employee set.\n3. Adjust the leave quota by setting the accrual rules, such as fixed or hourly accrual.\n4. Configure additional settings like rollover days, cap on annual leave, and pro rata distribution if needed.\n5. Save your changes to apply the new leave quota settings.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000051255", "reference_answer": "To change leave quotas in AttendanceBot, follow these steps: 1. Navigate to the 'accrual settings' tab in the edit screen. 2. Decide if you want a universal leave policy or a policy for a specific employee set. 3. Adjust the leave quota by setting the accrual rules, such as fixed or hourly accrual. 4. Configure additional settings like rollover days, cap on annual leave, and pro rata distribution if needed. 5. Save your changes to apply the new leave quota settings.", "quality_score": 4.4, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "deleting leaves of members", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I delete a leave applied by a member of my team?", "How to delete approved leave for a reportee or employee", "How to delete past or future wfo and wfh leaves? - for hybrid teams"], "generated_answer": "To delete a leave applied by a member of your team, follow these steps:\n\n1. Type the command \"delete @username\" in Slack, where \"@username\" is the Slack username of the team member.\n2. A list of approved leaves for that user will appear, showing both past and upcoming leaves.\n3. Click the Delete button below the leave you wish to delete.\n4. You will receive a Slack notification confirming the cancellation, and the team member will be notified as well.\n\nIf you need to delete leaves from a specific date onwards, use the command \"Delete <date> @username\" to filter the list.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000116057", "reference_answer": "To delete a leave applied by a member of your team, type 'delete @username' in Slack. A list of approved leaves will appear. Click the Delete button for the leave you want to remove. For specific date filtering, use 'Delete <date> @username'.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "delete leave comment", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I delete a leave applied by a member of my team?", "How to delete approved leave for a reportee or employee", "Checking Your Leave Balance"], "generated_answer": "To delete a leave applied by a member of your team, follow these steps:\n\n1. Type the command \"delete @username\" to AttendanceBot, replacing \"@username\" with the Slack username of the team member.\n2. A list of approved leaves for that user will appear, showing both past and upcoming leaves.\n3. Click the Delete button below the leave you wish to delete.\n4. You will receive a Slack notification confirming the cancellation, and the reportee will be notified as well.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000116057", "reference_answer": "To delete a leave applied by a member of your team, type 'delete @username' to AttendanceBot, select the leave from the list, and click Delete. You will receive a confirmation notification.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
