{"query": "report that shows punch in times", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to approve the timesheets of my reportees"], "generated_answer": "To view or edit specific punch in times, you can use the timesheet editor in AttendanceBot. Here's how:\n\n1. From the \"Menu,\" select \"Timesheet actions\" and click on \u201cEdit\u201d to access your timesheet editor.\n2. Choose the desired date range using the \u201cDate Range\u201d dropdown.\n3. If you have reportees, you can select another employee to view their timesheet.\n4. Click \"expand\" on any day to see the minute-by-minute punch history.\n5. To change a punch in time, click the pencil icon in the punch row, update the details, and hit \"save.\"\n\nFor a report, you may need to export the timesheet data after reviewing or editing it.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118260", "reference_answer": "To view a report that shows punch in times using AttendanceBot, follow these steps: 1. Send 'Menu' as a direct message to AttendanceBot in Slack. 2. Open the 'Data & Integrations' section of the menu. 3. Click on 'Reports' to access detailed data. 4. Alternatively, use the timesheet editor to view and edit punch in times.", "quality_score": 4.4, "bucket": "well_answered"}
