{"query": "Employee toil not adding on", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?", "How to configure and use time-off-in-lieu (TOIL) (Slack)", "How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?"], "generated_answer": "If TOIL (Time Off In Lieu) is not being added for an employee, follow these steps to troubleshoot:\n\n1. Ensure that TOIL is activated by going to Settings -> Time Tracking -> Overtime and toggling ON the \u201cTime off in lieu (TOIL)\u201d option.\n2. Check that the overtime thresholds are correctly set for the employee. This can be done in the employee's profile by setting the appropriate daily or weekly hours.\n3. Verify that the TOIL leave type has been created under the vacation management tab.\n4. Confirm that existing overtime rules are turned off, as TOIL and overtime cannot be calculated simultaneously.\n\nIf these steps don't resolve the issue, consider opening a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000112422", "reference_answer": "If TOIL is not being added for an employee, ensure TOIL is activated, check overtime thresholds, verify TOIL leave type is created, and confirm existing overtime rules are turned off. If issues persist, open a support ticket.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "How does the calendar integration work", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to integrate calendars", "How to integrate your calendar with AttendanceBot for Slack", "How to integrate your calendar with AttendanceBot for Slack"], "generated_answer": "To integrate your calendar with AttendanceBot in Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open the options \"menu\" in AttendanceBot and select \"data & integrations.\"\n2. Choose \"Calendar\" from the sub-menu.\n3. Depending on your integration preference, use \"Enable\" for a personal calendar sync or \"Get link\" for a public calendar link.\n4. For Apple Calendar, use \u2318-Option-S or \u201cNew Calendar Subscription\u201d and paste the URL.\n5. For Google Calendar, use \u201cAdd by URL\u201d under \u201cOther calendars.\u201d\n6. For Office 365/Outlook, use \u201cOpen Calendar\u201d under \u201cOther Calendars\u201d and enter the URL.\n7. For Outlook.com, use \u201cimport\u201d and paste the URL in \u201cCalendar URL.\u201d\n\nAll calendars will display times in your local timezone.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000017361", "reference_answer": "To integrate your calendar with AttendanceBot in Slack, go to the options menu, select 'data & integrations,' and choose 'Calendar.' Use 'Enable' for personal calendar sync or 'Get link' for a public calendar link. For Apple Calendar, use \u2318-Option-S or 'New Calendar Subscription' and paste the URL. For Google Calendar, use 'Add by URL' under 'Other calendars.' For Office 365/Outlook, use 'Open Calendar' under 'Other Calendars' and enter the URL. For Outlook.com, use 'import' and paste the URL in 'Calendar URL.' All calendars will display times in your local timezone.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "what does calendar integration do", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to integrate calendars", "How to integrate your calendar with AttendanceBot for Slack", "How to integrate your calendar with AttendanceBot for Slack"], "generated_answer": "Calendar integration with AttendanceBot allows you to sync your team's vacation calendar with various platforms like Google Calendar, Apple Calendar, Office 365, and Outlook.com. You can subscribe to a public calendar to view team leaves or integrate with a personal calendar to automatically block out-of-office and unavailable times based on AttendanceBot data. This ensures that all calendar events are updated in your local time zone, making it easier for distributed teams to manage time off requests across different time zones.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000116056", "reference_answer": "Calendar integration with AttendanceBot allows you to sync your team's vacation calendar with platforms like Google Calendar, Apple Calendar, Office 365, and Outlook.com. This enables you to view team leaves on a shared calendar and automatically block out-of-office times based on AttendanceBot data, ensuring all events are updated in your local time zone.", "quality_score": 4.6, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "Hi! I currently have inactive users in the list. How do I delete them? I don't want to pay since there are only 3 active people in our slack. The others do not work for us anymore.", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to inactivate users?", "How to deactivate a user in AttendanceBot", "I'm getting an error message \"You are viewing the archives of a deactivated account\" while accessing AttendanceBot in Slack. What should I do?"], "generated_answer": "You cannot delete users in AttendanceBot, but you can inactivate them to prevent them from interacting with the app. Here's how you can inactivate users:\n\n1. Open the settings panel by typing \"Settings\" as a direct message to AttendanceBot and click on the link prompted.\n2. Navigate to the People --> Personnel tab.\n3. Find the employee using search or scroll, and click the \"Inactive\" toggle next to their profile.\n\nThis will ensure they cannot use the app, and you won't be charged for inactive users.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131681", "reference_answer": "You cannot delete users in AttendanceBot, but you can inactivate them to prevent them from interacting with the app. Here's how to inactivate users: 1. Open the settings panel by typing 'Settings' as a direct message to AttendanceBot and click on the link prompted. 2. Navigate to the People --> Personnel tab. 3. Find the employee using search or scroll, and click the 'Inactive' toggle next to their profile. This will ensure they cannot use the app, and you won't be charged for inactive users.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how to use breaks in/out ", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to announce in/out and breaks/lunch on a Slack channel", "How do I apply for lunch or break with AttendanceBot in Slack?", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times "], "generated_answer": "To apply for a break using AttendanceBot in Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Type \"break for 10 mins\" or \"brb in 10 mins\" in Slack. You can adjust the duration as needed.\n2. Once the break time is up, AttendanceBot will ask if you want to punch back in or continue your break.\n3. If you're done, select \"Yes\" to punch back in. If you want to extend, select \"No, still on break\" and provide the new duration.\n\nFor lunch, simply type \"lunch\" to start your lunch break. You can punch back in anytime by typing \":in\" if you return early.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000063989", "reference_answer": "To use breaks in AttendanceBot, type 'break for 10 mins' or 'brb in 10 mins' in Slack. After your break, AttendanceBot will prompt you to punch back in. For lunch, type 'lunch' to start your lunch break, and you can punch back in anytime by typing ':in'.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how to checkin and out ", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to track time in Slack using AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "To check in and out using AttendanceBot in Slack:\n\n1. Send \"Menu\" as a direct message to AttendanceBot to open the option menu.\n2. To punch in, select the \"In \u2705\" button to start recording your hours. If you are tracking projects, choose a project from the menu and confirm.\n3. To punch out, select the \"Out \u274c\" button to stop recording your hours.\n4. For breaks or lunch, use the respective buttons instead of \"out\" to classify the time correctly.\n5. Alternatively, you can type \"in\" and \"out\" as direct messages to AttendanceBot for quick actions.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118256", "reference_answer": "To check in and out using AttendanceBot in Slack, send 'Menu' to open the options. Select 'In \u2705' to check in and 'Out \u274c' to check out. Use the respective buttons for breaks. You can also type 'in' and 'out' for quick actions.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how to apply for leave", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to apply for leave next year or any future year", "How can I apply for leave in Slack with AttendanceBot", "How to apply leave on behalf of employee on Slack as admin/manager"], "generated_answer": "To apply for leave in Slack using AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Message \"menu\" to AttendanceBot to open the options menu navigator.\n2. Click the \u2018Apply\u2019 button to open a request form popup.\n3. Complete your request by choosing the leave type, duration, and date, and hit \u201cSubmit\u201d.\n\nYou can also shortcut the process by messaging AttendanceBot with specific leave details, like \u201csick today\u201d or \u201cpto next Thursday\u201d.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131679", "reference_answer": "To apply for leave in Slack using AttendanceBot, type 'Apply' to open the request form. Fill in the leave type, duration, and dates, then hit 'Confirm.' For quick requests, you can message AttendanceBot with details like 'sick today.'", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
