{"query": "OUr employees can start work between 08:00 and 10:00", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to create employee specific work schedules?", "How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?", "How to configure overtime and time off in lieu (TOIL) rules?"], "generated_answer": "To set up a flexible start time for your employees between 08:00 and 10:00, you can create a customized work schedule for them. Here's how:\n\n1. Go to the work schedule section under the People tab on the settings dashboard.\n2. Select the employee and click on the edit button.\n3. Edit the working days and set the start time to allow a range between 08:00 and 10:00.\n4. Save the changes.\n\nThis will allow your employees to start their workday within the specified time range.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000142683", "reference_answer": "To set up a flexible start time for your employees between 08:00 and 10:00, go to the work schedule section under the People tab on the settings dashboard. Select the employee, click edit, and set the start time to allow a range between 08:00 and 10:00. Save the changes.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "Is break only possible for a set amount of time? Or can you check in and out for this?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I apply for lunch or break with AttendanceBot in Slack?", "Taking time off", "How to announce in/out and breaks/lunch on a Slack channel"], "generated_answer": "You can set a specific duration for your break, such as \"break for 10 mins\" or \"brb in 10 mins\". Once the break time is up, AttendanceBot will ask if you want to punch back in or continue your break. If you return early, you can punch back in anytime by typing \":in\" to the app, and your break duration will be calculated accordingly.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000063989", "reference_answer": "You can set a specific duration for your break, such as 'break for 10 mins' or 'brb in 10 mins.' AttendanceBot will notify you when your break is over, and you can punch back in anytime by typing ':in'.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how can I see my leave details? ", "retrieved_contexts": ["Checking Your Leave Balance", "How to enable and understand leave privacy and hidden leave types", "How to download team vacation data and reporting"], "generated_answer": "To check your leave details, follow these steps:\n\n1. Type \"balance\" to the AttendanceBot in Slack.\n2. The bot will display your leave balance for each leave type, including details like \"Carry forwarded\", \"Days Taken\", \"Accrued\", and the \"Annual count\".\n3. Leave types with unlimited balance will be shown at the end.\n\nIf you are a manager, you can also check the leave balance of your team members by typing \"balance @username\".\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000116112", "reference_answer": "To check your leave details, type 'balance' to the AttendanceBot in Slack. It will show your leave balance for each type, including 'Carry forwarded', 'Days Taken', 'Accrued', and 'Annual count'. Managers can check their team's leave by typing 'balance @username'.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "please cancel", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to cancel / retract / rescind / delete a leave request", "How do I uninstall AttendanceBot from Google Chat ?", "How to delete approved leave for a reportee or employee"], "generated_answer": "I don't have enough information to assist with your request. If you're trying to cancel a leave request in AttendanceBot, please follow these steps:\n\n1. Open the \"Menu\" and select \"Time off & hybrid work\".\n2. Look for the option labeled \u201cDelete\u201d next to your requested leave.\n3. Click \u201cDelete\u201d to cancel the leave, which will notify both you and your manager.\n\nIf this doesn't help, please provide more details or consider opening a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000121203", "reference_answer": "To cancel a leave request in AttendanceBot, please follow these steps: 1. Open the 'Menu' and select 'Time off & hybrid work'. 2. Look for the option labeled 'Delete' next to your requested leave. 3. Click 'Delete' to cancel the leave, which will notify both you and your manager. If you need further assistance, consider opening a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
