{"query": "how to add members i have 20 but only 11 showing up", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I add admin users?", "How do I invite new users on my team to start using AttendanceBot?", "How do I find my missing employee profile on the dashboard? (Slack)"], "generated_answer": "To add members and ensure all are showing up in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure all members are part of your Slack or Microsoft Teams workspace, as AttendanceBot syncs with these platforms.\n2. If you want AttendanceBot to activate new users automatically:\n   - Go to your main 'settings' dashboard.\n   - Scroll down and toggle on \"Activate new users.\"\n   - Optionally, toggle on \"Auto invite new users\" for a welcome message.\n3. If you prefer to manually activate users:\n   - Open the 'settings' dashboard and go to People --> Personnel tab.\n   - Ensure \"Show active personnel only\" is toggled off.\n   - Search for the new user profile and toggle their status to \"Active.\"\n4. If some profiles are still missing, click the \"RE-SYNC\" button in the Personnel tab and wait 1-4 hours.\n\nIf issues persist, contact support at support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115576", "reference_answer": "To add members in AttendanceBot, ensure they are part of your Slack or Teams workspace. Activate new users in settings or manually toggle their status to 'Active' in the Personnel tab. If profiles are missing, use the 'RE-SYNC' button. For persistent issues, contact support.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
