{"query": "where can i find an export of peoples attendance?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to bulk update employee data using import / export functionality", "How to download team vacation data and reporting", "How to upload medical certificates for sick time"], "generated_answer": "To export employee attendance data, you can use the bulk update feature in AttendanceBot. Follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the People section in the AttendanceBot dashboard.\n2. Select \"Import Team Data\" to access the import/export functionality.\n3. Download the current data to export and view personnel information.\n\nRemember not to add any rows or columns to the downloaded file, as new fields cannot be created using export/import. \n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000124709", "reference_answer": "To export employee attendance data, go to the People section in the AttendanceBot dashboard, select 'Import Team Data', and download the current data. Ensure not to modify the file structure.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "disable break", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I apply for lunch or break with AttendanceBot in Slack?", "How to announce in/out and breaks/lunch on a Slack channel", "How to deactivate a user in AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "To deactivate a user in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open the settings panel by typing \"Settings\" as a direct message to AttendanceBot and click on the link prompted.\n2. Once you open the dashboard, go to the \"people\" section, then the \"personnel\" tab.\n3. Find the employee using search or scroll, and click the \"Inactive\" toggle on the right of the profile tile.\n\nNote: AttendanceBot hides inactive employees by default, but this can be changed using the toggle at the top.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131681", "reference_answer": "I'm sorry, but I don't have enough information on how to disable breaks in AttendanceBot. I suggest you open a support ticket for assistance. You can also explore more about AttendanceBot functionalities by visiting the support portal or direct messaging 'help' in Slack or Teams.", "quality_score": 2.4, "bucket": "content_gap"}
{"query": "how do i set the same punch out time for the team", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to set up auto-punch out for my employees", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to set up punch in/out reminders"], "generated_answer": "To set the same punch out time for your team using AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Type 'settings' in your Slack and click on the settings panel link that appears.\n2. Scroll down to the \"Time Tracking\" section.\n3. Go to \"General Time Settings\".\n4. Switch the toggle ON for \"Auto punch-out time\".\n5. Update the time at which you want to punch out your employees.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118262", "reference_answer": "To set the same punch-out time for your team using AttendanceBot, follow these steps: 1. Type 'settings' in your Slack and click on the settings panel link that appears. 2. Scroll down to the 'Time Tracking' section. 3. Go to 'General Time Settings'. 4. Switch the toggle ON for 'Auto punch-out time'. 5. Update the time at which you want to punch out your employees.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "apply vacation leave", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to apply for recurring leave or hybrid status", "How to apply for leave next year or any future year", "How can I apply for leave in Slack with AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "To apply for vacation leave using AttendanceBot in Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Message \"menu\" to AttendanceBot to open the options menu navigator.\n2. Click the \u2018Apply\u2019 button to open a request form popup.\n3. Complete your request by choosing the leave type (e.g., vacation), duration, and date, then hit \u201cSubmit\u201d.\n\nAlternatively, you can directly message AttendanceBot with a command like \u201cvacation tomorrow\u201d or \u201cvacation next Monday\u201d to quickly apply for leave.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131679", "reference_answer": "To apply for vacation leave using AttendanceBot in Slack, type 'Apply' as a direct message to AttendanceBot. Follow the prompts to enter details such as leave type (vacation), duration, and dates, then hit 'Confirm' to submit your application. Alternatively, you can message AttendanceBot with commands like 'vacation tomorrow' or 'vacation next Monday' for quick applications.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
