{"query": "how can i invite my officemate to join attendancebot?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I install AttendanceBot in Slack?", "How do I invite new users on my team to start using AttendanceBot?", "Adding New Users to Hangouts/Google Chat"], "generated_answer": "To invite your officemate to join AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure your officemate is already a member of your Slack workspace.\n2. Option 1: Automatically activate new users.\n   - Go to the main 'settings' dashboard.\n   - Scroll down and toggle on \"Activate new users\".\n   - Optionally, toggle on \"Auto invite new users\" for a welcome message.\n3. Option 2: Manually activate new users.\n   - Open the 'settings' dashboard and go to people --> personnel tab.\n   - Ensure \"Show active personnel only\" toggle is off.\n   - Search for the new user profile and toggle their status to \"Active\".\n   - Optionally, set additional fields like manager, office, etc.\n   - Trigger a welcome message by going to People > Invite, and send a message to the activated user.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115576", "reference_answer": "To invite your officemate to join AttendanceBot, ensure they are a member of your Slack workspace. You can either automatically activate new users by toggling on 'Activate new users' in the settings dashboard or manually activate them by searching for their profile in the personnel tab and toggling their status to 'Active'. Optionally, send a welcome message.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how to invite a new one join my team?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I invite new users on my team to start using AttendanceBot?", "Installing AttendanceBot in Google Chat & Introducing New Users", "Adding New Users to Hangouts/Google Chat"], "generated_answer": "To invite new users to your team in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure the new user is already a member of your Slack or Microsoft Teams workspace.\n2. Option 1: Automatically activate new users:\n   - Go to your main 'settings' dashboard.\n   - Scroll down and toggle on \"Activate new users\".\n   - Optionally, toggle on \"Auto invite new users\" for a welcome message.\n3. Option 2: Manually activate new users:\n   - Open 'settings' and go to the people --> personnel tab.\n   - Ensure \"Show active personnel only\" is off.\n   - Search for the new user and toggle their status to \"Active\".\n   - Optionally, set up additional profile fields and send a welcome message.\n\nIf you encounter issues, contact support at support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com or type \"dialm\" to open a support ticket.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115576", "reference_answer": "To invite a new user to join your team using AttendanceBot, ensure they are a member of your Slack or Microsoft Teams workspace. You can either automatically activate them in the settings dashboard or manually activate them by searching for their name in the personnel tab. For more details, visit the AttendanceBot support page.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
