{"query": "Hi, we received a charge to our bank account from Aneak on the 12th September for 21.40 - account Sonia McEntee Solicitors.  I do not think we should have been charged or can you send me a copy of the invoice for this as we did not receive one", "retrieved_contexts": ["Billing - how do I download past invoices or receipts?", "Billing - can I get a discount as a non-profit organization using AttendanceBot?", "Billing - how does adding or removing users affect my billing?"], "generated_answer": "I don't have enough information to address this specific charge. To obtain a copy of the invoice, you can:\n\n1. Direct message \"Settings\" to AttendanceBot to access the settings dashboard.\n2. Navigate to the Subscription section to find the invoice number for the specific month.\n3. Share the invoice number with our support team by opening a ticket using the command 'dialm' or start a live chat.\n\nAlternatively, you can open a support ticket by typing 'ticket' for further assistance. \n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000131565", "reference_answer": "I\u2019ve logged a support ticket for you regarding the charge from Aneak on September 12th. You will hear from our team soon. If you need to access your invoices, you can check the Subscription section in the settings dashboard.", "quality_score": 3.8, "bucket": "partial"}
{"query": "how do i create a shift", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to create and manage open shifts and shift templates", "How to use shift attributes", "How to copy shift schedules"], "generated_answer": "To create a shift in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the dashboard and navigate to the Shift Management page.\n2. Click on the \u201cCreate Shift\u201d button.\n3. Choose between creating an \"Open shift\" or a regular shift.\n4. For open shifts, select \u201cOpen shifts\u201d and create a new one by entering the shift name, shift time (re-usable or single use), shift timings, shift days, and optional shift attributes.\n5. Once created, the shift will be visible on the Shift Management page.\n\nFor more detailed instructions, refer to the documentation.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000112956", "reference_answer": "To create a shift in AttendanceBot, follow these steps: 1. Go to the dashboard and navigate to the Shift Management page. 2. Click on the 'Create Shift' button. 3. Choose between creating an 'Open shift' or a regular shift. 4. For open shifts, select 'Open shifts' and create a new one by entering the shift name, shift time (re-usable or single use), shift timings, shift days, and optional shift attributes. 5. Once created, the shift will be visible on the Shift Management page. For more detailed instructions, refer to the documentation: https://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000112956", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how do you punch in", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to set up auto-punch out for my employees", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times "], "generated_answer": "To punch in using AttendanceBot on Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open your Slack workspace.\n2. In any channel or direct message with AttendanceBot, type \"punch in\".\n3. AttendanceBot will confirm your punch in with a message.\n\nIf you need further assistance, please let me know!\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118260", "reference_answer": "To punch in using AttendanceBot on Slack, simply type 'punch in' in a channel or direct message with AttendanceBot, and it will confirm your action.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how do you clock in", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to track time in Slack using AttendanceBot", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to set up auto-punch out for my employees"], "generated_answer": "To clock in using AttendanceBot in Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Send \"Menu\" as a direct message to AttendanceBot.\n2. In the option menu that appears, select the \"In \u2705\" button to start recording your hours.\n3. If you are tracking projects, this will open a menu of assigned projects and tasks. Choose a project and confirm your selection.\n4. Alternatively, you can simply type \"in\" as a direct message to AttendanceBot to clock in quickly.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118256", "reference_answer": "To clock in using AttendanceBot in Slack, send 'Menu' as a direct message to AttendanceBot. Select the 'In \u2705' button to start recording your hours. If tracking projects, choose a project from the menu that appears. Alternatively, you can type 'in' to clock in quickly.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how do you clock out", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to set up auto-punch out for my employees", "How to track time in Slack using AttendanceBot", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times "], "generated_answer": "To clock out using AttendanceBot in Slack, follow these steps:\n\n1. Send \"Menu\" as a direct message to AttendanceBot to open the option menu.\n2. Select the \"Out \u274c\" button to stop recording your hours entirely.\n\nAlternatively, you can type \"out\" as a direct message to AttendanceBot to clock out quickly.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118256", "reference_answer": "To clock out using AttendanceBot in Slack, send 'Menu' to open the option menu and select 'Out \u274c' or simply type 'out' to clock out quickly. For more details, visit: https://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118256.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
