{"query": "Hi! How do I set it so we have flexible work schedule? We can work anytime of the day as long as it's 8 hours.", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to create employee specific work schedules?", "How to manage hybrid work schedules (WFO/WFH days) in Slack using AttendanceBot", "How to configure hybrid work policies"], "generated_answer": "To set up a flexible work schedule where employees can work any time of the day as long as it's 8 hours, you can create a custom work schedule for each employee. Here's how:\n\n1. Go to the \"People\" tab on the settings dashboard and navigate to the work schedule section.\n2. Select the employee and click on the edit button.\n3. Edit the working days and start time, or add different start times and work hours for different days.\n4. Save the changes.\n\nThis will add a personal tag to the employee profile, allowing for flexible scheduling.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000142683", "reference_answer": "To set up a flexible work schedule where employees can work any time of the day as long as it's 8 hours, go to the 'People' tab on the settings dashboard, select the employee, and edit their work schedule to allow for flexible hours. Save the changes to implement the new schedule.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "no free plans?", "retrieved_contexts": ["AttendanceBot Plans and Features", "How long is my AttendanceBot trial?", "AttendanceBot Plans and Features"], "generated_answer": "AttendanceBot offers a free plan for teams with 5 users or less. For teams with more than 5 members, you will need to subscribe to a paid plan. The app provides a 14-day free trial on Slack and Microsoft Teams, and you won't be auto-charged after the trial ends. You can view the pricing plans for more details.\n\nhttps://www.attendancebot.com/pricing/", "reference_answer": "AttendanceBot offers a free plan for teams with 5 users or less. For teams with more than 5 members, a paid plan is required. A 14-day free trial is available on Slack and Microsoft Teams, with no auto-charge after the trial ends. More details can be found on the pricing page.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
