{"query": "how do i pull a report for our timesheets?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How do I get the summary or report of my time in office?", "How to approve the timesheets of my reportees", "How to approve the timesheets of my reportees"], "generated_answer": "To pull a report for your timesheets, follow these steps:\n\n1. Type \"timesheet\" to get a summary of your punch logs for the current day.\n2. For a report of your time in office for the current and previous month, type \"timesheet report\" to receive a downloadable CSV report.\n3. To generate a report for a specific time period, append the date range to the command. For example, type \"Timesheet Report jan 3 to feb 10\".\n\nIf you are a manager, you can type \"Report\" and select the report type as Timesheet Report/Timesheet Summary Report, select the relevant details, and hit \"Confirm\" to download a CSV report.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118258", "reference_answer": "To pull a report for your timesheets, type 'timesheet' for today's summary, 'timesheet report' for a monthly report, or specify a date range like 'Timesheet Report jan 3 to feb 10'. Managers can select report types for detailed downloads.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
