{"query": "do you have to log your hours in slack", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to track time in Slack using AttendanceBot", "How to send hours to Gusto for payroll", "How to generate a payroll report in Slack with AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "Yes, you can log your hours in Slack using AttendanceBot. Here's how:\n\n1. Send \"Menu\" as a direct message to AttendanceBot to open the option menu.\n2. To punch in, select the \"In \u2705\" button. If it says \"Out \u274c\", you're already signed in.\n3. To punch out, select the \"Out \u274c\" button.\n4. For quick actions, you can directly message \"in\" or \"out\" to AttendanceBot.\n5. To view your timesheet, type \"timesheet\" or \"timesheet report\" for a CSV.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118256", "reference_answer": "Yes, you can log your hours in Slack using AttendanceBot. Send 'Menu' to open the options, then select 'In \u2705' to punch in or 'Out \u274c' to punch out. You can also message 'in' or 'out' directly. For your timesheet, type 'timesheet' or 'timesheet report' for a CSV.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "can you log your hours in the attendancebot.com website", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to send hours to Gusto for payroll", "I don't use Slack or Microsoft Teams. Can I still use AttendanceBot?", "What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?"], "generated_answer": "Yes, you can use AttendanceBot directly in your browser, but currently, only the Vacation Management features are available in the web version, which is in beta. For logging hours, you would need to use Slack, MS Teams, or Google Chat. \n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115575", "reference_answer": "Yes, you can log your hours in AttendanceBot, but you need to use Slack, MS Teams, or Google Chat as the web version currently only supports Vacation Management features.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how to print my team's punch summary", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to view employee status on a dashboard or in Slack", "How to set up auto-punch out for my employees", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times "], "generated_answer": "To print your team's punch summary, follow these steps:\n\n1. Direct message AttendanceBot with the command \"punch card\" to receive a text summary of everyone's status.\n2. Once you have the summary, you can copy the text and paste it into a document or directly print it from Slack, depending on your platform's capabilities.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000052710", "reference_answer": "To print your team's punch summary, type the command 'Report', select 'Timesheet Report' or 'Timesheet Summary Report', choose the relevant details, hit 'Confirm', and download the CSV report.", "quality_score": 3.0, "bucket": "partial"}
{"query": "giving designated lunch or breaks", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to setup lunch hours for your team", "How do I apply for lunch or break with AttendanceBot in Slack?", "How to announce in/out and breaks/lunch on a Slack channel"], "generated_answer": "To set up designated lunch or break times in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Type \"settings\" in the AttendanceBot app to access the settings panel.\n2. Navigate to Time Tracking -> General Time Settings.\n3. Configure the following options:\n   - Lunch Duration in Minutes\n   - Break Duration in Minutes\n   - Decide whether to include lunch and breaks in work hours\n\nThis setup allows you to manage how lunch and break times are accounted for in your team's schedule.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000093813", "reference_answer": "To apply for a designated lunch or break with AttendanceBot in Slack, type 'break for [duration]' or 'brb in [duration]'. For setting up designated lunch or break times, go to 'settings' in the AttendanceBot app, then navigate to Time Tracking -> General Time Settings to configure lunch and break durations.", "quality_score": 3.6, "bucket": "partial"}
{"query": "do you have free access?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How long is my AttendanceBot trial?", "Billing - can I get a discount as a non-profit organization using AttendanceBot?", "AttendanceBot Plans and Features"], "generated_answer": "Yes, AttendanceBot offers a 14-day free trial on Slack and Microsoft Teams. Additionally, the app is free for teams with 5 users or less. If your team has more than 5 members, you will need to subscribe to the app after the trial period. \n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000115577", "reference_answer": "Yes, AttendanceBot offers a 14-day free trial on Slack and Microsoft Teams. Additionally, the app is free for teams with 5 users or less. If your team has more than 5 members, you will need to subscribe to the app after the trial period.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "how to file leaves", "retrieved_contexts": ["What are the different kinds of leaves?", "How to apply for leave next year or any future year", "How to download team vacation data and reporting"], "generated_answer": "To file leaves using AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Send a direct message to AttendanceBot with the command \"Apply\".\n2. Select the leave type, duration, and dates.\n3. Hit \"Confirm\" to submit your leave request.\n\nIf you have any questions, you can open a support ticket by typing \"Dialm\" as a message to AttendanceBot.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118253", "reference_answer": "To file leaves using AttendanceBot, follow these steps: 1. Send a direct message to AttendanceBot with the command 'Apply'. 2. Select the leave type, duration, and dates. 3. Hit 'Confirm' to submit your leave request. For further assistance, type 'Dialm' to open a support ticket.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "is there a less expensive plan?", "retrieved_contexts": ["Billing - can I get a discount as a non-profit organization using AttendanceBot?", "AttendanceBot Plans and Features", "How long is my AttendanceBot trial?"], "generated_answer": "AttendanceBot offers different plans to suit various needs. The Standard Plan includes essential features like time tracking, hybrid status, custom leave types, real-time reports, and notifications. If you need more advanced features like overtime tracking and a live punch board, you might consider the Pro Plan. For specific pricing details, you can check the pricing page or contact support for assistance.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000138965", "reference_answer": "AttendanceBot offers different plans, including a Standard Plan with essential features and a Pro Plan with advanced features. For specific pricing details or to inquire about discounts, please check the pricing page or contact support.", "quality_score": 4.6, "bucket": "well_answered"}
