{"query": "how do I set up channel notification", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to setup Slack channel notifications with AttendanceBot", "How to announce in/out and breaks/lunch on a Slack channel", "How to configure shift alerts"], "generated_answer": "To set up channel notifications in Slack using AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. Add AttendanceBot to the relevant Slack channel by typing \"/invite @attendancebot\" in the channel.\n2. Navigate to the configuration menu by selecting \"Settings, people, policy\" > \"Notifications.\"\n3. Click on \"Create new\" to start configuring a new notification rule.\n4. Choose the type of notification you want to set up, such as \"In/Out Notifications,\" \"Break/Lunch notifications,\" or \"Shift assignment alert.\"\n5. Configure the channel, people, and timing for the notification.\n6. Save your changes.\n\nYou can create multiple notifications for different channels, personnel, and times of day.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000049835", "reference_answer": "To set up channel notifications in Slack using AttendanceBot, follow these steps: 1. Add AttendanceBot to the relevant Slack channel by typing '/invite @attendancebot'. 2. Navigate to 'Settings, people, policy' > 'Notifications'. 3. Click on 'Create new' to configure a notification rule. 4. Choose the type of notification (e.g., 'In/Out Notifications'). 5. Configure the channel, people, and timing. 6. Save your changes. You can create multiple notifications for different channels and times.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
