{"query": "how to check team's punches", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to view employee status on a dashboard or in Slack", "What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?", "How to set up punch in/out reminders"], "generated_answer": "To check your team's punches, you can use the live punch board or Slack:\n\n1. **Live Punch Board:**\n   - Go to the \"Menu\" and select \"Timesheet actions.\"\n   - In the sub-menu, choose \u201cPunchboard\u201d to access the live punch board view.\n   - Alternatively, navigate from the dashboard to time tracking and then punch board.\n   - The punch board provides a filterable, live-updating view of your team's status, showing their last punch time, project, and current status (e.g., in office, on leave).\n\n2. **Slack:**\n   - If status syncing is enabled, team members' Slack statuses will show if they\u2019re in, out, on break, etc.\n   - Send a direct message to AttendanceBot with \u201cpunch card\u201d to get a text summary of everyone's status.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000052710", "reference_answer": "To check your team's punches in AttendanceBot, you can use the live punch board or Slack. Access the punch board through 'Timesheet actions' in the menu for a live view of your team's status, or check Slack statuses if syncing is enabled. You can also message AttendanceBot for a summary.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "real time punches", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to round Slack punch timings to the nearest minute, 6 minutes, 7 minutes, 15 minutes, or more", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to view employee status on a dashboard or in Slack"], "generated_answer": "To view real-time punches, you can use the live punch board or Slack status syncing:\n\n1. **Live Punch Board**:\n   - Go to \"Menu\" > \"Timesheet actions\" > \"Punchboard\" or access it via the dashboard under \"time tracking\" > \"punch board\".\n   - The punch board provides a live-updating view of employee statuses, filterable by office, department, or direct reports.\n\n2. **Slack Status Syncing**:\n   - If your team is auto-syncing with AttendanceBot, their Slack status will reflect their current punch status.\n   - For a text summary, DM AttendanceBot with \u201cpunch card\u201d to get a snapshot of the punch board.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000052710", "reference_answer": "To view real-time punches, use the live punch board or Slack status syncing. Access the punch board via 'Menu' > 'Timesheet actions' > 'Punchboard' for a live view of employee statuses. If synced with Slack, their status reflects current punches. DM AttendanceBot with 'punch card' for a summary.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
