{"query": "One of our admin members is not able to clock in and out. It shared we need to update time from 9/4/25. Everytime I click that day to update time it comes up with \"Server Error\". I have tried to do this throughout the month and it is the only day that won't work. Can you please advise as we need this employee to be able to use attendancebot. Thank you.", "retrieved_contexts": ["What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?", "How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "How to manage AttendanceBot timezone for Slack employees"], "generated_answer": "It seems like you're encountering a \"Server Error\" when trying to update the time for a specific day. Unfortunately, the documentation does not provide specific troubleshooting steps for server errors. I recommend opening a support ticket with AttendanceBot to resolve this issue.\n\nticket", "reference_answer": "It seems like you're encountering a 'Server Error' when trying to update the time for 9/4/25. This could be due to a temporary issue or a specific problem with that date. I recommend checking if the date is within the allowed range for edits. If the issue persists, please open a support ticket with AttendanceBot for further assistance.", "quality_score": 3.8, "bucket": "partial"}
{"query": "I am trying to update a clock in/out time and it says I need to fix the clock out on 9/4, however that page never loads for me so now I can't use attendance bot to clock in and out", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to edit or delete punch in and out times ", "What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?", "How to track time in Slack using AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "To update your clock in/out time in AttendanceBot, follow these steps:\n\n1. From the \"Menu,\" select \"Timesheet actions\" and click on \u201cEdit\u201d to access your timesheet editor.\n2. Choose the date range that includes 9/4 by clicking on the blue \u201cDate Range\u201d dropdown.\n3. Once the timesheet loads, find 9/4 and click \"expand\" to view the punch history for that day.\n4. Click the pencil icon next to the clock out time to edit it. Update the details and hit \"save.\"\n5. If the page doesn't load, try clearing your browser cache or using a different browser.\n\nIf the issue persists, you may need to open a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118260", "reference_answer": "To update your clock in/out time in AttendanceBot, go to the Timesheet actions in the Menu, select Edit, and choose the date range including 9/4. If the page doesn't load, clear your browser cache or try a different browser. If the issue persists, open a support ticket.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "Speak with someone", "retrieved_contexts": ["How can I get help from AttendanceBot support?", "How to apply for leave next year or any future year", "How to change account admin"], "generated_answer": "To speak with someone from AttendanceBot support, you can:\n\n1. Drop an email at support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com.\n2. Email the support lead directly at sarah@harmonizehq.com.\n3. Raise a ticket by messaging 'dialm' as a direct message to AttendanceBot in Slack or Teams.\n4. Chat live using the chat bubble on the AttendanceBot dashboard or website.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118263", "reference_answer": "To speak with someone from AttendanceBot support, you can email support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com, contact the support lead at sarah@harmonizehq.com, raise a ticket via 'dialm' in Slack or Teams, or use the live chat on the AttendanceBot dashboard or website.", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
