{"query": "We\u2019ve been having some issues with AttendanceBot lately. Many team members are reporting that commands aren\u2019t being registered correctly. When employees use the \u201cin\u201d, \u201clunch\u201d, or \u201cout\u201d commands, AttendanceBot sometimes doesn\u2019t register them. This has affected multiple team members and is causing discrepancies in the weekly hours reports. Could you please advise what might be causing these glitches and how we can resolve them? Thank you. ", "retrieved_contexts": ["What can a manager do in AttendanceBot?", "How can I get help from AttendanceBot support?", "How to setup lunch hours for your team"], "generated_answer": "I don't have enough information to diagnose the issue directly. I recommend opening a support ticket for personalized assistance. You can do this by:\n\n1. Messaging 'dialm' as a direct message to AttendanceBot in Slack or Teams.\n2. Click \"Open a ticket\" to start the process.\n\nAlternatively, you can email support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com for further help.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118263", "reference_answer": "It sounds like there may be a technical issue with AttendanceBot not registering commands. Please check if team members are using the correct syntax and ensure there are no connectivity issues. If the problem persists, I recommend opening a support ticket by messaging 'dialm' in Slack or Teams, or emailing support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com for assistance.", "quality_score": 3.6, "bucket": "partial"}
{"query": "Is this bot is free?", "retrieved_contexts": ["How long is my AttendanceBot trial?", "Billing - can I get a discount as a non-profit organization using AttendanceBot?", "How AttendanceBot calculates billing amount for billable clients"], "generated_answer": "AttendanceBot offers a 14-day free trial on Slack and Microsoft Teams. The app is free for teams with 5 users or less. If your team has more than 5 members, you will need to subscribe to the app. You can check the pricing plans here:\n\nhttps://www.attendancebot.com/pricing", "reference_answer": "AttendanceBot offers a 14-day free trial on Slack and Microsoft Teams. The app is free for teams with 5 users or less. For teams with more than 5 members, a subscription is required. You can check the pricing plans here: https://www.attendancebot.com/pricing", "quality_score": 5.0, "bucket": "well_answered"}
{"query": "what is subscription ?", "retrieved_contexts": ["Billing - how does adding or removing users affect my billing?", "Billing - how does adding or removing users affect my billing?", "How do I change my credit card details?"], "generated_answer": "I don't have enough information to answer your question about \"subscription.\" Could you please provide more specific details or context? Alternatively, you can open a support ticket by typing 'ticket'.", "reference_answer": "A subscription in AttendanceBot typically refers to the plan you choose for using the service, which can affect features and billing. For more details, you can check our billing documentation or open a support ticket.", "quality_score": 2.6, "bucket": "partial"}
{"query": "I need help troubleshooting in AttendanceBot", "retrieved_contexts": ["How can I get help from AttendanceBot support?", "How do I learn more about the product?", "How do I install AttendanceBot in Slack?"], "generated_answer": "For troubleshooting in AttendanceBot, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. Direct message \"help\" to AttendanceBot in Slack to get assistance with commands and features.\n2. If you need further help, message \"dialm\" as a direct message to AttendanceBot to open a support ticket.\n3. You can also chat live with support using the chat bubble on the AttendanceBot dashboard or any page of our website.\n4. For additional resources, browse the article database on Freshdesk or check out the quick start guides and YouTube channel.\n\nIf these steps do not resolve your issue, consider reaching out to support via email at support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com.\n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000118263", "reference_answer": "For troubleshooting in AttendanceBot, you can direct message 'help' to AttendanceBot in Slack, open a support ticket by messaging 'dialm', or chat live with support on the AttendanceBot dashboard. For more resources, check the article database on Freshdesk or email support@attendancebot.freshdesk.com if needed.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
