{"query": "what does this track", "retrieved_contexts": ["How to Configure Project, Client, and Task / Subproject Tracking in AttendanceBot", "How to track time spent on a project, task, or client", "How to Configure Project, Client, and Task / Subproject Tracking in AttendanceBot"], "generated_answer": "AttendanceBot tracks time spent on projects, tasks, or clients. It allows users to log time against specific projects, clients, or tasks, which can then be used for reporting and analytics. This includes timesheet reports, project reports, and a project tracking dashboard for detailed analysis of time usage. If you need more specific information, please provide details about what you're interested in tracking. \n\nhttps://attendancebot.freshdesk.com/support/solutions/articles/17000051253", "reference_answer": "AttendanceBot tracks time spent on projects, tasks, or clients, allowing users to log time for reporting and analytics. You can generate timesheet reports and access a project tracking dashboard for detailed analysis.", "quality_score": 4.8, "bucket": "well_answered"}
